{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012ZtVqbwU8EfLgqwuJPqXHw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"1db014de-e144-41c9-babf-9f69871a7eb6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HjkjLpgxSAxkFH7YmiNpCJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→\n    24→import javax.ejb.EJBException;\n    25→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    26→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    27→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    28→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    29→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    30→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    31→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    32→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    33→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    35→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    36→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    37→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    38→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    39→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    40→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    41→import javax.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    42→\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    45→\n    46→@Entity(name = \"accountejb\")\n    47→@Table(name = \"accountejb\")\n    48→public class AccountDataBean implements Serializable {\n    49→\n    50→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 8437841265136840545L;\n    51→\n    52→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    53→    @TableGenerator(name = \"accountIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"account\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    54→    @Id\n    55→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"accountIdGen\")\n    56→    @Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\", nullable = false)\n    57→    private Integer accountID; /* accountID */\n    58→\n    59→    @NotNull\n    60→    @PositiveOrZero\n    61→    @Column(name = \"LOGINCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    62→    private int loginCount; /* loginCount */\n    63→\n    64→    @NotNull\n    65→    @PositiveOrZero\n    66→    @Column(name = \"LOGOUTCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    67→    private int logoutCount; /* logoutCount */\n    68→\n    69→    @Column(name = \"LASTLOGIN\")\n    70→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    71→    @PastOrPresent\n    72→    private Date lastLogin; /* lastLogin Date */\n    73→\n    74→    @Column(name = \"CREATIONDATE\")\n    75→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    76→    @PastOrPresent\n    77→    private Date creationDate; /* creationDate */\n    78→\n    79→    @Column(name = \"BALANCE\")\n    80→    private BigDecimal balance; /* balance */\n    81→\n    82→    @Column(name = \"OPENBALANCE\")\n    83→    private BigDecimal openBalance; /* open balance */\n    84→\n    85→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    86→    private Collection<OrderDataBean> orders;\n    87→\n    88→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    89→    private Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings;\n    90→\n    91→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    92→    @JoinColumn(name = \"PROFILE_USERID\")\n    93→    private AccountProfileDataBean profile;\n    94→\n    95→    /*\n    96→     * Accessor methods for relationship fields are only included for the\n    97→     * AccountProfile profileID\n    98→     */\n    99→    @Transient\n   100→    private String profileID;\n   101→\n   102→    public AccountDataBean() {\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    public AccountDataBean(Integer accountID, int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance,\n   106→            String profileID) {\n   107→        setAccountID(accountID);\n   108→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   109→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   110→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   111→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   112→        setBalance(balance);\n   113→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   114→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public AccountDataBean(int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance, String profileID) {\n   118→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   119→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   120→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   121→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   122→        setBalance(balance);\n   123→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   124→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public static AccountDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   128→        return new AccountDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // accountID\n   129→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // loginCount\n   130→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // logoutCount\n   131→                new java.util.Date(), // lastLogin\n   132→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // creationDate\n   133→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // balance\n   134→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // openBalance\n   135→                TradeConfig.rndUserID() // profileID\n   136→        );\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    @Override\n   140→    public String toString() {\n   141→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Data for account: \" + getAccountID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t  logoutCount:\" + getLogoutCount()\n   142→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"\\n\\t\\t creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t      balance:\" + getBalance()\n   143→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"\\n\\t\\t    profileID:\" + getProfileID();\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public String toHTML() {\n   147→        return \"<BR>Account Data for account: <B>\" + getAccountID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  logoutCount:\"\n   148→                + getLogoutCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   149→                + \"<LI>      balance:\" + getBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    profileID:\" + getProfileID()\n   150→                + \"</LI>\";\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    public void print() {\n   154→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    public Integer getAccountID() {\n   158→        return accountID;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    public void setAccountID(Integer accountID) {\n   162→        this.accountID = accountID;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public int getLoginCount() {\n   166→        return loginCount;\n   167→    }\n   168→\n   169→    public void setLoginCount(int loginCount) {\n   170→        this.loginCount = loginCount;\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public int getLogoutCount() {\n   174→        return logoutCount;\n   175→    }\n   176→\n   177→    public void setLogoutCount(int logoutCount) {\n   178→        this.logoutCount = logoutCount;\n   179→    }\n   180→\n   181→    public Date getLastLogin() {\n   182→        return lastLogin;\n   183→    }\n   184→\n   185→    public void setLastLogin(Date lastLogin) {\n   186→        this.lastLogin = lastLogin;\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    public Date getCreationDate() {\n   190→        return creationDate;\n   191→    }\n   192→\n   193→    public void setCreationDate(Date creationDate) {\n   194→        this.creationDate = creationDate;\n   195→    }\n   196→\n   197→    public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   198→        return balance;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   202→        this.balance = balance;\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   206→        return openBalance;\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   210→        this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   211→    }\n   212→\n   213→    public String getProfileID() {\n   214→        return profileID;\n   215→    }\n   216→\n   217→    public void setProfileID(String profileID) {\n   218→        this.profileID = profileID;\n   219→    }\n   220→\n   221→    /*\n   222→     * Disabled for D185273 public String getUserID() { return getProfileID(); }\n   223→     */\n   224→\n   225→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders() {\n   226→        return orders;\n   227→    }\n   228→\n   229→    public void setOrders(Collection<OrderDataBean> orders) {\n   230→        this.orders = orders;\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings() {\n   234→        return holdings;\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    public void setHoldings(Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings) {\n   238→        this.holdings = holdings;\n   239→    }\n   240→\n   241→    public AccountProfileDataBean getProfile() {\n   242→        return profile;\n   243→    }\n   244→\n   245→    public void setProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profile) {\n   246→        this.profile = profile;\n   247→    }\n   248→\n   249→    public void login(String password) {\n   250→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = getProfile();\n   251→        if ((profile == null) || (profile.getPassword().equals(password) == false)) {\n   252→            String error = \"AccountBean:Login failure for account: \" + getAccountID()\n   253→                    + ((profile == null) ? \"null AccountProfile\" : \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + profile.getUserID() + \":\" + profile.getPassword());\n   254→            throw new EJBException(error);\n   255→        }\n   256→\n   257→        setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   258→        setLoginCount(getLoginCount() + 1);\n   259→    }\n   260→\n   261→    public void logout() {\n   262→        setLogoutCount(getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   263→    }\n   264→\n   265→    @Override\n   266→    public int hashCode() {\n   267→        int hash = 0;\n   268→        hash += (this.accountID != null ? this.accountID.hashCode() : 0);\n   269→        return hash;\n   270→    }\n   271→\n   272→    @Override\n   273→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   274→        \n   275→        if (!(object instanceof AccountDataBean)) {\n   276→            return false;\n   277→        }\n   278→        AccountDataBean other = (AccountDataBean) object;\n   279→\n   280→        if (this.accountID != other.accountID && (this.accountID == null || !this.accountID.equals(other.accountID))) {\n   281→            return false;\n   282→        }\n   283→\n   284→        return true;\n   285→    }\n   286→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"fe69559c-067b-4279-8c6a-d27c8d84ea95"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013Yzb7BzPCUa6xzn5dPFUFF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→//import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    21→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    22→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    24→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    25→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    26→import javax.validation.constraints.Email;\n    27→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    28→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    32→\n    33→@Entity(name = \"accountprofileejb\")\n    34→@Table(name = \"accountprofileejb\")\n    35→public class AccountProfileDataBean implements java.io.Serializable {\n    36→\n    37→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    38→\n    39→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2794584136675420624L;\n    40→\n    41→    @Id\n    42→    @NotNull\n    43→    @Column(name = \"USERID\", nullable = false)\n    44→    private String userID; /* userID */\n    45→\n    46→    @Column(name = \"PASSWD\")\n    47→    @NotBlank\n    48→    private String passwd; /* password */\n    49→\n    50→    @Column(name = \"FULLNAME\")\n    51→    @NotBlank\n    52→    private String fullName; /* fullName */\n    53→\n    54→    @Column(name = \"ADDRESS\")\n    55→    @NotBlank\n    56→    private String address; /* address */\n    57→\n    58→    @Column(name = \"EMAIL\")\n    59→    @Email(message = \"Email should be valid\")\n    60→    private String email; /* email */\n    61→\n    62→    @Column(name = \"CREDITCARD\")\n    63→    @NotBlank\n    64→    private String creditCard; /* creditCard */\n    65→\n    66→    @OneToOne(mappedBy = \"profile\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    67→    private AccountDataBean account;\n    68→\n    69→    public AccountProfileDataBean() {\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    public AccountProfileDataBean(String userID, String password, String fullName, String address, String email, String creditCard) {\n    73→        setUserID(userID);\n    74→        setPassword(password);\n    75→        setFullName(fullName);\n    76→        setAddress(address);\n    77→        setEmail(email);\n    78→        setCreditCard(creditCard);\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    public static AccountProfileDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    82→        return new AccountProfileDataBean(TradeConfig.rndUserID(), // userID\n    83→                TradeConfig.rndUserID(), // passwd\n    84→                TradeConfig.rndFullName(), // fullname\n    85→                TradeConfig.rndAddress(), // address\n    86→                TradeConfig.rndEmail(TradeConfig.rndUserID()), // email\n    87→                TradeConfig.rndCreditCard() // creditCard\n    88→        );\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    @Override\n    92→    public String toString() {\n    93→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Profile Data for userID:\" + getUserID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   passwd:\" + getPassword() + \"\\n\\t\\t   fullName:\" + getFullName()\n    94→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    address:\" + getAddress() + \"\\n\\t\\t      email:\" + getEmail() + \"\\n\\t\\t creditCard:\" + getCreditCard();\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    public String toHTML() {\n    98→        return \"<BR>Account Profile Data for userID: <B>\" + getUserID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   passwd:\" + getPassword() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>   fullName:\"\n    99→                + getFullName() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    address:\" + getAddress() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      email:\" + getEmail() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creditCard:\"\n   100→                + getCreditCard() + \"</LI>\";\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public void print() {\n   104→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public String getUserID() {\n   108→        return userID;\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public void setUserID(String userID) {\n   112→        this.userID = userID;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public String getPassword() {\n   116→        return passwd;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public void setPassword(String password) {\n   120→        this.passwd = password;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public String getFullName() {\n   124→        return fullName;\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public void setFullName(String fullName) {\n   128→        this.fullName = fullName;\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public String getAddress() {\n   132→        return address;\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    public void setAddress(String address) {\n   136→        this.address = address;\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    public String getEmail() {\n   140→        return email;\n   141→    }\n   142→\n   143→    public void setEmail(String email) {\n   144→        this.email = email;\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    public String getCreditCard() {\n   148→        return creditCard;\n   149→    }\n   150→\n   151→    public void setCreditCard(String creditCard) {\n   152→        this.creditCard = creditCard;\n   153→    }\n   154→\n   155→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   156→        return account;\n   157→    }\n   158→\n   159→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   160→        this.account = account;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    @Override\n   164→    public int hashCode() {\n   165→        int hash = 0;\n   166→        hash += (this.userID != null ? this.userID.hashCode() : 0);\n   167→        return hash;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    @Override\n   171→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   172→       \n   173→        if (!(object instanceof AccountProfileDataBean)) {\n   174→            return false;\n   175→        }\n   176→        AccountProfileDataBean other = (AccountProfileDataBean) object;\n   177→\n   178→        if (this.userID != other.userID && (this.userID == null || !this.userID.equals(other.userID))) {\n   179→            return false;\n   180→        }\n   181→\n   182→        return true;\n   183→    }\n   184→}\n   185→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"a48f0b4d-3670-4f27-92ea-b84dbef28e5a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014PHK4Wb6pvhBBgcMrpAZJ9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.Date;\n    21→\n    22→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    24→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    25→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    26→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    27→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    28→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    29→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    30→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    31→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    32→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    33→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    35→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    36→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    37→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    38→\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    41→\n    42→@Entity(name = \"holdingejb\")\n    43→@Table(name = \"holdingejb\")\n    44→public class HoldingDataBean implements Serializable {\n    45→\n    46→    /* persistent/relationship fields */\n    47→\n    48→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -2338411656251935480L;\n    49→\n    50→    @Id\n    51→    @TableGenerator(name = \"holdingIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"holding\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    52→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"holdingIdGen\")\n    53→    @Column(name = \"HOLDINGID\", nullable = false)\n    54→    private Integer holdingID; /* holdingID */\n    55→\n    56→    @NotNull\n    57→    @Positive\n    58→    @Column(name = \"QUANTITY\", nullable = false)\n    59→    private double quantity; /* quantity */\n    60→\n    61→    @Column(name = \"PURCHASEPRICE\")\n    62→    @Positive\n    63→    private BigDecimal purchasePrice; /* purchasePrice */\n    64→\n    65→    @Column(name = \"PURCHASEDATE\")\n    66→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    67→    @PastOrPresent\n    68→    private Date purchaseDate; /* purchaseDate */\n    69→\n    70→    @Transient\n    71→    private String quoteID; /* Holding(*) ---> Quote(1) */\n    72→\n    73→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    74→    @JoinColumn(name = \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID\")\n    75→    private AccountDataBean account;\n    76→\n    77→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    78→    @JoinColumn(name = \"QUOTE_SYMBOL\")\n    79→    private QuoteDataBean quote;\n    80→\n    81→    public HoldingDataBean() {\n    82→    }\n    83→\n    84→    public HoldingDataBean(Integer holdingID, double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice, Date purchaseDate, String quoteID) {\n    85→        setHoldingID(holdingID);\n    86→        setQuantity(quantity);\n    87→        setPurchasePrice(purchasePrice);\n    88→        setPurchaseDate(purchaseDate);\n    89→        setQuoteID(quoteID);\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    public HoldingDataBean(double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice, Date purchaseDate, AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote) {\n    93→        setQuantity(quantity);\n    94→        setPurchasePrice(purchasePrice);\n    95→        setPurchaseDate(purchaseDate);\n    96→        setAccount(account);\n    97→        setQuote(quote);\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public static HoldingDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   101→        return new HoldingDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // holdingID\n   102→                TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), // quantity\n   103→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // purchasePrice\n   104→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // purchaseDate\n   105→                TradeConfig.rndSymbol() // symbol\n   106→        );\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Override\n   110→    public String toString() {\n   111→        return \"\\n\\tHolding Data for holding: \" + getHoldingID() + \"\\n\\t\\t      quantity:\" + getQuantity() + \"\\n\\t\\t purchasePrice:\" + getPurchasePrice()\n   112→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  purchaseDate:\" + getPurchaseDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t       quoteID:\" + getQuoteID();\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public String toHTML() {\n   116→        return \"<BR>Holding Data for holding: \" + getHoldingID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>      quantity:\" + getQuantity() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> purchasePrice:\"\n   117→                + getPurchasePrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  purchaseDate:\" + getPurchaseDate() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       quoteID:\" + getQuoteID() + \"</LI>\";\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public void print() {\n   121→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   122→    }\n   123→\n   124→    public Integer getHoldingID() {\n   125→        return holdingID;\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    public void setHoldingID(Integer holdingID) {\n   129→        this.holdingID = holdingID;\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    public double getQuantity() {\n   133→        return quantity;\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    public void setQuantity(double quantity) {\n   137→        this.quantity = quantity;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public BigDecimal getPurchasePrice() {\n   141→        return purchasePrice;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public void setPurchasePrice(BigDecimal purchasePrice) {\n   145→        this.purchasePrice = purchasePrice;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public Date getPurchaseDate() {\n   149→        return purchaseDate;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public void setPurchaseDate(Date purchaseDate) {\n   153→        this.purchaseDate = purchaseDate;\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public String getQuoteID() {\n   157→        if (quote != null) {\n   158→            return quote.getSymbol();\n   159→        }\n   160→        return quoteID;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    public void setQuoteID(String quoteID) {\n   164→        this.quoteID = quoteID;\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   168→        return account;\n   169→    }\n   170→\n   171→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   172→        this.account = account;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote() {\n   176→        return quote;\n   177→    }\n   178→\n   179→    public void setQuote(QuoteDataBean quote) {\n   180→        this.quote = quote;\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Override\n   184→    public int hashCode() {\n   185→        int hash = 0;\n   186→        hash += (this.holdingID != null ? this.holdingID.hashCode() : 0);\n   187→        return hash;\n   188→    }\n   189→\n   190→    @Override\n   191→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   192→        \n   193→        if (!(object instanceof HoldingDataBean)) {\n   194→            return false;\n   195→        }\n   196→        HoldingDataBean other = (HoldingDataBean) object;\n   197→\n   198→        if (this.holdingID != other.holdingID && (this.holdingID == null || !this.holdingID.equals(other.holdingID))) {\n   199→            return false;\n   200→        }\n   201→\n   202→        return true;\n   203→    }\n   204→}\n   205→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"6b36f705-022f-4a13-b7e2-4c985ec3e1c0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GekSCVP3Czgeq5kFKaM3tE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→//import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    21→import java.util.Date;\n    22→\n    23→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    24→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    25→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    26→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    27→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    28→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    29→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    30→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    31→import javax.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    32→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    33→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    35→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    36→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    37→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    38→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    39→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    40→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    41→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    42→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    43→\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    45→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    46→\n    47→@Entity(name = \"orderejb\")\n    48→@Table(name = \"orderejb\")\n    49→@NamedQueries({\n    50→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderfee\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderFee = :orderfee\"),\n    51→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByCompletiondate\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.completionDate = :completiondate\"),\n    52→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrdertype\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderType = :ordertype\"),\n    53→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderstatus\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = :orderstatus\"),\n    54→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByPrice\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.price = :price\"),\n    55→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByQuantity\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.quantity = :quantity\"),\n    56→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOpendate\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.openDate = :opendate\"),\n    57→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderID = :orderid\"),\n    58→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByAccountAccountid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.account.accountID = :accountAccountid\"),\n    59→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByQuoteSymbol\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.quote.symbol = :quoteSymbol\"),\n    60→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByHoldingHoldingid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.holding.holdingID = :holdingHoldingid\"),\n    61→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.closedOrders\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\"),\n    62→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.completeClosedOrders\", query = \"UPDATE orderejb o SET o.orderStatus = 'completed' WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\") })\n    63→public class OrderDataBean implements Serializable {\n    64→\n    65→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 120650490200739057L;\n    66→\n    67→    @Id\n    68→    @TableGenerator(name = \"orderIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"order\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    69→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"orderIdGen\")\n    70→    @Column(name = \"ORDERID\", nullable = false)\n    71→    private Integer orderID; /* orderID */\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = \"ORDERTYPE\")\n    74→    @NotBlank\n    75→    private String orderType; /* orderType (buy, sell, etc.) */\n    76→\n    77→    @Column(name = \"ORDERSTATUS\")\n    78→    @NotBlank\n    79→    private String orderStatus; /*\n    80→                                 * orderStatus (open, processing, completed,\n    81→                                 * closed, cancelled)\n    82→                                 */\n    83→\n    84→    @Column(name = \"OPENDATE\")\n    85→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    86→    @PastOrPresent\n    87→    private Date openDate; /* openDate (when the order was entered) */\n    88→\n    89→    @Column(name = \"COMPLETIONDATE\")\n    90→    @PastOrPresent\n    91→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    92→    private Date completionDate; /* completionDate */\n    93→\n    94→    @NotNull\n    95→    @Column(name = \"QUANTITY\", nullable = false)\n    96→    private double quantity; /* quantity */\n    97→\n    98→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    99→    @Positive\n   100→    private BigDecimal price; /* price */\n   101→\n   102→    @Column(name = \"ORDERFEE\")\n   103→    @Positive\n   104→    private BigDecimal orderFee; /* price */\n   105→\n   106→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n   107→    @JoinColumn(name = \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID\")\n   108→    private AccountDataBean account;\n   109→\n   110→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n   111→    @JoinColumn(name = \"QUOTE_SYMBOL\")\n   112→    private QuoteDataBean quote;\n   113→\n   114→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n   115→    @JoinColumn(name = \"HOLDING_HOLDINGID\")\n   116→    private HoldingDataBean holding;\n   117→\n   118→    /* Fields for relationship fields are not kept in the Data Bean */\n   119→    @Transient\n   120→    private String symbol;\n   121→\n   122→    public OrderDataBean() {\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    public OrderDataBean(Integer orderID, String orderType, String orderStatus, Date openDate, Date completionDate, double quantity, BigDecimal price,\n   126→            BigDecimal orderFee, String symbol) {\n   127→        setOrderID(orderID);\n   128→        setOrderType(orderType);\n   129→        setOrderStatus(orderStatus);\n   130→        setOpenDate(openDate);\n   131→        setCompletionDate(completionDate);\n   132→        setQuantity(quantity);\n   133→        setPrice(price);\n   134→        setOrderFee(orderFee);\n   135→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public OrderDataBean(String orderType, String orderStatus, Date openDate, Date completionDate, double quantity, BigDecimal price, BigDecimal orderFee,\n   139→            AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding) {\n   140→        setOrderType(orderType);\n   141→        setOrderStatus(orderStatus);\n   142→        setOpenDate(openDate);\n   143→        setCompletionDate(completionDate);\n   144→        setQuantity(quantity);\n   145→        setPrice(price);\n   146→        setOrderFee(orderFee);\n   147→        setAccount(account);\n   148→        setQuote(quote);\n   149→        setHolding(holding);\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public static OrderDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   153→        return new OrderDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), TradeConfig.rndBoolean() ? \"buy\" : \"sell\", \"open\", new java.util.Date(\n   154→                TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), TradeConfig.rndQuantity(),\n   155→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), TradeConfig.rndSymbol());\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    @Override\n   159→    public String toString() {\n   160→        return \"Order \" + getOrderID() + \"\\n\\t      orderType: \" + getOrderType() + \"\\n\\t    orderStatus: \" + getOrderStatus() + \"\\n\\t       openDate: \"\n   161→                + getOpenDate() + \"\\n\\t completionDate: \" + getCompletionDate() + \"\\n\\t       quantity: \" + getQuantity() + \"\\n\\t          price: \"\n   162→                + getPrice() + \"\\n\\t       orderFee: \" + getOrderFee() + \"\\n\\t         symbol: \" + getSymbol();\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public String toHTML() {\n   166→        return \"<BR>Order <B>\" + getOrderID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>      orderType: \" + getOrderType() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    orderStatus: \" + getOrderStatus()\n   167→                + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       openDate: \" + getOpenDate() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> completionDate: \" + getCompletionDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   168→                + \"<LI>       quantity: \" + getQuantity() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>          price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       orderFee: \" + getOrderFee()\n   169→                + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>         symbol: \" + getSymbol() + \"</LI>\";\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public void print() {\n   173→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    public Integer getOrderID() {\n   177→        return orderID;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    public void setOrderID(Integer orderID) {\n   181→        this.orderID = orderID;\n   182→    }\n   183→\n   184→    public String getOrderType() {\n   185→        return orderType;\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    public void setOrderType(String orderType) {\n   189→        this.orderType = orderType;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    public String getOrderStatus() {\n   193→        return orderStatus;\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    public void setOrderStatus(String orderStatus) {\n   197→        this.orderStatus = orderStatus;\n   198→    }\n   199→\n   200→    public Date getOpenDate() {\n   201→        return openDate;\n   202→    }\n   203→\n   204→    public void setOpenDate(Date openDate) {\n   205→        this.openDate = openDate;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    public Date getCompletionDate() {\n   209→        return completionDate;\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    public void setCompletionDate(Date completionDate) {\n   213→        this.completionDate = completionDate;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    public double getQuantity() {\n   217→        return quantity;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    public void setQuantity(double quantity) {\n   221→        this.quantity = quantity;\n   222→    }\n   223→\n   224→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n   225→        return price;\n   226→    }\n   227→\n   228→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   229→        this.price = price;\n   230→    }\n   231→\n   232→    public BigDecimal getOrderFee() {\n   233→        return orderFee;\n   234→    }\n   235→\n   236→    public void setOrderFee(BigDecimal orderFee) {\n   237→        this.orderFee = orderFee;\n   238→    }\n   239→\n   240→    public String getSymbol() {\n   241→        if (quote != null) {\n   242→            return quote.getSymbol();\n   243→        }\n   244→        return symbol;\n   245→    }\n   246→\n   247→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   248→        this.symbol = symbol;\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   252→        return account;\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   256→        this.account = account;\n   257→    }\n   258→\n   259→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote() {\n   260→        return quote;\n   261→    }\n   262→\n   263→    public void setQuote(QuoteDataBean quote) {\n   264→        this.quote = quote;\n   265→    }\n   266→\n   267→    public HoldingDataBean getHolding() {\n   268→        return holding;\n   269→    }\n   270→\n   271→    public void setHolding(HoldingDataBean holding) {\n   272→        this.holding = holding;\n   273→    }\n   274→\n   275→    public boolean isBuy() {\n   276→        String orderType = getOrderType();\n   277→        if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"buy\") == 0) {\n   278→            return true;\n   279→        }\n   280→        return false;\n   281→    }\n   282→\n   283→    public boolean isSell() {\n   284→        String orderType = getOrderType();\n   285→        if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"sell\") == 0) {\n   286→            return true;\n   287→        }\n   288→        return false;\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    public boolean isOpen() {\n   292→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   293→        if ((orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"open\") == 0) || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"processing\") == 0)) {\n   294→            return true;\n   295→        }\n   296→        return false;\n   297→    }\n   298→\n   299→    public boolean isCompleted() {\n   300→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   301→        if ((orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"completed\") == 0) || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"alertcompleted\") == 0)\n   302→                || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"cancelled\") == 0)) {\n   303→            return true;\n   304→        }\n   305→        return false;\n   306→    }\n   307→\n   308→    public boolean isCancelled() {\n   309→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   310→        if (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"cancelled\") == 0) {\n   311→            return true;\n   312→        }\n   313→        return false;\n   314→    }\n   315→\n   316→    public void cancel() {\n   317→        setOrderStatus(\"cancelled\");\n   318→    }\n   319→\n   320→    @Override\n   321→    public int hashCode() {\n   322→        int hash = 0;\n   323→        hash += (this.orderID != null ? this.orderID.hashCode() : 0);\n   324→        return hash;\n   325→    }\n   326→\n   327→    @Override\n   328→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   329→        \n   330→        if (!(object instanceof OrderDataBean)) {\n   331→            return false;\n   332→        }\n   333→        OrderDataBean other = (OrderDataBean) object;\n   334→        if (this.orderID != other.orderID && (this.orderID == null || !this.orderID.equals(other.orderID))) {\n   335→            return false;\n   336→        }\n   337→        return true;\n   338→    }\n   339→}\n   340→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"d382d1c4-c4ce-4ac6-86e1-29b240779df6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013HjK5fcKwRy4HtRYpPZSir","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    22→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    24→import javax.persistence.NamedNativeQueries;\n    25→import javax.persistence.NamedNativeQuery;\n    26→import javax.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    27→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    28→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    29→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    30→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    31→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→@Entity(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    37→@Table(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    38→@NamedQueries({\n    39→        @NamedQuery(name = \"quoteejb.allQuotes\", query = \"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q\")})\n    40→@NamedNativeQueries({ @NamedNativeQuery(name = \"quoteejb.quoteForUpdate\", query = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=? for update\", resultClass = com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean.class) })\n    41→public class QuoteDataBean implements Serializable {\n    42→\n    43→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    44→\n    45→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1847932261895838791L;\n    46→\n    47→    @Id\n    48→    @NotNull\n    49→    @Column(name = \"SYMBOL\", nullable = false)\n    50→    private String symbol; /* symbol */\n    51→\n    52→    @Column(name = \"COMPANYNAME\")\n    53→    @NotBlank\n    54→    private String companyName; /* companyName */\n    55→\n    56→    @NotNull\n    57→    @Column(name = \"VOLUME\", nullable = false)\n    58→    private double volume; /* volume */\n    59→\n    60→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    61→    @Positive\n    62→    private BigDecimal price; /* price */\n    63→\n    64→    @Column(name = \"OPEN1\")\n    65→    @Positive\n    66→    private BigDecimal open1; /* open1 price */\n    67→\n    68→    @Column(name = \"LOW\")\n    69→    @Positive\n    70→    private BigDecimal low; /* low price */\n    71→\n    72→    @Column(name = \"HIGH\")\n    73→    @Positive\n    74→    private BigDecimal high; /* high price */\n    75→\n    76→    @NotNull\n    77→    @Column(name = \"CHANGE1\", nullable = false)\n    78→    private double change1; /* price change */\n    79→\n    80→    /* Accessor methods for relationship fields are not kept in the DataBean */\n    81→\n    82→    public QuoteDataBean() {\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol, String companyName, double volume, BigDecimal price, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high, double change) {\n    86→        setSymbol(symbol);\n    87→        setCompanyName(companyName);\n    88→        setVolume(volume);\n    89→        setPrice(price);\n    90→        setOpen(open);\n    91→        setLow(low);\n    92→        setHigh(high);\n    93→        setChange(change);\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    public static QuoteDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    97→        return new QuoteDataBean(TradeConfig.rndSymbol(), // symbol\n    98→                TradeConfig.rndSymbol() + \" Incorporated\", // Company Name\n    99→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000), // volume\n   100→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // price\n   101→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // open1\n   102→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // low\n   103→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // high\n   104→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000) // volume\n   105→        );\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    // Create a \"zero\" value quoteDataBean for the given symbol\n   109→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol) {\n   110→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    @Override\n   114→    public String toString() {\n   115→        return \"\\n\\tQuote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t\\t companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"\\n\\t\\t       price: \"\n   116→                + getPrice() + \"\\n\\t\\t        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"\\n\\t\\t         low: \" + getLow() + \"\\n\\t\\t        high: \" + getHigh()\n   117→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      change1: \" + getChange();\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public String toHTML() {\n   121→        return \"<BR>Quote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"<LI> companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\"\n   122→                + \"<LI>       price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>         low: \" + getLow() + \"</LI>\"\n   123→                + \"<LI>        high: \" + getHigh() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      change1: \" + getChange() + \"</LI>\";\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    public void print() {\n   127→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public String getSymbol() {\n   131→        return symbol;\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   135→        this.symbol = symbol;\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public String getCompanyName() {\n   139→        return companyName;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    public void setCompanyName(String companyName) {\n   143→        this.companyName = companyName;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n   147→        return price;\n   148→    }\n   149→\n   150→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   151→        this.price = price;\n   152→    }\n   153→\n   154→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   155→        return open1;\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   159→        this.open1 = open;\n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   163→        return low;\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   167→        this.low = low;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   171→        return high;\n   172→    }\n   173→\n   174→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   175→        this.high = high;\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→    public double getChange() {\n   179→        return change1;\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→    public void setChange(double change) {\n   183→        this.change1 = change;\n   184→    }\n   185→\n   186→    public double getVolume() {\n   187→        return volume;\n   188→    }\n   189→\n   190→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   191→        this.volume = volume;\n   192→    }\n   193→\n   194→    @Override\n   195→    public int hashCode() {\n   196→        int hash = 0;\n   197→        hash += (this.symbol != null ? this.symbol.hashCode() : 0);\n   198→        return hash;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    @Override\n   202→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   203→        \n   204→        if (!(object instanceof QuoteDataBean)) {\n   205→            return false;\n   206→        }\n   207→        QuoteDataBean other = (QuoteDataBean) object;\n   208→        if (this.symbol != other.symbol && (this.symbol == null || !this.symbol.equals(other.symbol))) {\n   209→            return false;\n   210→        }\n   211→        return true;\n   212→    }\n   213→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"be906f84-3b6d-44d6-81a3-2e8007b5be6d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QwL13cuoqYyAxpafxya7r7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import javax.json.Json;\n    26→import javax.json.JsonObject;\n    27→import javax.json.JsonObjectBuilder;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→public class MarketSummaryDataBean implements Serializable {\n    35→\n    36→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 650652242288745600L;\n    37→    private BigDecimal TSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average */\n    38→    private BigDecimal openTSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average at the open */\n    39→    private double volume; /* volume of shares traded */\n    40→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers; /*\n    41→                                                   * Collection of top gaining\n    42→                                                   * stocks\n    43→                                                   */\n    44→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers; /*\n    45→                                                  * Collection of top losing\n    46→                                                  * stocks\n    47→                                                  */\n    48→    // FUTURE private Collection topVolume; /* Collection of top stocks by\n    49→    // volume */\n    50→    private Date summaryDate; /* Date this summary was taken */\n    51→\n    52→    // cache the gainPercent once computed for this bean\n    53→    private BigDecimal gainPercent = null;\n    54→\n    55→    public MarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public MarketSummaryDataBean(BigDecimal TSIA, BigDecimal openTSIA, double volume, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers// , Collection topVolume\n    59→    ) {\n    60→        setTSIA(TSIA);\n    61→        setOpenTSIA(openTSIA);\n    62→        setVolume(volume);\n    63→        setTopGainers(topGainers);\n    64→        setTopLosers(topLosers);\n    65→        setSummaryDate(new java.sql.Date(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n    66→        gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n    67→\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public static MarketSummaryDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    71→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> gain = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    72→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> lose = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    73→\n    74→        for (int ii = 0; ii < 5; ii++) {\n    75→            QuoteDataBean quote1 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    76→            QuoteDataBean quote2 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    77→\n    78→            gain.add(quote1);\n    79→            lose.add(quote2);\n    80→        }\n    81→\n    82→        return new MarketSummaryDataBean(TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), gain, lose);\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @Override\n    86→    public String toString() {\n    87→        String ret = \"\\n\\tMarket Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"\\n\\t\\t    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA()\n    88→                + \"\\n\\t\\t        gain:\" + getGainPercent() + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume:\" + getVolume();\n    89→\n    90→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n    91→            return ret;\n    92→        }\n    93→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Gainers:\";\n    94→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n    95→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n    96→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n    97→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n    98→        }\n    99→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Losers:\";\n   100→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n   101→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   102→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   103→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n   104→        }\n   105→        return ret;\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    public String toHTML() {\n   109→        String ret = \"<BR>Market Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"<LI>        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA() + \"</LI>\"\n   110→                + \"<LI>      volume:\" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\";\n   111→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n   112→            return ret;\n   113→        }\n   114→        ret += \"<BR> Current Top Gainers:\";\n   115→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n   116→\n   117→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   118→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   119→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   120→        }\n   121→        ret += \"<BR>   Current Top Losers:\";\n   122→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n   123→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   124→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   125→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   126→        }\n   127→        return ret;\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public JsonObject toJSON() {\n   131→        \n   132→        JsonObjectBuilder jObjectBuilder = Json.createObjectBuilder();\n   133→        \n   134→        int i = 1;\n   135→        for (Iterator<QuoteDataBean> iterator = topGainers.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   136→            QuoteDataBean quote = iterator.next();\n   137→\n   138→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_stock\",quote.getSymbol());\n   139→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_price\",\"$\" + quote.getPrice());\n   140→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_change\",quote.getChange());\n   141→            i++;\n   142→        }\n   143→\n   144→        i = 1;\n   145→        for (Iterator<QuoteDataBean> iterator = topLosers.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   146→            QuoteDataBean quote = iterator.next();\n   147→\n   148→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_stock\",quote.getSymbol());\n   149→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_price\",\"$\" + quote.getPrice());\n   150→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_change\",quote.getChange());\n   151→            i++;\n   152→        }\n   153→\n   154→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"tsia\", TSIA);\n   155→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"volume\",volume);\n   156→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"date\", summaryDate.toString());\n   157→\n   158→        return jObjectBuilder.build();\n   159→        \n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public void print() {\n   163→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   167→        if (gainPercent == null) {\n   168→            gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n   169→        }\n   170→        return gainPercent;\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    /**\n   174→     * Gets the tSIA\n   175→     *\n   176→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   177→     */\n   178→    public BigDecimal getTSIA() {\n   179→        return TSIA;\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→    /**\n   183→     * Sets the tSIA\n   184→     *\n   185→     * @param tSIA\n   186→     *            The tSIA to set\n   187→     */\n   188→    public void setTSIA(BigDecimal tSIA) {\n   189→        TSIA = tSIA;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    /**\n   193→     * Gets the openTSIA\n   194→     *\n   195→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   196→     */\n   197→    public BigDecimal getOpenTSIA() {\n   198→        return openTSIA;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    /**\n   202→     * Sets the openTSIA\n   203→     *\n   204→     * @param openTSIA\n   205→     *            The openTSIA to set\n   206→     */\n   207→    public void setOpenTSIA(BigDecimal openTSIA) {\n   208→        this.openTSIA = openTSIA;\n   209→    }\n   210→\n   211→    /**\n   212→     * Gets the volume\n   213→     *\n   214→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   215→     */\n   216→    public double getVolume() {\n   217→        return volume;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    /**\n   221→     * Sets the volume\n   222→     *\n   223→     * @param volume\n   224→     *            The volume to set\n   225→     */\n   226→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   227→        this.volume = volume;\n   228→    }\n   229→\n   230→    /**\n   231→     * Gets the topGainers\n   232→     *\n   233→     * @return Returns a Collection\n   234→     */\n   235→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopGainers() {\n   236→        return topGainers;\n   237→    }\n   238→\n   239→    /**\n   240→     * Sets the topGainers\n   241→     *\n   242→     * @param topGainers\n   243→     *            The topGainers to set\n   244→     */\n   245→    public void setTopGainers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers) {\n   246→        this.topGainers = topGainers;\n   247→    }\n   248→\n   249→    /**\n   250→     * Gets the topLosers\n   251→     *\n   252→     * @return Returns a Collection\n   253→     */\n   254→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopLosers() {\n   255→        return topLosers;\n   256→    }\n   257→\n   258→    /**\n   259→     * Sets the topLosers\n   260→     *\n   261→     * @param topLosers\n   262→     *            The topLosers to set\n   263→     */\n   264→    public void setTopLosers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n   265→        this.topLosers = topLosers;\n   266→    }\n   267→\n   268→    /**\n   269→     * Gets the summaryDate\n   270→     *\n   271→     * @return Returns a Date\n   272→     */\n   273→    public Date getSummaryDate() {\n   274→        return summaryDate;\n   275→    }\n   276→\n   277→    /**\n   278→     * Sets the summaryDate\n   279→     *\n   280→     * @param summaryDate\n   281→     *            The summaryDate to set\n   282→     */\n   283→    public void setSummaryDate(Date summaryDate) {\n   284→        this.summaryDate = summaryDate;\n   285→    }\n   286→\n   287→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"48f76330-03d3-4389-aace-9f5004e8a1ea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TJa7RTi7Y1gwHmtCash9AS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→\n    20→public class RunStatsDataBean implements Serializable {\n    21→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 4017778674103242167L;\n    22→\n    23→    // Constructors\n    24→    public RunStatsDataBean() {\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    // count of trade users in the database (users w/ userID like 'uid:%')\n    28→    private int tradeUserCount;\n    29→    // count of trade stocks in the database (stocks w/ symbol like 's:%')\n    30→    private int tradeStockCount;\n    31→\n    32→    // count of new registered users in this run (users w/ userID like 'ru:%')\n    33→    // -- random user\n    34→    private int newUserCount;\n    35→\n    36→    // sum of logins by trade users\n    37→    private int sumLoginCount;\n    38→    // sum of logouts by trade users\n    39→    private int sumLogoutCount;\n    40→\n    41→    // count of holdings of trade users\n    42→    private int holdingCount;\n    43→\n    44→    // count of orders of trade users\n    45→    private int orderCount;\n    46→    // count of buy orders of trade users\n    47→    private int buyOrderCount;\n    48→    // count of sell orders of trade users\n    49→    private int sellOrderCount;\n    50→    // count of cancelled orders of trade users\n    51→    private int cancelledOrderCount;\n    52→    // count of open orders of trade users\n    53→    private int openOrderCount;\n    54→    // count of orders deleted during this trade Reset\n    55→    private int deletedOrderCount;\n    56→\n    57→    @Override\n    58→    public String toString() {\n    59→        return \"\\n\\tRunStatsData for reset at \" + new java.util.Date() + \"\\n\\t\\t      tradeUserCount: \" + getTradeUserCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t        newUserCount: \"\n    60→                + getNewUserCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t       sumLoginCount: \" + getSumLoginCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t      sumLogoutCount: \" + getSumLogoutCount()\n    61→                + \"\\n\\t\\t        holdingCount: \" + getHoldingCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t          orderCount: \" + getOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t       buyOrderCount: \"\n    62→                + getBuyOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t      sellOrderCount: \" + getSellOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t cancelledOrderCount: \" + getCancelledOrderCount()\n    63→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      openOrderCount: \" + getOpenOrderCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t   deletedOrderCount: \" + getDeletedOrderCount();\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Gets the tradeUserCount\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @return Returns a int\n    70→     */\n    71→    public int getTradeUserCount() {\n    72→        return tradeUserCount;\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    /**\n    76→     * Sets the tradeUserCount\n    77→     *\n    78→     * @param tradeUserCount\n    79→     *            The tradeUserCount to set\n    80→     */\n    81→    public void setTradeUserCount(int tradeUserCount) {\n    82→        this.tradeUserCount = tradeUserCount;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    /**\n    86→     * Gets the newUserCount\n    87→     *\n    88→     * @return Returns a int\n    89→     */\n    90→    public int getNewUserCount() {\n    91→        return newUserCount;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    /**\n    95→     * Sets the newUserCount\n    96→     *\n    97→     * @param newUserCount\n    98→     *            The newUserCount to set\n    99→     */\n   100→    public void setNewUserCount(int newUserCount) {\n   101→        this.newUserCount = newUserCount;\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    /**\n   105→     * Gets the sumLoginCount\n   106→     *\n   107→     * @return Returns a int\n   108→     */\n   109→    public int getSumLoginCount() {\n   110→        return sumLoginCount;\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * Sets the sumLoginCount\n   115→     *\n   116→     * @param sumLoginCount\n   117→     *            The sumLoginCount to set\n   118→     */\n   119→    public void setSumLoginCount(int sumLoginCount) {\n   120→        this.sumLoginCount = sumLoginCount;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Gets the sumLogoutCount\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return Returns a int\n   127→     */\n   128→    public int getSumLogoutCount() {\n   129→        return sumLogoutCount;\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    /**\n   133→     * Sets the sumLogoutCount\n   134→     *\n   135→     * @param sumLogoutCount\n   136→     *            The sumLogoutCount to set\n   137→     */\n   138→    public void setSumLogoutCount(int sumLogoutCount) {\n   139→        this.sumLogoutCount = sumLogoutCount;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    /**\n   143→     * Gets the holdingCount\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @return Returns a int\n   146→     */\n   147→    public int getHoldingCount() {\n   148→        return holdingCount;\n   149→    }\n   150→\n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Sets the holdingCount\n   153→     *\n   154→     * @param holdingCount\n   155→     *            The holdingCount to set\n   156→     */\n   157→    public void setHoldingCount(int holdingCount) {\n   158→        this.holdingCount = holdingCount;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    /**\n   162→     * Gets the buyOrderCount\n   163→     *\n   164→     * @return Returns a int\n   165→     */\n   166→    public int getBuyOrderCount() {\n   167→        return buyOrderCount;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    /**\n   171→     * Sets the buyOrderCount\n   172→     *\n   173→     * @param buyOrderCount\n   174→     *            The buyOrderCount to set\n   175→     */\n   176→    public void setBuyOrderCount(int buyOrderCount) {\n   177→        this.buyOrderCount = buyOrderCount;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    /**\n   181→     * Gets the sellOrderCount\n   182→     *\n   183→     * @return Returns a int\n   184→     */\n   185→    public int getSellOrderCount() {\n   186→        return sellOrderCount;\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    /**\n   190→     * Sets the sellOrderCount\n   191→     *\n   192→     * @param sellOrderCount\n   193→     *            The sellOrderCount to set\n   194→     */\n   195→    public void setSellOrderCount(int sellOrderCount) {\n   196→        this.sellOrderCount = sellOrderCount;\n   197→    }\n   198→\n   199→    /**\n   200→     * Gets the cancelledOrderCount\n   201→     *\n   202→     * @return Returns a int\n   203→     */\n   204→    public int getCancelledOrderCount() {\n   205→        return cancelledOrderCount;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    /**\n   209→     * Sets the cancelledOrderCount\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param cancelledOrderCount\n   212→     *            The cancelledOrderCount to set\n   213→     */\n   214→    public void setCancelledOrderCount(int cancelledOrderCount) {\n   215→        this.cancelledOrderCount = cancelledOrderCount;\n   216→    }\n   217→\n   218→    /**\n   219→     * Gets the openOrderCount\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return Returns a int\n   222→     */\n   223→    public int getOpenOrderCount() {\n   224→        return openOrderCount;\n   225→    }\n   226→\n   227→    /**\n   228→     * Sets the openOrderCount\n   229→     *\n   230→     * @param openOrderCount\n   231→     *            The openOrderCount to set\n   232→     */\n   233→    public void setOpenOrderCount(int openOrderCount) {\n   234→        this.openOrderCount = openOrderCount;\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    /**\n   238→     * Gets the deletedOrderCount\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @return Returns a int\n   241→     */\n   242→    public int getDeletedOrderCount() {\n   243→        return deletedOrderCount;\n   244→    }\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Sets the deletedOrderCount\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param deletedOrderCount\n   250→     *            The deletedOrderCount to set\n   251→     */\n   252→    public void setDeletedOrderCount(int deletedOrderCount) {\n   253→        this.deletedOrderCount = deletedOrderCount;\n   254→    }\n   255→\n   256→    /**\n   257→     * Gets the orderCount\n   258→     *\n   259→     * @return Returns a int\n   260→     */\n   261→    public int getOrderCount() {\n   262→        return orderCount;\n   263→    }\n   264→\n   265→    /**\n   266→     * Sets the orderCount\n   267→     *\n   268→     * @param orderCount\n   269→     *            The orderCount to set\n   270→     */\n   271→    public void setOrderCount(int orderCount) {\n   272→        this.orderCount = orderCount;\n   273→    }\n   274→\n   275→    /**\n   276→     * Gets the tradeStockCount\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @return Returns a int\n   279→     */\n   280→    public int getTradeStockCount() {\n   281→        return tradeStockCount;\n   282→    }\n   283→\n   284→    /**\n   285→     * Sets the tradeStockCount\n   286→     *\n   287→     * @param tradeStockCount\n   288→     *            The tradeStockCount to set\n   289→     */\n   290→    public void setTradeStockCount(int tradeStockCount) {\n   291→        this.tradeStockCount = tradeStockCount;\n   292→    }\n   293→\n   294→}\n   295→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"bd387a73-073d-4260-b0d6-e9ee1a1cf16a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AuGBnFWSUTEtKi9jdUU692","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→\n    22→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    23→import javax.ejb.Lock;\n    24→import javax.ejb.LockType;\n    25→import javax.ejb.Schedule;\n    26→import javax.ejb.Singleton;\n    27→import javax.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedExecutorService;\n    28→import javax.enterprise.event.Event;\n    29→import javax.enterprise.event.NotificationOptions;\n    30→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    31→import javax.json.JsonObject;\n    32→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n    33→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    34→import javax.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    35→import javax.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    36→import javax.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    37→import javax.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    38→\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    45→\n    46→@Singleton\n    47→public class MarketSummarySingleton {\n    48→\n    49→  private MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n    50→\n    51→  @PersistenceContext\n    52→  private EntityManager entityManager;\n    53→  \n    54→  @Inject\n    55→  @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    56→  Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    57→  \n    58→  @Resource\n    59→  private ManagedExecutorService mes;\n    60→  \n    61→\n    62→  /* Update Market Summary every 20 seconds */\n    63→  @Schedule(second = \"*/20\",minute = \"*\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    64→  private void updateMarketSummary() { \n    65→\n    66→\n    67→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    68→\n    69→\n    70→    if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3)\n    71→    {\n    72→      Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating\");\n    73→      return; // Only do the actual work if in EJB3 Mode\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    77→\n    78→    try {        \n    79→      // Find Trade Stock Index Quotes (Top 100 quotes) ordered by their change in value\n    80→      CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    81→      CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    82→      Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    83→      criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n    84→      criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n    85→      TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n    86→      quotes = q.getResultList();\n    87→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    88→      Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured. If this is the first time the application has been started, please create and populate the database tables. Then restart the server.\");\n    89→      return;\n    90→    }\t\n    91→\n    92→    /* TODO: Make this cleaner? */\n    93→    QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n    94→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    95→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    96→    BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    97→    BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    98→    double totalVolume = 0.0;\n    99→\n   100→    if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n   101→      for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   102→        topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   103→      }\n   104→      for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n   105→        topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   106→      }\n   107→\n   108→      for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n   109→        BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   110→        BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n   111→        double volume = quote.getVolume();\n   112→        TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n   113→        openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n   114→        totalVolume += volume;\n   115→      }\n   116→      TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   117→      openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n   121→    mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\", NotificationOptions.builder().setExecutor(mes).build());\n   122→  }\n   123→\n   124→  @Lock(LockType.READ)\n   125→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() { \n   126→    if (marketSummaryDataBean == null){\n   127→      updateMarketSummary();\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    return marketSummaryDataBean;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  @Lock(LockType.WRITE)\n   134→  public void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n   135→    this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n   136→  }\n   137→\n   138→}\n   139→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"7adaab5f-2e19-45ac-9055-d3fc9d19457f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CRM211JEt7S8HyCK6cizW5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    22→import javax.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    23→import javax.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    24→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    25→import javax.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    26→import javax.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    27→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    28→import javax.ws.rs.POST;\n    29→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    30→import javax.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    31→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    32→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    33→\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    38→\n    39→@Path(\"quotes\")\n    40→@RequestScoped\n    41→public class QuoteResource {\n    42→\n    43→  private TradeServices tradeService;  \n    44→\n    45→  \n    46→  public QuoteResource() {\n    47→  }\n    48→  \n    49→  @Inject \n    50→  public QuoteResource(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    51→    tradeService = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @GET\n    55→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    56→  @Path(\"/{symbols}\")\n    57→  public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesGet(@PathParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    58→    return getQuotes(symbols);\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  @POST\n    62→  @Consumes({ \"application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" })\n    63→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    64→  public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesPost(@FormParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    65→    return getQuotes(symbols);\n    66→  }\n    67→  \n    68→  private List<QuoteDataBean> getQuotes(String symbols) {\n    69→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    70→\n    71→    try {\n    72→      String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n    73→      for (String symbol: symbolsSplit) {\n    74→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeService.getQuote(symbol);\n    75→        quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n    76→      } \n    77→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    78→      e.printStackTrace();\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    return (List<QuoteDataBean>)quoteDataBeans;\n    82→  }\n    83→  \n    84→}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"e8de47d1-ef90-4fc0-adaf-c7f15f73ad37"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012M16APMQcCJMLkQPwNf2sE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import javax.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n    19→import javax.ws.rs.core.Application;\n    20→\n    21→/**\n    22→ *\n    23→ * @author hantsy\n    24→ */\n    25→@ApplicationPath(\"/rest\")\n    26→public class JAXRSApplication extends Application {\n    27→    \n    28→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"1f574f8d-e8d3-48f5-bca5-f490f82dbd32"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Nu2yb2NeYCrTMoeLuKEdgH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.annotation.Priority;\n    21→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    22→import javax.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\n    23→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    24→import javax.interceptor.Interceptor;\n    25→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    26→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    27→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    28→import javax.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    29→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    30→import javax.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent.Builder;\n    31→import javax.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\n    32→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\n    33→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\n    34→\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    37→\n    38→@Path(\"broadcastevents\")\n    39→@ApplicationScoped\n    40→public class BroadcastResource {\n    41→\n    42→  private SseBroadcaster broadcaster;\n    43→  private Builder builder; \n    44→\n    45→  @Inject RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    46→\n    47→  @Context\n    48→  public void setSse(Sse sse) {\n    49→    broadcaster = sse.newBroadcaster();\n    50→    builder = sse.newEventBuilder();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @GET\n    54→  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    55→  public void register(@Context SseEventSink eventSink) {\n    56→    if (recentQuotePriceChangeList.isEmpty()) {\n    57→      eventSink.send(builder.data(new String(\"welcome!\")).build());\n    58→    } else {\n    59→      eventSink.send(builder.mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    60→      .data(List.class,recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList()).build());\n    61→    }\n    62→    broadcaster.register(eventSink);\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public void eventStreamCdi(@ObservesAsync @Priority(Interceptor.Priority.APPLICATION + 1) @QuotePriceChange String event) {\n    66→    broadcaster.broadcast(builder.mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    67→        .data(List.class,recentQuotePriceChangeList.recentList()).build());\n    68→\n    69→  }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"36f033d7-3191-4b51-a0a6-1ec3f9e4433f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UGMVgP5DHqzfM59zPGAhDR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    21→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    22→import javax.servlet.ServletContext;\n    23→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    24→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    26→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    27→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    28→import javax.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    29→import javax.servlet.http.PushBuilder;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    34→\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ *\n    38→ * TradeAppServlet provides the standard web interface to Trade and can be\n    39→ * accessed with the Go Trade! link. Driving benchmark load using this interface\n    40→ * requires a sophisticated web load generator that is capable of filling HTML\n    41→ * forms and posting dynamic data.\n    42→ */\n    43→\n    44→@WebServlet(name = \"TradeAppServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/app\" })\n    45→@Trace\n    46→public class TradeAppServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    47→\n    48→  @Inject\n    49→  TradeServletAction tsAction; \n    50→  \n    51→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 481530522846648373L;\n    52→\n    53→  /**\n    54→   * Servlet initialization method.\n    55→   */\n    56→  @Override\n    57→  public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    58→    super.init(config);\n    59→    java.util.Enumeration<String> en = config.getInitParameterNames();\n    60→    while (en.hasMoreElements()) {\n    61→      String parm = en.nextElement();\n    62→      String value = config.getInitParameter(parm);\n    63→      TradeConfig.setConfigParam(parm, value);\n    64→    }\n    65→    try {\n    66→      // TODO: Uncomment this once split-tier issue is resolved\n    67→      // TradeDirect.init();\n    68→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    69→      Log.error(e, \"TradeAppServlet:init -- Error initializing TradeDirect\");\n    70→    }\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  /**\n    74→   * Returns a string that contains information about TradeScenarioServlet\n    75→   *\n    76→   * @return The servlet information\n    77→   */\n    78→  @Override\n    79→  public java.lang.String getServletInfo() {\n    80→    return \"TradeAppServlet provides the standard web interface to Trade\";\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  /**\n    84→   * Process incoming HTTP GET requests\n    85→   *\n    86→   * @param request\n    87→   *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    88→   * @param response\n    89→   *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    90→   */\n    91→  @Override\n    92→  public void doGet(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request, javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    93→    performTask(request, response);\n    94→  }\n    95→\n    96→  /**\n    97→   * Process incoming HTTP POST requests\n    98→   *\n    99→   * @param request\n   100→   *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n   101→   * @param response\n   102→   *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n   103→   */\n   104→  @Override\n   105→  public void doPost(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request, javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   106→    performTask(request, response);\n   107→  }\n   108→\n   109→  /**\n   110→   * Main service method for TradeAppServlet\n   111→   *\n   112→   * @param request\n   113→   *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n   114→   * @param response\n   115→   *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n   116→   */\n   117→  public void performTask(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   118→\n   119→    String action = null;\n   120→    String userID = null;\n   121→    // String to create full dispatch path to TradeAppServlet w/ request\n   122→    // Parameters\n   123→\n   124→    resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   125→\n   126→    // Dyna - need status string - prepended to output\n   127→    action = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n   128→\n   129→    ServletContext ctx = getServletConfig().getServletContext();\n   130→\n   131→    if (action == null) {\n   132→      tsAction.doWelcome(ctx, req, resp, \"\");\n   133→      return;\n   134→    } else if (action.equals(\"login\")) {\n   135→      userID = req.getParameter(\"uid\");\n   136→      String passwd = req.getParameter(\"passwd\");\n   137→      tsAction.doLogin(ctx, req, resp, userID, passwd);\n   138→      return;\n   139→    } else if (action.equals(\"register\")) {\n   140→      userID = req.getParameter(\"user id\");\n   141→      String passwd = req.getParameter(\"passwd\");\n   142→      String cpasswd = req.getParameter(\"confirm passwd\");\n   143→      String fullname = req.getParameter(\"Full Name\");\n   144→      String ccn = req.getParameter(\"Credit Card Number\");\n   145→      String money = req.getParameter(\"money\");\n   146→      String email = req.getParameter(\"email\");\n   147→      String smail = req.getParameter(\"snail mail\");\n   148→      tsAction.doRegister(ctx, req, resp, userID, passwd, cpasswd, fullname, ccn, money, email, smail);\n   149→      return;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    // The rest of the operations require the user to be logged in -\n   153→    // Get the Session and validate the user.\n   154→    HttpSession session = req.getSession();\n   155→    userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n   156→\n   157→    if (userID == null) {\n   158→      System.out.println(\"TradeAppServlet service error: User Not Logged in\");\n   159→      tsAction.doWelcome(ctx, req, resp, \"User Not Logged in\");\n   160→      return;\n   161→    }\n   162→    \n   163→    // try http/2 push if we get here\n   164→    // should be logged in and doing real work by this point\n   165→    if (!action.equals(\"logout\") && TradeConfig.getWebInterface() == TradeConfig.JSP_Images_HTTP2) {\n   166→      pushHeaderImages(req.newPushBuilder());\n   167→    }\n   168→    \n   169→    if (action.equals(\"quotes\")) {\n   170→      String symbols = req.getParameter(\"symbols\");\n   171→      tsAction.doQuotes(ctx, req, resp, userID, symbols);\n   172→    } else if (action.equals(\"buy\")) {\n   173→      String symbol = req.getParameter(\"symbol\");\n   174→      String quantity = req.getParameter(\"quantity\");\n   175→      tsAction.doBuy(ctx, req, resp, userID, symbol, quantity);\n   176→    } else if (action.equals(\"sell\")) {\n   177→      int holdingID = Integer.parseInt(req.getParameter(\"holdingID\"));\n   178→      tsAction.doSell(ctx, req, resp, userID, new Integer(holdingID));\n   179→    } else if (action.equals(\"portfolio\") || action.equals(\"portfolioNoEdge\")) {\n   180→      tsAction.doPortfolio(ctx, req, resp, userID, \"Portfolio as of \" + new java.util.Date());\n   181→    } else if (action.equals(\"logout\")) {\n   182→      tsAction.doLogout(ctx, req, resp, userID);\n   183→    } else if (action.equals(\"home\")) {\n   184→      tsAction.doHome(ctx, req, resp, userID, \"Ready to Trade\");\n   185→    } else if (action.equals(\"account\")) {\n   186→      tsAction.doAccount(ctx, req, resp, userID, \"\");\n   187→    } else if (action.equals(\"update_profile\")) {      \n   188→      String password = req.getParameter(\"password\");\n   189→      String cpassword = req.getParameter(\"cpassword\");\n   190→      String fullName = req.getParameter(\"fullname\");\n   191→      String address = req.getParameter(\"address\");\n   192→      String creditcard = req.getParameter(\"creditcard\");\n   193→      String email = req.getParameter(\"email\");\n   194→      tsAction.doAccountUpdate(ctx, req, resp, userID, password == null ? \"\" : password.trim(), cpassword == null ? \"\" : cpassword.trim(),\n   195→          fullName == null ? \"\" : fullName.trim(), address == null ? \"\" : address.trim(), creditcard == null ? \"\" : creditcard.trim(),\n   196→              email == null ? \"\" : email.trim());\n   197→    } else if (action.equals(\"mksummary\")) {\n   198→      tsAction.doMarketSummary(ctx, req, resp, userID);\n   199→    } else {\n   200→      System.out.println(\"TradeAppServlet: Invalid Action=\" + action);\n   201→      tsAction.doWelcome(ctx, req, resp, \"TradeAppServlet: Invalid Action\" + action);\n   202→    }\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→  private void pushHeaderImages(PushBuilder pushBuilder) {       \n   206→    if (pushBuilder != null) {\n   207→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/menuHome.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   208→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/account.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   209→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/portfolio.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   210→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/quotes.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   211→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/logout.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   212→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/graph.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   213→      pushBuilder.path(\"images/line.gif\").addHeader(\"content-type\", \"image/gif\").push();\n   214→      Log.trace(\"HTTP/2 is enabled\");\n   215→    } else {\n   216→      Log.error(\"HTTP/2 not enabled\");\n   217→    }\n   218→    \n   219→  }\n   220→\n   221→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"0bb67201-d76e-4c00-a040-6494dd81bf48"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018usxJMh8PRYK9bdaL3gkue","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    21→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    22→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    23→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    24→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    26→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    27→\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirectDBUtils;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    34→\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * TradeConfigServlet provides a servlet interface to adjust DayTrader runtime parameters.\n    38→ * TradeConfigServlet updates values in the {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.TradeConfig} JavaBean holding\n    39→ * all configuration and runtime parameters for the Trade application\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→@WebServlet(name = \"TradeConfigServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/config\" })\n    43→@Trace\n    44→public class TradeConfigServlet extends HttpServlet {  \n    45→\n    46→  @Inject\n    47→  private TradeDirectDBUtils dbUtils;\n    48→\n    49→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -1910381529792500095L;\n    50→\n    51→  /**\n    52→   * Servlet initialization method.\n    53→   */\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    56→    super.init(config);\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  /**\n    60→   * Create the TradeConfig bean and pass it the config.jsp page\n    61→   * to display the current Trade runtime configuration\n    62→   * Creation date: (2/8/2000 3:43:59 PM)\n    63→   */\n    64→  void doConfigDisplay(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String results) throws Exception {\n    65→\n    66→    TradeConfig currentConfig = new TradeConfig();\n    67→\n    68→    req.setAttribute(\"tradeConfig\", currentConfig);\n    69→    req.setAttribute(\"status\", results);\n    70→    getServletConfig().getServletContext().getRequestDispatcher(TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.CONFIG_PAGE)).include(req, resp);\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  void doResetTrade(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String results) throws Exception {\n    74→    RunStatsDataBean runStatsData = new RunStatsDataBean();\n    75→    TradeConfig currentConfig = new TradeConfig();\n    76→\n    77→    try {\n    78→      runStatsData = dbUtils.resetTrade(false);\n    79→\n    80→      req.setAttribute(\"runStatsData\", runStatsData);\n    81→      req.setAttribute(\"tradeConfig\", currentConfig);\n    82→      results += \"Trade Reset completed successfully\";\n    83→      req.setAttribute(\"status\", results);\n    84→\n    85→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    86→      results += \"Trade Reset Error  - see log for details\";\n    87→      Log.error(e, results);\n    88→      throw e;\n    89→    }\n    90→    getServletConfig().getServletContext().getRequestDispatcher(TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.STATS_PAGE)).include(req, resp);\n    91→\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  /**\n    95→   * Update Trade runtime configuration paramaters\n    96→   * Creation date: (2/8/2000 3:44:24 PM)\n    97→   */\n    98→  void doConfigUpdate(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws Exception {\n    99→    String currentConfigStr = \"\\n\\n########## Trade configuration update. Current config:\\n\\n\";\n   100→\n   101→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tRuntimeMode:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] + \"\\n\";\n   102→    \n   103→    String orderProcessingModeStr = req.getParameter(\"OrderProcessingMode\");\n   104→    if (orderProcessingModeStr != null) {\n   105→      try {\n   106→        int i = Integer.parseInt(orderProcessingModeStr);\n   107→        if ((i >= 0) && (i < TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames().length)) //Input validation\n   108→          TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(i);\n   109→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   110→        //>>rjm\n   111→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\", \"trying to set orderProcessing to \" + orderProcessingModeStr,\n   112→            \"reverting to current value\");\n   113→\n   114→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   115→    }\n   116→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tOrderProcessingMode:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()] + \"\\n\";\n   117→\n   118→    String webInterfaceStr = req.getParameter(\"WebInterface\");\n   119→    if (webInterfaceStr != null) {\n   120→      try {\n   121→        int i = Integer.parseInt(webInterfaceStr);\n   122→        if ((i >= 0) && (i < TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames().length)) //Input validation\n   123→          TradeConfig.setWebInterface(i);\n   124→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   125→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\", \"trying to set WebInterface to \" + webInterfaceStr,\n   126→            \"reverting to current value\");\n   127→\n   128→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   129→    }\n   130→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tWeb Interface:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getWebInterfaceNames()[TradeConfig.getWebInterface()] + \"\\n\";\n   131→\n   132→    String parm = req.getParameter(\"MaxUsers\");\n   133→    if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   134→      try {\n   135→        TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   136→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   137→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet.doConfigUpdate(..): minor exception caught\", \"Setting maxusers, probably error parsing string to int:\" + parm,\n   138→            \"revertying to current value: \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS());\n   139→\n   140→      } //On error, revert to saved\n   141→    }\n   142→    parm = req.getParameter(\"MaxQuotes\");\n   143→    if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   144→      try {\n   145→        TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   146→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   147→        //>>rjm\n   148→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\", \"trying to set max_quotes, error on parsing int \" + parm,\n   149→            \"reverting to current value \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES());\n   150→        //<<rjm\n   151→\n   152→      } //On error, revert to saved\n   153→    }\n   154→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade Users:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \"\\n\";\n   155→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTrade Quotes:\\t\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \"\\n\";\n   156→\n   157→    parm = req.getParameter(\"marketSummaryInterval\");\n   158→    if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   159→      try {\n   160→        TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   161→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   162→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\", \"trying to set marketSummaryInterval, error on parsing int \" + parm,\n   163→            \"reverting to current value \" + TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval());\n   164→\n   165→      }\n   166→    }\n   167→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tMarket Summary Interval:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() + \"\\n\";\n   168→\n   169→    parm = req.getParameter(\"primIterations\");\n   170→    if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   171→      try {\n   172→        TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   173→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   174→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\", \"trying to set primIterations, error on parsing int \" + parm,\n   175→            \"reverting to current value \" + TradeConfig.getPrimIterations());\n   176→\n   177→      }\n   178→    }\n   179→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tPrimitive Iterations:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getPrimIterations() + \"\\n\";\n   180→\n   181→    String enablePublishQuotePriceChange = req.getParameter(\"EnablePublishQuotePriceChange\");\n   182→\n   183→    if (enablePublishQuotePriceChange != null)\n   184→      TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(true);\n   185→    else\n   186→      TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(false);\n   187→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tTradeStreamer MDB Enabled:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange() + \"\\n\";\n   188→\n   189→    parm = req.getParameter(\"ListQuotePriceChangeFrequency\");\n   190→    if ((parm != null) && (parm.length() > 0)) {\n   191→      try {\n   192→        TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(Integer.parseInt(parm));\n   193→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   194→        Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet: minor exception caught\", \"trying to set percentSentToWebSocket, error on parsing int \" + parm,\n   195→            \"reverting to current value \" + TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency());\n   196→\n   197→      }\n   198→    }\n   199→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\t% of trades on Websocket:\\t\" + TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() + \"\\n\";\n   200→\n   201→    String enableLongRun = req.getParameter(\"EnableLongRun\");\n   202→\n   203→    if (enableLongRun != null)\n   204→      TradeConfig.setLongRun(true);\n   205→    else\n   206→      TradeConfig.setLongRun(false);\n   207→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tLong Run Enabled:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getLongRun() + \"\\n\";\n   208→\n   209→    String displayOrderAlerts = req.getParameter(\"DisplayOrderAlerts\");\n   210→\n   211→    if (displayOrderAlerts != null)\n   212→      TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(true);\n   213→    else\n   214→      TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(false);\n   215→    currentConfigStr += \"\\t\\tDisplay Order Alerts:\\t\\t\" + TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts() + \"\\n\";\n   216→\n   217→    System.out.println(currentConfigStr);\n   218→  }\n   219→\n   220→  @Override\n   221→  public void service(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   222→\n   223→    String action = null;\n   224→    String result = \"\";\n   225→\n   226→    resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   227→    try {\n   228→      action = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n   229→      if (action == null) {\n   230→        doConfigDisplay(req, resp, result + \"<b><br>Current DayTrader Configuration:</br></b>\");\n   231→        return;\n   232→      } else if (action.equals(\"updateConfig\")) {\n   233→        doConfigUpdate(req, resp);\n   234→        result = \"<B><BR>DayTrader Configuration Updated</BR></B>\";\n   235→      } else if (action.equals(\"resetTrade\")) {\n   236→        doResetTrade(req, resp, \"\");\n   237→        return;\n   238→      } else if (action.equals(\"buildDB\")) {\n   239→        resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   240→        dbUtils.buildDB(resp.getWriter(), null);\n   241→        result = \"DayTrader Database Built - \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \"users created\";\n   242→      } else if (action.equals(\"buildDBTables\")) {\n   243→\n   244→        resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   245→\n   246→        String dbProductName = null;\n   247→        try {\n   248→          dbProductName = dbUtils.checkDBProductName();\n   249→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   250→          Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to check DB Product name\");\n   251→        }\n   252→        if (dbProductName == null) {\n   253→          resp.getWriter().println(\n   254→              \"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to check DB Product name, please check Database/AppServer configuration and retry ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   255→          return;\n   256→        }\n   257→\n   258→        String ddlFile = null;\n   259→        //Locate DDL file for the specified database\n   260→        try {\n   261→          resp.getWriter().println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Database Product detected: \" + dbProductName + \" ****</BR>\");\n   262→          if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"DB2/\")) {// if db is DB2\n   263→            ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/db2/Table.ddl\";\n   264→          } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Apache Derby\")) { //if db is Derby\n   265→            ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/derby/Table.ddl\";\n   266→          } else if (dbProductName.startsWith(\"Oracle\")) { // if the Db is Oracle\n   267→            ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/oracle/Table.ddl\";\n   268→          } else {// Unsupported \"Other\" Database\n   269→            ddlFile = \"/dbscripts/other/Table.ddl\";\n   270→            resp.getWriter().println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** This Database is unsupported/untested use at your own risk ****</BR>\");\n   271→          }\n   272→\n   273→          resp.getWriter().println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** The DDL file at path <I>\" + ddlFile + \"</I> will be used ****</BR>\");\n   274→          resp.getWriter().flush();\n   275→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   276→          Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database\");\n   277→          resp.getWriter().println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to locate DDL file for the specified database ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   278→          return;\n   279→        }\n   280→\n   281→        dbUtils.buildDB(resp.getWriter(), getServletContext().getResourceAsStream(ddlFile));\n   282→\n   283→      }\n   284→      doConfigDisplay(req, resp, result + \"Current DayTrader Configuration:\");\n   285→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   286→      Log.error(e, \"TradeConfigServlet.service(...)\", \"Exception trying to perform action=\" + action);\n   287→\n   288→      resp.sendError(500, \"TradeConfigServlet.service(...)\" + \"Exception trying to perform action=\" + action + \"\\nException details: \" + e.toString());\n   289→\n   290→    }\n   291→  }\n   292→}\n   293→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"793f6a80-4ee7-4cba-bd03-30a093241d9d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ThJdMPtjURt6qKzL4r9X7V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Iterator;\n    22→\n    23→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    24→import javax.servlet.ServletContext;\n    25→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    26→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→import javax.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    31→\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * TradeScenarioServlet emulates a population of web users by generating a\n    38→ * specific Trade operation for a randomly chosen user on each access to the\n    39→ * URL. Test this servlet by clicking Trade Scenario and hit \"Reload\" on your\n    40→ * browser to step through a Trade Scenario. To benchmark using this URL aim\n    41→ * your favorite web load generator (such as AKStress) at the Trade Scenario URL\n    42→ * and fire away.\n    43→ */\n    44→@WebServlet(name = \"TradeScenarioServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/scenario\" })\n    45→public class TradeScenarioServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    46→\n    47→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1410005249314201829L;\n    48→\n    49→    /**\n    50→     * Servlet initialization method.\n    51→     */\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    54→        super.init(config);\n    55→        java.util.Enumeration<String> en = config.getInitParameterNames();\n    56→        while (en.hasMoreElements()) {\n    57→            String parm = en.nextElement();\n    58→            String value = config.getInitParameter(parm);\n    59→            TradeConfig.setConfigParam(parm, value);\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    /**\n    64→     * Returns a string that contains information about TradeScenarioServlet\n    65→     *\n    66→     * @return The servlet information\n    67→     */\n    68→    @Override\n    69→    public java.lang.String getServletInfo() {\n    70→        return \"TradeScenarioServlet emulates a population of web users\";\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Process incoming HTTP GET requests\n    75→     *\n    76→     * @param request\n    77→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    78→     * @param response\n    79→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    80→     */\n    81→    @Override\n    82→    public void doGet(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request, javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    83→        performTask(request, response);\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Process incoming HTTP POST requests\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @param request\n    90→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    91→     * @param response\n    92→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    93→     */\n    94→    @Override\n    95→    public void doPost(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request, javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    96→        performTask(request, response);\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    /**\n   100→     * Main service method for TradeScenarioServlet\n   101→     *\n   102→     * @param request\n   103→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n   104→     * @param response\n   105→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n   106→     */\n   107→    public void performTask(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   108→\n   109→        // Scenario generator for Trade2\n   110→        char action = ' ';\n   111→        String userID = null;\n   112→\n   113→        // String to create full dispatch path to TradeAppServlet w/ request\n   114→        // Parameters\n   115→        String dispPath = null; // Dispatch Path to TradeAppServlet\n   116→\n   117→        resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   118→\n   119→        String scenarioAction = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n   120→        if ((scenarioAction != null) && (scenarioAction.length() >= 1)) {\n   121→            action = scenarioAction.charAt(0);\n   122→            if (action == 'n') { // null;\n   123→                try {\n   124→                    // resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   125→                    PrintWriter out = new PrintWriter(resp.getOutputStream());\n   126→                    out.println(\"<HTML><HEAD>TradeScenarioServlet</HEAD><BODY>Hello</BODY></HTML>\");\n   127→                    out.close();\n   128→                    return;\n   129→\n   130→                } catch (Exception e) {\n   131→                    Log.error(\"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...)\" + \"error creating printwriter from responce.getOutputStream\", e);\n   132→\n   133→                    resp.sendError(500,\n   134→                            \"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...): erorr creating and writing to PrintStream created from response.getOutputStream()\");\n   135→                } // end of catch\n   136→\n   137→            } // end of action=='n'\n   138→        }\n   139→\n   140→        ServletContext ctx = null;\n   141→        HttpSession session = null;\n   142→        try {\n   143→            ctx = getServletConfig().getServletContext();\n   144→            // These operations require the user to be logged in. Verify the\n   145→            // user and if not logged in\n   146→            // change the operation to a login\n   147→            session = req.getSession(true);\n   148→            userID = (String) session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n   149→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   150→            Log.error(\"trade_client.TradeScenarioServlet.service(...): performing \" + scenarioAction\n   151→                    + \"error getting ServletContext,HttpSession, or UserID from session\" + \"will make scenarioAction a login and try to recover from there\", e);\n   152→            userID = null;\n   153→            action = 'l';\n   154→        }\n   155→\n   156→        if (userID == null) {\n   157→            action = 'l'; // change to login\n   158→            TradeConfig.incrementScenarioCount();\n   159→        } else if (action == ' ') {\n   160→            // action is not specified perform a random operation according to\n   161→            // current mix\n   162→            // Tell getScenarioAction if we are an original user or a registered\n   163→            // user\n   164→            // -- sellDeficits should only be compensated for with original\n   165→            // users.\n   166→            action = TradeConfig.getScenarioAction(userID.startsWith(TradeConfig.newUserPrefix));\n   167→        }\n   168→        switch (action) {\n   169→\n   170→        case 'q': // quote\n   171→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"quotes&symbols=\" + TradeConfig.rndSymbols();\n   172→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   173→            break;\n   174→        case 'a': // account\n   175→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"account\";\n   176→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   177→            break;\n   178→        case 'u': // update account profile\n   179→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"account\";\n   180→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   181→\n   182→            String fullName = \"rnd\" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n   183→            String address = \"rndAddress\";\n   184→            String password = \"xxx\";\n   185→            String email = \"rndEmail\";\n   186→            String creditcard = \"rndCC\";\n   187→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"update_profile&fullname=\" + fullName + \"&password=\" + password + \"&cpassword=\" + password + \"&address=\" + address\n   188→                    + \"&email=\" + email + \"&creditcard=\" + creditcard;\n   189→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   190→            break;\n   191→        case 'h': // home\n   192→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"home\";\n   193→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   194→            break;\n   195→        case 'l': // login\n   196→            userID = TradeConfig.getUserID();\n   197→            String password2 = \"xxx\";\n   198→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"login&inScenario=true&uid=\" + userID + \"&passwd=\" + password2;\n   199→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   200→\n   201→            // login is successful if the userID is written to the HTTP session\n   202→            if (session.getAttribute(\"uidBean\") == null) {\n   203→                System.out.println(\"TradeScenario login failed. Reset DB between runs\");\n   204→            }\n   205→            break;\n   206→        case 'o': // logout\n   207→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"logout\";\n   208→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   209→            break;\n   210→        case 'p': // portfolio\n   211→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"portfolio\";\n   212→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   213→            break;\n   214→        case 'r': // register\n   215→            // Logout the current user to become a new user\n   216→            // see note in TradeServletAction\n   217→            req.setAttribute(\"TSS-RecreateSessionInLogout\", Boolean.TRUE);\n   218→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"logout\";\n   219→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   220→\n   221→            userID = TradeConfig.rndNewUserID();\n   222→            String passwd = \"yyy\";\n   223→            fullName = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   224→            creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   225→            String money = TradeConfig.rndBalance();\n   226→            email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   227→            String smail = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   228→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"register&Full Name=\" + fullName + \"&snail mail=\" + smail + \"&email=\" + email + \"&user id=\" + userID + \"&passwd=\"\n   229→                    + passwd + \"&confirm passwd=\" + passwd + \"&money=\" + money + \"&Credit Card Number=\" + creditcard;\n   230→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   231→            break;\n   232→        case 's': // sell\n   233→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"portfolioNoEdge\";\n   234→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   235→\n   236→            Collection<?> holdings = (Collection<?>) req.getAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\");\n   237→            int numHoldings = holdings.size();\n   238→            if (numHoldings > 0) {\n   239→                // sell first available security out of holding\n   240→\n   241→                Iterator<?> it = holdings.iterator();\n   242→                boolean foundHoldingToSell = false;\n   243→                while (it.hasNext()) {\n   244→                    HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n   245→                    if (!(holdingData.getPurchaseDate().equals(new java.util.Date(0)))) {\n   246→                        Integer holdingID = holdingData.getHoldingID();\n   247→\n   248→                        dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"sell&holdingID=\" + holdingID;\n   249→                        ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   250→                        foundHoldingToSell = true;\n   251→                        break;\n   252→                    }\n   253→                }\n   254→                if (foundHoldingToSell) {\n   255→                    break;\n   256→                }\n   257→\n   258→                Log.trace(\"TradeScenario: No holding to sell -switch to buy -- userID = \" + userID + \"  Collection count = \" + numHoldings);\n   259→                \n   260→\n   261→            }\n   262→            // At this point: A TradeScenario Sell was requested with No Stocks\n   263→            // in Portfolio\n   264→            // This can happen when a new registered user happens to request a\n   265→            // sell before a buy\n   266→            // In this case, fall through and perform a buy instead\n   267→\n   268→            /*\n   269→             * Trade 2.037: Added sell_deficit counter to maintain correct\n   270→             * buy/sell mix. When a users portfolio is reduced to 0 holdings, a\n   271→             * buy is requested instead of a sell. This throws off the buy/sell\n   272→             * mix by 1. This results in unwanted holding table growth To fix\n   273→             * this we increment a sell deficit counter to maintain the correct\n   274→             * ratio in getScenarioAction The 'z' action from getScenario\n   275→             * denotes that this is a sell action that was switched from a buy\n   276→             * to reduce a sellDeficit\n   277→             */\n   278→            if (userID.startsWith(TradeConfig.newUserPrefix) == false) {\n   279→                TradeConfig.incrementSellDeficit();\n   280→            }\n   281→        case 'b': // buy\n   282→            String symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n   283→            String amount = TradeConfig.rndQuantity() + \"\";\n   284→\n   285→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"quotes&symbols=\" + symbol;\n   286→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   287→\n   288→            dispPath = tasPathPrefix + \"buy&quantity=\" + amount + \"&symbol=\" + symbol;\n   289→            ctx.getRequestDispatcher(dispPath).include(req, resp);\n   290→            break;\n   291→        } // end of switch statement\n   292→    }\n   293→\n   294→    // URL Path Prefix for dispatching to TradeAppServlet\n   295→    private static final String tasPathPrefix = \"/app?action=\";\n   296→\n   297→}\n   298→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"aadad8c8-91bc-49f8-b4a1-4523508d08ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G4eE93j4j5h1sotfFq5zBu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import static javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig.Version.JSF_2_3;\n    19→\n    20→import java.io.InputStream;\n    21→import java.util.Properties;\n    22→\n    23→import javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig;\n    24→import javax.servlet.ServletContextEvent;\n    25→import javax.servlet.ServletContextListener;\n    26→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebListener;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    30→\n    31→@WebListener()\n    32→@FacesConfig(version = JSF_2_3)\n    33→public class TradeWebContextListener implements ServletContextListener {\n    34→  \n    35→  \n    36→  \n    37→    // receieve trade web app startup/shutown events to start(initialized)/stop\n    38→    // TradeDirect\n    39→    @Override\n    40→    public void contextInitialized(ServletContextEvent event) {\n    41→      Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener contextInitialized -- initializing TradeDirect\");\n    42→        \n    43→      // Load settings from properties file (if it exists)\n    44→      Properties prop = new Properties();\n    45→      InputStream stream =  event.getServletContext().getResourceAsStream(\"/properties/daytrader.properties\");\n    46→        \n    47→      try {\n    48→        prop.load(stream);\n    49→        System.out.println(\"Settings from daytrader.properties: \" + prop);\n    50→        \n    51→        if (System.getenv(\"RUNTIME_MODE\") != null) {\n    52→          TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"RUNTIME_MODE\")));\n    53→        } else {\n    54→          TradeConfig.setRunTimeMode(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"runtimeMode\")));\n    55→        }\n    56→        System.out.print(\"Running in \" + TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()] + \" Mode\");\n    57→            \n    58→        if (System.getenv(\"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\") != null) {\n    59→          TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE\")));\n    60→        } else {\n    61→          TradeConfig.setOrderProcessingMode(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"orderProcessingMode\")));\n    62→        }\n    63→        System.out.print(\"Running in \" + TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames()[TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode()] + \" Order Processing Mode\");  \n    64→        \n    65→        if (System.getenv(\"MAX_USERS\") != null) {\n    66→          TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"MAX_USERS\")));\n    67→        } else {\n    68→          TradeConfig.setMAX_USERS(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"maxUsers\")));\n    69→        }\n    70→        System.out.print(\"MAX_USERS = \" +  TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \" users\");\n    71→        \n    72→        if (System.getenv(\"MAX_QUOTES\") != null) {\n    73→          TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"MAX_QUOTES\")));\n    74→        } else {\n    75→          TradeConfig.setMAX_QUOTES(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"maxQuotes\")));\n    76→        }\n    77→        System.out.print(\"MAX_QUOTES = \" +  TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \" quotes\");\n    78→       \n    79→        if (System.getenv(\"PUBLISH_QUOTES\") != null) {\n    80→          TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv(\"PUBLISH_QUOTES\")));\n    81→        } else {\n    82→          TradeConfig.setPublishQuotePriceChange(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"publishQuotePriceChange\")));\n    83→        }\n    84→       \n    85→        if (System.getenv(\"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\") != null) {\n    86→          TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv(\"DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS\")));\n    87→        } else {\n    88→          TradeConfig.setDisplayOrderAlerts(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"displayOrderAlerts\")));\n    89→        }\n    90→        if (System.getenv(\"WEB_INTERFACE\") != null) {\n    91→          TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"WEB_INTERFACE\")));\n    92→        } else {\n    93→          TradeConfig.setWebInterface(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"webInterface\")));\n    94→        }\n    95→        if (System.getenv(\"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\") != null) {\n    96→          TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(Integer.parseInt(System.getenv(\"LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\")));\n    97→        } else {\n    98→          TradeConfig.setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"listQuotePriceChangeFrequency\")));\n    99→        }\n   100→        \n   101→        TradeConfig.setPrimIterations(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"primIterations\")));\n   102→        TradeConfig.setMarketSummaryInterval(Integer.parseInt(prop.getProperty(\"marketSummaryInterval\")));\n   103→        TradeConfig.setLongRun(Boolean.parseBoolean(prop.getProperty(\"longRun\")));\n   104→       \n   105→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   106→        System.out.println(\"daytrader.properties not found\");\n   107→      }\n   108→       \n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @Override\n   112→    public void contextDestroyed(ServletContextEvent event) {\n   113→        Log.trace(\"TradeWebContextListener  contextDestroy calling TradeDirect:destroy()\");\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→}\n   117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"d51543a2-272e-4f93-b317-9a97a1cea21b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D2LmqqDrQhDXMkphHJkHjF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.Random;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * TradeConfig is a JavaBean holding all configuration and runtime parameters\n    24→ * for the Trade application TradeConfig sets runtime parameters such as the\n    25→ * RunTimeMode (EJB, JDBC, EJB_ALT)\n    26→ *\n    27→ */\n    28→\n    29→public class TradeConfig {\n    30→\n    31→  /* Trade Runtime Configuration Parameters */\n    32→\n    33→  /* Trade Runtime Mode parameters */\n    34→  private static String[] runTimeModeNames = { \"Full EJB3\", \"Direct (JDBC)\", \"Session to Direct\"};\n    35→  public static final int EJB3 = 0;\n    36→  public static final int DIRECT = 1;\n    37→  public static final int SESSION_TO_DIRECT = 2;\n    38→  private static int runTimeMode = EJB3;\n    39→\n    40→  private static String[] orderProcessingModeNames = { \"Sync\", \"Async\",\"Async_2-Phase\" };\n    41→  public static final int SYNCH = 0;\n    42→  public static final int ASYNCH = 1;\n    43→  public static final int ASYNCH_2PHASE = 2;\n    44→  private static int orderProcessingMode = SYNCH;\n    45→\n    46→  private static String[] accessModeNames = { \"Standard\", \"WebServices\" };\n    47→  public static final int STANDARD = 0;\n    48→  private static int accessMode = STANDARD;\n    49→\n    50→  /* Trade Web Interface parameters */\n    51→  private static String[] webInterfaceNames = { \"JSP\", \"JSP-Images\", \"JSP-Images-Http2\" };\n    52→  public static final int JSP = 0;\n    53→  public static final int JSP_Images = 1;\n    54→  public static final int JSP_Images_HTTP2 = 2;\n    55→  private static int webInterface = JSP;\n    56→\n    57→  /* Trade Database Scaling parameters */\n    58→  private static int MAX_USERS = 15000;\n    59→  private static int MAX_QUOTES = 10000;\n    60→\n    61→  \n    62→  /* Trade XA Datasource specific parameters */\n    63→  public static boolean JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation = false;\n    64→\n    65→  /* Trade Config Miscellaneous itmes */\n    66→  public static String DATASOURCE = \"java:comp/env/jdbc/TradeDataSource\";\n    67→  public static int KEYBLOCKSIZE = 1000;\n    68→  public static int QUOTES_PER_PAGE = 10;\n    69→  public static boolean RND_USER = true;\n    70→  // public static int RND_SEED = 0;\n    71→  private static int MAX_HOLDINGS = 10;\n    72→  private static int count = 0;\n    73→  private static Object userID_count_semaphore = new Object();\n    74→  private static int userID_count = 0;\n    75→  private static String hostName = null;\n    76→  private static Random r0 = new Random(System.currentTimeMillis());\n    77→  // private static Random r1 = new Random(RND_SEED);\n    78→  private static Random randomNumberGenerator = r0;\n    79→  public static final String newUserPrefix = \"ru:\";\n    80→  public static final int verifyPercent = 5;\n    81→  private static boolean updateQuotePrices = true;\n    82→  private static int primIterations = 1;\n    83→  private static boolean longRun = true;\n    84→  private static boolean publishQuotePriceChange = true;\n    85→  private static int listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = 100;\n    86→  private static boolean displayOrderAlerts = true;\n    87→\n    88→  /**\n    89→   * -1 means every operation 0 means never perform a market summary > 0 means\n    90→   * number of seconds between summaries. These will be synchronized so only\n    91→   * one transaction in this period will create a summary and will cache its\n    92→   * results.\n    93→   */\n    94→  private static int marketSummaryInterval = 20;\n    95→\n    96→  /*\n    97→   * Penny stocks is a problem where the random price change factor gets a\n    98→   * stock down to $.01. In this case trade jumpstarts the price back to $6.00\n    99→   * to keep the math interesting.\n   100→   */\n   101→  public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_PRICE;\n   102→  public static BigDecimal PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER;\n   103→  static {\n   104→    PENNY_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(0.01);\n   105→    PENNY_STOCK_PRICE = PENNY_STOCK_PRICE.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   106→    PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(600.0);\n   107→    PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  /*\n   111→   * CJB (DAYTRADER-25) - Also need to impose a ceiling on the quote price to\n   112→   * ensure prevent account and holding balances from exceeding the databases\n   113→   * decimal precision. At some point, this maximum value can be used to\n   114→   * trigger a stock split.\n   115→   */\n   116→\n   117→  public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE;\n   118→  public static BigDecimal MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER;\n   119→  static {\n   120→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE = new BigDecimal(400);\n   121→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   122→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER = new BigDecimal(0.5);\n   123→    MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER.setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   124→  }\n   125→\n   126→  /*\n   127→   * Trade Scenario actions mixes. Each of the array rows represents a\n   128→   * specific Trade Scenario Mix. The columns give the percentages for each\n   129→   * action in the column header. Note: \"login\" is always 0. logout represents\n   130→   * both login and logout (because each logout operation will cause a new\n   131→   * login when the user context attempts the next action.\n   132→   */\n   133→  /* Trade Scenario Workload parameters */\n   134→  public static final int HOME_OP = 0;\n   135→  public static final int QUOTE_OP = 1;\n   136→  public static final int LOGIN_OP = 2;\n   137→  public static final int LOGOUT_OP = 3;\n   138→  public static final int REGISTER_OP = 4;\n   139→  public static final int ACCOUNT_OP = 5;\n   140→  public static final int PORTFOLIO_OP = 6;\n   141→  public static final int BUY_OP = 7;\n   142→  public static final int SELL_OP = 8;\n   143→  public static final int UPDATEACCOUNT_OP = 9;\n   144→\n   145→  private static int[][] scenarioMixes = {\n   146→      // h q l o r a p b s u\n   147→      { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 10, 12, 4, 4, 4 }, // STANDARD\n   148→      { 20, 40, 0, 4, 2, 7, 7, 7, 7, 6 }, // High Volume\n   149→  };\n   150→  private static char[] actions = { 'h', 'q', 'l', 'o', 'r', 'a', 'p', 'b', 's', 'u' };\n   151→  private static int sellDeficit = 0;\n   152→  // Tracks the number of buys over sell when a users portfolio is empty\n   153→  // Used to maintain the correct ratio of buys/sells\n   154→\n   155→  /* JSP pages for all Trade Actions */\n   156→\n   157→  public static final int WELCOME_PAGE = 0;\n   158→  public static final int REGISTER_PAGE = 1;\n   159→  public static final int PORTFOLIO_PAGE = 2;\n   160→  public static final int QUOTE_PAGE = 3;\n   161→  public static final int HOME_PAGE = 4;\n   162→  public static final int ACCOUNT_PAGE = 5;\n   163→  public static final int ORDER_PAGE = 6;\n   164→  public static final int CONFIG_PAGE = 7;\n   165→  public static final int STATS_PAGE = 8;\n   166→  public static final int MARKET_SUMMARY_PAGE = 9;\n   167→\n   168→  // FUTURE Add XML/XSL View\n   169→  public static String[][] webUI = {\n   170→      { \"/welcome.jsp\", \"/register.jsp\", \"/portfolio.jsp\", \"/quote.jsp\", \"/tradehome.jsp\", \"/account.jsp\", \"/order.jsp\", \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\",\n   171→      \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   172→      // JSP Interface\n   173→      { \"/welcomeImg.jsp\", \"/registerImg.jsp\", \"/portfolioImg.jsp\", \"/quoteImg.jsp\", \"/tradehomeImg.jsp\", \"/accountImg.jsp\", \"/orderImg.jsp\",\n   174→        \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\", \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   175→      // JSP Interface\n   176→      { \"/welcomeImg.jsp\", \"/registerImg.jsp\", \"/portfolioImg.jsp\", \"/quoteImg.jsp\", \"/tradehomeImg.jsp\", \"/accountImg.jsp\", \"/orderImg.jsp\",\n   177→          \"/config.jsp\", \"/runStats.jsp\", \"/marketSummary.jsp\" },\n   178→  };\n   179→\n   180→\n   181→  /**\n   182→   * Return the hostname for this system Creation date: (2/16/2000 9:02:25 PM)\n   183→   */\n   184→\n   185→  private static String getHostname() {\n   186→    try {\n   187→      if (hostName == null) {\n   188→        hostName = java.net.InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName();\n   189→        // Strip of fully qualifed domain if necessary\n   190→        try {\n   191→          hostName = hostName.substring(0, hostName.indexOf('.'));\n   192→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   193→        }\n   194→      }\n   195→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   196→      Log.error(\"Exception getting local host name using 'localhost' - \", e);\n   197→      hostName = \"localhost\";\n   198→    }\n   199→    return hostName;\n   200→  }\n   201→\n   202→  /**\n   203→   * Return a Trade UI Web page based on the current configuration This may\n   204→   * return a JSP page or a Servlet page Creation date: (3/14/2000 9:08:34 PM)\n   205→   */\n   206→\n   207→  public static String getPage(int pageNumber) {\n   208→    return webUI[webInterface][pageNumber];\n   209→  }\n   210→\n   211→  /**\n   212→   * Return the list of run time mode names Creation date: (3/8/2000 5:58:34\n   213→   * PM)\n   214→   *\n   215→   * @return java.lang.String[]\n   216→   */\n   217→  public static java.lang.String[] getRunTimeModeNames() {\n   218→    return runTimeModeNames;\n   219→  }\n   220→\n   221→  private static int scenarioCount = 0;\n   222→\n   223→  /**\n   224→   * Return a Trade Scenario Operation based on the setting of the current mix\n   225→   * (TradeScenarioMix) Creation date: (2/10/2000 9:08:34 PM)\n   226→   */\n   227→\n   228→  public static char getScenarioAction(boolean newUser) {\n   229→    int r = rndInt(100); // 0 to 99 = 100\n   230→    int i = 0;\n   231→    int sum = scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   232→    while (sum <= r) {\n   233→      i++;\n   234→      sum += scenarioMixes[0][i];\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    incrementScenarioCount();\n   238→\n   239→    /*\n   240→     * In TradeScenarioServlet, if a sell action is selected, but the users\n   241→     * portfolio is empty, a buy is executed instead and sellDefecit is\n   242→     * incremented. This allows the number of buy/sell operations to stay in\n   243→     * sync w/ the given Trade mix.\n   244→     */\n   245→\n   246→    if ((!newUser) && (actions[i] == 'b')) {\n   247→      synchronized (TradeConfig.class) {\n   248→        if (sellDeficit > 0) {\n   249→          sellDeficit--;\n   250→          return 's';\n   251→          // Special case for TradeScenarioServlet to note this is a\n   252→          // buy switched to a sell to fix sellDeficit\n   253→        }\n   254→      }\n   255→    }\n   256→\n   257→    return actions[i];\n   258→  }\n   259→\n   260→  public static String getUserID() {\n   261→    String userID;\n   262→    if (RND_USER) {\n   263→      userID = rndUserID();\n   264→    } else {\n   265→      userID = nextUserID();\n   266→    }\n   267→    return userID;\n   268→  }\n   269→\n   270→  private static final BigDecimal orderFee = new BigDecimal(\"24.95\");\n   271→  private static final BigDecimal cashFee = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\");\n   272→\n   273→  public static BigDecimal getOrderFee(String orderType) {\n   274→    if ((orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"BUY\") == 0) || (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"SELL\") == 0)) {\n   275→      return orderFee;\n   276→    }\n   277→\n   278→    return cashFee;\n   279→\n   280→  }\n   281→\n   282→  /**\n   283→   * Increment the sell deficit counter Creation date: (6/21/2000 11:33:45 AM)\n   284→   */\n   285→  public static synchronized void incrementSellDeficit() {\n   286→    sellDeficit++;\n   287→  }\n   288→\n   289→  public static String nextUserID() {\n   290→    String userID;\n   291→    synchronized (userID_count_semaphore) {\n   292→      userID = \"uid:\" + userID_count;\n   293→      userID_count++;\n   294→      if (userID_count % MAX_USERS == 0) {\n   295→        userID_count = 0;\n   296→      }\n   297→    }\n   298→    return userID;\n   299→  }\n   300→\n   301→  public static double random() {\n   302→    return randomNumberGenerator.nextDouble();\n   303→  }\n   304→\n   305→  public static String rndAddress() {\n   306→    return rndInt(1000) + \" Oak St.\";\n   307→  }\n   308→\n   309→  public static String rndBalance() {\n   310→    // Give all new users a cool mill in which to trade\n   311→    return \"1000000\";\n   312→  }\n   313→\n   314→  public static String rndCreditCard() {\n   315→    return rndInt(100) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000) + \"-\" + rndInt(1000);\n   316→  }\n   317→\n   318→  public static String rndEmail(String userID) {\n   319→    return userID.replace(\":\", \"\") + \"@\" + rndInt(100) + \".com\";\n   320→  }\n   321→\n   322→  public static String rndFullName() {\n   323→    return \"first:\" + rndInt(1000) + \" last:\" + rndInt(5000);\n   324→  }\n   325→\n   326→  public static int rndInt(int i) {\n   327→    return (new Float(random() * i)).intValue();\n   328→  }\n   329→\n   330→  public static float rndFloat(int i) {\n   331→    return (new Float(random() * i)).floatValue();\n   332→  }\n   333→\n   334→  public static BigDecimal rndBigDecimal(float f) {\n   335→    return (new BigDecimal(random() * f)).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   336→  }\n   337→\n   338→  public static boolean rndBoolean() {\n   339→    return randomNumberGenerator.nextBoolean();\n   340→  }\n   341→\n   342→  /**\n   343→   * Returns a new Trade user Creation date: (2/16/2000 8:50:35 PM)\n   344→   */\n   345→  public static synchronized String rndNewUserID() {\n   346→\n   347→    return newUserPrefix + getHostname() + System.currentTimeMillis() + count++;\n   348→  }\n   349→\n   350→  public static float rndPrice() {\n   351→    return ((new Integer(rndInt(200))).floatValue()) + 1.0f;\n   352→  }\n   353→\n   354→  private static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(1.0);\n   355→\n   356→  public static BigDecimal getRandomPriceChangeFactor() {\n   357→    // CJB (DAYTRADER-25) - Vary change factor between 1.1 and 0.9\n   358→    double percentGain = rndFloat(1) * 0.1;\n   359→    if (random() < .5) {\n   360→      percentGain *= -1;\n   361→    }\n   362→    percentGain += 1;\n   363→\n   364→    // change factor is between +/- 20%\n   365→    BigDecimal percentGainBD = (new BigDecimal(percentGain)).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   366→    if (percentGainBD.doubleValue() <= 0.0) {\n   367→      percentGainBD = ONE;\n   368→    }\n   369→\n   370→    return percentGainBD;\n   371→  }\n   372→\n   373→  public static float rndQuantity() {\n   374→    return ((new Integer(rndInt(200))).floatValue()) + 1.0f;\n   375→  }\n   376→\n   377→  public static String rndSymbol() {\n   378→    return \"s:\" + rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1);\n   379→  }\n   380→\n   381→  public static String rndSymbols() {\n   382→\n   383→    String symbols = \"\";\n   384→    int num_symbols = rndInt(QUOTES_PER_PAGE);\n   385→\n   386→    for (int i = 0; i <= num_symbols; i++) {\n   387→      symbols += \"s:\" + rndInt(MAX_QUOTES - 1);\n   388→      if (i < num_symbols) {\n   389→        symbols += \",\";\n   390→      }\n   391→    }\n   392→    return symbols;\n   393→  }\n   394→\n   395→  public static String rndUserID() {\n   396→    String nextUser = getNextUserIDFromDeck();\n   397→\n   398→    Log.trace(\"TradeConfig:rndUserID -- new trader = \" + nextUser);\n   399→\n   400→\n   401→    return nextUser;\n   402→  }\n   403→\n   404→  private static synchronized String getNextUserIDFromDeck() {\n   405→    int numUsers = getMAX_USERS();\n   406→    if (deck == null) {\n   407→      deck = new ArrayList<Integer>(numUsers);\n   408→      for (int i = 0; i < numUsers; i++) {\n   409→        deck.add(i, new Integer(i));\n   410→      }\n   411→      java.util.Collections.shuffle(deck, r0);\n   412→    }\n   413→    if (card >= numUsers) {\n   414→      card = 0;\n   415→    }\n   416→    return \"uid:\" + deck.get(card++);\n   417→\n   418→  }\n   419→\n   420→  // Trade implements a card deck approach to selecting\n   421→  // users for trading with tradescenarioservlet\n   422→  private static ArrayList<Integer> deck = null;\n   423→  private static int card = 0;\n   424→\n   425→  /**\n   426→   * This is a convenience method for servlets to set Trade configuration\n   427→   * parameters from servlet initialization parameters. The servlet provides\n   428→   * the init param and its value as strings. This method then parses the\n   429→   * parameter, converts the value to the correct type and sets the\n   430→   * corresponding TradeConfig parameter to the converted value\n   431→   *\n   432→   */\n   433→  public static void setConfigParam(String parm, String value) {\n   434→    Log.log(\"TradeConfig setting parameter: \" + parm + \"=\" + value);\n   435→    // Compare the parm value to valid TradeConfig parameters that can be\n   436→    // set\n   437→    // by servlet initialization\n   438→\n   439→    // First check the proposed new parm and value - if empty or null ignore\n   440→    // it\n   441→    if (parm == null) {\n   442→      return;\n   443→    }\n   444→    parm = parm.trim();\n   445→    if (parm.length() <= 0) {\n   446→      return;\n   447→    }\n   448→    if (value == null) {\n   449→      return;\n   450→    }\n   451→    value = value.trim();\n   452→\n   453→    if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"orderProcessingMode\")) {\n   454→      try {\n   455→        for (int i = 0; i < orderProcessingModeNames.length; i++) {\n   456→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(orderProcessingModeNames[i])) {\n   457→            orderProcessingMode = i;\n   458→            break;\n   459→          }\n   460→        }\n   461→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   462→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set orderProcessingMode to \" + value\n   463→            + \"reverting to current value: \" + orderProcessingModeNames[orderProcessingMode], e);\n   464→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   465→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"accessMode\")) {\n   466→      try {\n   467→        for (int i = 0; i < accessModeNames.length; i++) {\n   468→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(accessModeNames[i])) {\n   469→            accessMode = i;\n   470→            break;\n   471→          }\n   472→        }\n   473→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   474→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set accessMode to \" + value + \"reverting to current value: \"\n   475→            + accessModeNames[accessMode], e);\n   476→      }\n   477→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"WebInterface\")) {\n   478→      try {\n   479→        for (int i = 0; i < webInterfaceNames.length; i++) {\n   480→          if (value.equalsIgnoreCase(webInterfaceNames[i])) {\n   481→            webInterface = i;\n   482→            break;\n   483→          }\n   484→        }\n   485→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   486→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"trying to set WebInterface to \" + value + \"reverting to current value: \"\n   487→            + webInterfaceNames[webInterface], e);\n   488→\n   489→      } // If the value is bad, simply revert to current\n   490→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"maxUsers\")) {\n   491→      try {\n   492→        MAX_USERS = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   493→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   494→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"Setting maxusers, error parsing string to int:\" + value\n   495→            + \"revering to current value: \" + MAX_USERS, e);\n   496→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   497→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"maxQuotes\")) {\n   498→      try {\n   499→        MAX_QUOTES = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   500→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   501→        // >>rjm\n   502→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(...) minor exception caught\" + \"Setting max_quotes, error parsing string to int \" + value\n   503→            + \"reverting to current value: \" + MAX_QUOTES, e);\n   504→        // <<rjm\n   505→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   506→    } else if (parm.equalsIgnoreCase(\"primIterations\")) {\n   507→      try {\n   508→        primIterations = Integer.parseInt(value);\n   509→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   510→        Log.error(\"TradeConfig.setConfigParm(..): minor exception caught\" + \"Setting primIterations, error parsing string to int:\" + value\n   511→            + \"revering to current value: \" + primIterations, e);\n   512→      } // On error, revert to saved\n   513→    } \n   514→  }\n   515→\n   516→  /**\n   517→   * Gets the orderProcessingModeNames\n   518→   *\n   519→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   520→   */\n   521→  public static String[] getOrderProcessingModeNames() {\n   522→    return orderProcessingModeNames;\n   523→  }\n   524→\n   525→  /**\n   526→   * Gets the webInterfaceNames\n   527→   *\n   528→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   529→   */\n   530→  public static String[] getWebInterfaceNames() {\n   531→    return webInterfaceNames;\n   532→  }\n   533→\n   534→  /**\n   535→   * Gets the webInterfaceNames\n   536→   *\n   537→   * @return Returns a String[]\n   538→   */\n   539→  /*public static String[] getCachingTypeNames() {\n   540→        return cachingTypeNames;\n   541→    }*/\n   542→\n   543→  /**\n   544→   * Gets the scenarioMixes\n   545→   *\n   546→   * @return Returns a int[][]\n   547→   */\n   548→  public static int[][] getScenarioMixes() {\n   549→    return scenarioMixes;\n   550→  }\n   551→\n   552→  /**\n   553→   * Gets the mAX_USERS.\n   554→   *\n   555→   * @return Returns a int\n   556→   */\n   557→  public static int getMAX_USERS() {\n   558→    return MAX_USERS;\n   559→  }\n   560→\n   561→  /**\n   562→   * Sets the mAX_USERS.\n   563→   *\n   564→   * @param mAX_USERS\n   565→   *            The mAX_USERS to set\n   566→   */\n   567→  public static void setMAX_USERS(int mAX_USERS) {\n   568→    MAX_USERS = mAX_USERS;\n   569→    deck = null; // reset the card deck for selecting users\n   570→  }\n   571→\n   572→  /**\n   573→   * Gets the mAX_QUOTES.\n   574→   *\n   575→   * @return Returns a int\n   576→   */\n   577→  public static int getMAX_QUOTES() {\n   578→    return MAX_QUOTES;\n   579→  }\n   580→\n   581→  /**\n   582→   * Sets the mAX_QUOTES.\n   583→   *\n   584→   * @param mAX_QUOTES\n   585→   *            The mAX_QUOTES to set\n   586→   */\n   587→  public static void setMAX_QUOTES(int mAX_QUOTES) {\n   588→    MAX_QUOTES = mAX_QUOTES;\n   589→  }\n   590→\n   591→  /**\n   592→   * Gets the mAX_HOLDINGS.\n   593→   *\n   594→   * @return Returns a int\n   595→   */\n   596→  public static int getMAX_HOLDINGS() {\n   597→    return MAX_HOLDINGS;\n   598→  }\n   599→\n   600→  /**\n   601→   * Sets the mAX_HOLDINGS.\n   602→   *\n   603→   * @param mAX_HOLDINGS\n   604→   *            The mAX_HOLDINGS to set\n   605→   */\n   606→  public static void setMAX_HOLDINGS(int mAX_HOLDINGS) {\n   607→    MAX_HOLDINGS = mAX_HOLDINGS;\n   608→  }\n   609→\n   610→  /**\n   611→   * Gets the scenarioCount.\n   612→   *\n   613→   * @return Returns a int\n   614→   */\n   615→  public static int getScenarioCount() {\n   616→    return scenarioCount;\n   617→  }\n   618→\n   619→  /**\n   620→   * Sets the scenarioCount.\n   621→   *\n   622→   * @param scenarioCount\n   623→   *            The scenarioCount to set\n   624→   */\n   625→  public static void setScenarioCount(int scenarioCount) {\n   626→    TradeConfig.scenarioCount = scenarioCount;\n   627→  }\n   628→\n   629→  public static synchronized void incrementScenarioCount() {\n   630→    scenarioCount++;\n   631→  }\n   632→\n   633→  /**\n   634→   * Gets the jdbc driver needs global transaction Some XA Drivers require a\n   635→   * global transaction to be started for all SQL calls. To work around this,\n   636→   * set this to true to cause the direct mode to start a user transaction.\n   637→   *\n   638→   * @return Returns a boolean\n   639→   */\n   640→  public static boolean getJDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation() {\n   641→    return JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation;\n   642→  }\n   643→\n   644→  /**\n   645→   * Sets the jdbc driver needs global transaction\n   646→   *\n   647→   * @param JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal\n   648→   *            the value\n   649→   */\n   650→  public static void setJDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation(boolean JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal) {\n   651→    JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransation = JDBCDriverNeedsGlobalTransationVal;\n   652→  }\n   653→\n   654→  /**\n   655→   * Gets the updateQuotePrices.\n   656→   *\n   657→   * @return Returns a boolean\n   658→   */\n   659→  public static boolean getUpdateQuotePrices() {\n   660→    return updateQuotePrices;\n   661→  }\n   662→\n   663→  /**\n   664→   * Sets the updateQuotePrices.\n   665→   *\n   666→   * @param updateQuotePrices\n   667→   *            The updateQuotePrices to set\n   668→   */\n   669→  public static void setUpdateQuotePrices(boolean updateQuotePrices) {\n   670→    TradeConfig.updateQuotePrices = updateQuotePrices;\n   671→  }\n   672→\n   673→  public static int getPrimIterations() {\n   674→    return primIterations;\n   675→  }\n   676→\n   677→  public static void setPrimIterations(int iter) {\n   678→    primIterations = iter;\n   679→  }\n   680→\n   681→  public static boolean getLongRun() {\n   682→    return longRun;\n   683→  }\n   684→\n   685→  public static void setLongRun(boolean longRun) {\n   686→    TradeConfig.longRun = longRun;\n   687→  }\n   688→\n   689→  public static void setPublishQuotePriceChange(boolean publishQuotePriceChange) {\n   690→    TradeConfig.publishQuotePriceChange = publishQuotePriceChange;\n   691→  }\n   692→\n   693→  public static boolean getPublishQuotePriceChange() {\n   694→    return publishQuotePriceChange;\n   695→  }\n   696→\n   697→  public static void setMarketSummaryInterval(int seconds) {\n   698→    TradeConfig.marketSummaryInterval = seconds;\n   699→  }\n   700→\n   701→  public static int getMarketSummaryInterval() {\n   702→    return TradeConfig.marketSummaryInterval;\n   703→  }\n   704→\n   705→  public static void setRunTimeMode(int value) {\n   706→    runTimeMode = value;\n   707→  }\n   708→\n   709→  public static int getRunTimeMode() {\n   710→    return runTimeMode;\n   711→  }\n   712→\n   713→  public static void setOrderProcessingMode(int value) {\n   714→    orderProcessingMode = value;\n   715→  }\n   716→\n   717→  public static int getOrderProcessingMode() {\n   718→    return orderProcessingMode;\n   719→  }\n   720→\n   721→  public static void setAccessMode(int value) {\n   722→    accessMode = value;\n   723→  }\n   724→\n   725→  public static int getAccessMode() {\n   726→    return accessMode;\n   727→  }\n   728→\n   729→  public static void setWebInterface(int value) {\n   730→    webInterface = value;\n   731→  }\n   732→\n   733→  public static int getWebInterface() {\n   734→    return webInterface;\n   735→  }\n   736→\n   737→  public static void setDisplayOrderAlerts(boolean value) {\n   738→    displayOrderAlerts = value;\n   739→  }\n   740→\n   741→  public static boolean getDisplayOrderAlerts() {\n   742→    return displayOrderAlerts;\n   743→  }\n   744→\n   745→  public static void setListQuotePriceChangeFrequency(int value) {\n   746→    listQuotePriceChangeFrequency = value;\n   747→  }\n   748→\n   749→  public static int getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() {\n   750→    return  listQuotePriceChangeFrequency;\n   751→  }\t\n   752→}\n   753→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"17782e76-96c5-4845-97a9-2ecc42610cd5"}
