{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UznnG2mqVjq8Q8zcpLy5Mv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.inject.Qualifier;\n    22→\n    23→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n    24→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\n    25→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n    26→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\n    27→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n    28→\n    29→@Qualifier\n    30→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    31→@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\n    32→public @interface TradeSession2Direct {}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"9c5f212a-71c1-4bcc-b487-911e03196cb5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MyZcXvoLEgN12JK7Vim6Ug","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"e9c2829b-27e6-458f-8e4f-49d7cc1fe941"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F8sq7Z28yGMUgaznNYBZow","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→import java.util.Comparator;\n    22→import java.util.Iterator;\n    23→import java.util.List;\n    24→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    25→\n    26→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    27→import javax.ejb.EJB;\n    28→import javax.ejb.EJBException;\n    29→import javax.ejb.SessionContext;\n    30→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n    31→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    32→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    33→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagement;\n    34→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\n    35→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    36→import javax.jms.JMSContext;\n    37→import javax.jms.Queue;\n    38→import javax.jms.QueueConnectionFactory;\n    39→import javax.jms.TextMessage;\n    40→import javax.jms.Topic;\n    41→import javax.jms.TopicConnectionFactory;\n    42→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n    43→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    44→import javax.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    45→import javax.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    46→import javax.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    47→import javax.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    48→import javax.transaction.RollbackException;\n    49→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    50→\n    51→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    52→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    53→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeEJB;\n    54→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    55→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    56→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    57→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    58→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    59→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    60→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    61→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    62→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    63→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    64→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    65→\n    66→@Stateless\n    67→@TradeEJB\n    68→@RuntimeMode(\"Full EJB3\")\n    69→@Trace\n    70→@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    71→@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    72→public class TradeSLSBBean implements TradeServices {\n    73→\n    74→    // For Wildfly - add java:/ to these resource names.\n    75→    @Resource(name = \"jms/QueueConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n    76→    //@Resource(name = \"java:/jms/QueueConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n    77→    private QueueConnectionFactory queueConnectionFactory;\n    78→\n    79→    @Resource(name = \"jms/TopicConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n    80→    //@Resource(name = \"java:/jms/TopicConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n    81→    private TopicConnectionFactory topicConnectionFactory;\n    82→\n    83→    @Resource(lookup = \"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\")\n    84→    //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jms/TradeStreamerTopic\")\n    85→    private Topic tradeStreamerTopic;\n    86→\n    87→    @Resource(lookup = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n    88→    //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n    89→    private Queue tradeBrokerQueue;\n    90→\n    91→    @PersistenceContext\n    92→    private EntityManager entityManager;\n    93→\n    94→    @Resource\n    95→    private SessionContext context;\n    96→\n    97→    @EJB\n    98→    MarketSummarySingleton marketSummarySingleton;\n    99→\n   100→    @Inject \n   101→    AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter asyncEJBOrderSubmitter;\n   102→\n   103→    @Inject\n   104→    RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n   105→\n   106→    @Override\n   107→    public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() {\n   108→        return marketSummarySingleton.getMarketSummaryDataBean();\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @Override\n   112→    @NotNull\n   113→    public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) {\n   114→        OrderDataBean order = null;\n   115→        BigDecimal total;\n   116→        try {\n   117→\n   118→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   119→            AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   120→            QuoteDataBean quote = entityManager.find(QuoteDataBean.class, symbol);\n   121→            HoldingDataBean holding = null; // The holding will be created by\n   122→            // this buy order\n   123→\n   124→            order = createOrder(account, quote, holding, \"buy\", quantity);\n   125→ \n   126→            // UPDATE - account should be credited during completeOrder\n   127→            BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   128→            BigDecimal orderFee = order.getOrderFee();\n   129→            BigDecimal balance = account.getBalance();\n   130→            total = (new BigDecimal(quantity).multiply(price)).add(orderFee);\n   131→            account.setBalance(balance.subtract(total));\n   132→            final Integer orderID=order.getOrderID();\n   133→\n   134→            if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.SYNCH) {\n   135→              completeOrder(orderID, false);\n   136→            } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n   137→              completeOrderAsync(orderID, false);\n   138→            } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   139→              queueOrder(orderID, true);\n   140→            }\n   141→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   142→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean:buy(\" + userID + \",\" + symbol + \",\" + quantity + \") --> failed\", e);\n   143→            /* On exception - cancel the order */\n   144→            // TODO figure out how to do this with JPA\n   145→            // if (order != null) order.cancel();\n   146→            throw new EJBException(e);\n   147→        }\n   148→        return order;\n   149→    }\n   150→\n   151→    @Override\n   152→    @NotNull\n   153→    public OrderDataBean sell(final String userID, final Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) {\n   154→        OrderDataBean order=null;\n   155→        BigDecimal total;\n   156→        try {\n   157→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   158→            AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   159→\n   160→            HoldingDataBean holding = entityManager.find(HoldingDataBean.class, holdingID);\n   161→\n   162→            if (holding == null) {\n   163→                Log.debug(\"TradeSLSBBean:sell User \" + userID + \" attempted to sell holding \" + holdingID + \" which has already been sold\");\n   164→\n   165→                OrderDataBean orderData = new OrderDataBean();\n   166→                orderData.setOrderStatus(\"cancelled\");\n   167→                entityManager.persist(orderData);\n   168→\n   169→                return orderData;\n   170→            }\n   171→\n   172→            QuoteDataBean quote = holding.getQuote();\n   173→            double quantity = holding.getQuantity();\n   174→\n   175→            order = createOrder(account, quote, holding, \"sell\", quantity);\n   176→\n   177→            // UPDATE the holding purchase data to signify this holding is\n   178→            // \"inflight\" to be sold\n   179→            // -- could add a new holdingStatus attribute to holdingEJB\n   180→            holding.setPurchaseDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(0));\n   181→\n   182→            // UPDATE - account should be credited during completeOrder\n   183→            BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   184→            BigDecimal orderFee = order.getOrderFee();\n   185→            BigDecimal balance = account.getBalance();\n   186→            total = (new BigDecimal(quantity).multiply(price)).subtract(orderFee);\n   187→            account.setBalance(balance.add(total));\n   188→            final Integer orderID=order.getOrderID(); \n   189→\n   190→            if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.SYNCH) {\n   191→                completeOrder(orderID, false);\n   192→            } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n   193→                completeOrderAsync(orderID, false);\n   194→            } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   195→                queueOrder(orderID, true);\n   196→            }\n   197→\n   198→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   199→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean:sell(\" + userID + \",\" + holdingID + \") --> failed\", e);\n   200→            // if (order != null) order.cancel();\n   201→            // UPDATE - handle all exceptions like:\n   202→            throw new EJBException(\"TradeSLSBBean:sell(\" + userID + \",\" + holdingID + \")\", e);\n   203→        }\n   204→        return order;\n   205→    }\n   206→\n   207→    public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n   208→\n   209→        // 2 phase\n   210→        try (JMSContext queueContext = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();) {\n   211→          TextMessage message = queueContext.createTextMessage();\n   212→\n   213→          message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\");\n   214→          message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID);\n   215→          message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase);\n   216→          message.setText(\"neworder: orderID=\" + orderID + \" runtimeMode=EJB twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n   217→          message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   218→\n   219→          queueContext.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n   220→\n   221→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   222→          throw new EJBException(e.getMessage(), e); // pass the exception\n   223→        }\n   224→    }\n   225→\n   226→    @Override\n   227→    public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   228→        OrderDataBean order = entityManager.find(OrderDataBean.class, orderID);\n   229→\n   230→        if (order == null) {\n   231→          System.out.println(\"error\");\n   232→            throw new EJBException(\"Error: attempt to complete Order that is null\\n\" + order);\n   233→        }\n   234→\n   235→        order.getQuote();\n   236→\n   237→        if (order.isCompleted()) {\n   238→            throw new EJBException(\"Error: attempt to complete Order that is already completed\\n\" + order);\n   239→        }\n   240→\n   241→        AccountDataBean account = order.getAccount();\n   242→        QuoteDataBean quote = order.getQuote();\n   243→        HoldingDataBean holding = order.getHolding();\n   244→        BigDecimal price = order.getPrice();\n   245→        double quantity = order.getQuantity();\n   246→\n   247→        if (order.isBuy()) {\n   248→            /*\n   249→             * Complete a Buy operation - create a new Holding for the Account -\n   250→             * deduct the Order cost from the Account balance\n   251→             */\n   252→\n   253→            HoldingDataBean newHolding = createHolding(account, quote, quantity, price);\n   254→            order.setHolding(newHolding);\n   255→            order.setOrderStatus(\"closed\");\n   256→            order.setCompletionDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   257→            updateQuotePriceVolume(quote.getSymbol(), TradeConfig.getRandomPriceChangeFactor(), quantity);\n   258→        }\n   259→\n   260→        if (order.isSell()) {\n   261→            /*\n   262→             * Complete a Sell operation - remove the Holding from the Account -\n   263→             * deposit the Order proceeds to the Account balance\n   264→             */\n   265→            if (holding == null) {\n   266→                Log.debug(\"TradeSLSBBean:completeOrder -- Unable to sell order \" + order.getOrderID() + \" holding already sold\");\n   267→                order.cancel();\n   268→                //throw new EJBException(\"TradeSLSBBean:completeOrder -- Unable to sell order \" + order.getOrderID() + \" holding already sold\");\n   269→            } else {\n   270→                entityManager.remove(holding);\n   271→                order.setHolding(null);\n   272→                order.setOrderStatus(\"closed\");\n   273→                order.setCompletionDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   274→                updateQuotePriceVolume(quote.getSymbol(), TradeConfig.getRandomPriceChangeFactor(), quantity);\n   275→            }\n   276→        } \n   277→\n   278→        Log.trace(\"TradeSLSBBean:completeOrder--> Completed Order \" + order.getOrderID() + \"\\n\\t Order info: \" + order + \"\\n\\t Account info: \" + account\n   279→            + \"\\n\\t Quote info: \" + quote + \"\\n\\t Holding info: \" + holding);\n   280→\n   281→        return order;\n   282→    }\n   283→\n   284→    @Override\n   285→    public Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   286→      asyncEJBOrderSubmitter.submitOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   287→      return null;\n   288→    }\n   289→\n   290→    @Override\n   291→    public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n   292→        OrderDataBean order = entityManager.find(OrderDataBean.class, orderID);\n   293→        order.cancel();\n   294→    }\n   295→\n   296→    @Override\n   297→    public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) {\n   298→        throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"TradeSLSBBean:orderCompleted method not supported\");\n   299→    }\n   300→\n   301→    @Override\n   302→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders(String userID) {\n   303→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   304→        AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   305→        return account.getOrders();\n   306→    }\n   307→\n   308→    @Override\n   309→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getClosedOrders(String userID) {\n   310→\n   311→        try {\n   312→            /* I want to do a CriteriaUpdate here, but there are issues with JBoss/Hibernate */\n   313→            CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n   314→            CriteriaQuery<OrderDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(OrderDataBean.class);\n   315→            Root<OrderDataBean> orders = criteriaQuery.from(OrderDataBean.class);\n   316→            criteriaQuery.select(orders);\n   317→            criteriaQuery.where(\n   318→                    criteriaBuilder.equal(orders.get(\"orderStatus\"), \n   319→                            criteriaBuilder.parameter(String.class, \"p_status\")), \n   320→                    criteriaBuilder.equal(orders.get(\"account\").get(\"profile\").get(\"userID\"), \n   321→                            criteriaBuilder.parameter(String.class, \"p_userid\")));\n   322→\n   323→            TypedQuery<OrderDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n   324→            q.setParameter(\"p_status\", \"closed\");\n   325→            q.setParameter(\"p_userid\", userID);\n   326→            List<OrderDataBean> results = q.getResultList();\n   327→\n   328→            Iterator<OrderDataBean> itr = results.iterator();\n   329→            // Spin through the orders to remove or mark completed\n   330→            while (itr.hasNext()) {\n   331→                OrderDataBean order = itr.next();\n   332→                // TODO: Investigate ConncurrentModification Exceptions\n   333→                if (TradeConfig.getLongRun()) {\n   334→                    //Added this for Longruns (to prevent orderejb growth)\n   335→                    entityManager.remove(order); \n   336→                }\n   337→                else {\n   338→                    order.setOrderStatus(\"completed\");\n   339→                }\n   340→            }\n   341→\n   342→            return results;\n   343→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   344→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean.getClosedOrders\", e);\n   345→            throw new EJBException(\"TradeSLSBBean.getClosedOrders - error\", e);\n   346→        }\n   347→    }\n   348→\n   349→    @Override\n   350→    public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) {\n   351→        try {\n   352→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean(symbol, companyName, 0, price, price, price, price, 0);\n   353→            entityManager.persist(quote);\n   354→\n   355→            Log.trace(\"TradeSLSBBean:createQuote-->\" + quote);\n   356→\n   357→            return quote;\n   358→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   359→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean:createQuote -- exception creating Quote\", e);\n   360→            throw new EJBException(e);\n   361→        }\n   362→    }\n   363→\n   364→    @Override\n   365→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) {\n   366→        return entityManager.find(QuoteDataBean.class, symbol);\n   367→    }\n   368→\n   369→    @Override\n   370→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getAllQuotes() {\n   371→        TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> query = entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"quoteejb.allQuotes\", QuoteDataBean.class);\n   372→        return query.getResultList();\n   373→    }\n   374→\n   375→    @Override\n   376→    public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n   377→        if (!TradeConfig.getUpdateQuotePrices()) {\n   378→            return new QuoteDataBean();\n   379→        }\n   380→\n   381→        Log.trace(\"TradeSLSBBean:updateQuote\", symbol, changeFactor);\n   382→\n   383→        TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"quoteejb.quoteForUpdate\", QuoteDataBean.class);\n   384→        q.setParameter(1, symbol);\n   385→        QuoteDataBean quote = q.getSingleResult();\n   386→\n   387→        BigDecimal oldPrice = quote.getPrice();\n   388→        BigDecimal openPrice = quote.getOpen();\n   389→\n   390→        if (oldPrice.equals(TradeConfig.PENNY_STOCK_PRICE)) {\n   391→            changeFactor = TradeConfig.PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER;\n   392→        } else if (oldPrice.compareTo(TradeConfig.MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE) > 0) {\n   393→            changeFactor = TradeConfig.MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER;\n   394→        }\n   395→\n   396→        BigDecimal newPrice = changeFactor.multiply(oldPrice).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   397→\n   398→        quote.setPrice(newPrice);\n   399→        quote.setChange(newPrice.subtract(openPrice).doubleValue());\n   400→        quote.setVolume(quote.getVolume() + sharesTraded);\n   401→        entityManager.merge(quote);\n   402→\n   403→        if (TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange()) {\n   404→          publishQuotePriceChange(quote, oldPrice, changeFactor, sharesTraded);\n   405→        }\n   406→\n   407→        recentQuotePriceChangeList.add(quote);\n   408→\n   409→        return quote;\n   410→    }\n   411→\n   412→    @Override\n   413→    public Collection<@NotNull HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) {\n   414→        CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n   415→        CriteriaQuery<HoldingDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(HoldingDataBean.class);\n   416→        Root<HoldingDataBean> holdings = criteriaQuery.from(HoldingDataBean.class);\n   417→        criteriaQuery.where(\n   418→                criteriaBuilder.equal(holdings.get(\"account\").get(\"profile\").get(\"userID\"), \n   419→                        criteriaBuilder.parameter(String.class, \"p_userid\")));\n   420→        criteriaQuery.select(holdings);\n   421→\n   422→        TypedQuery<HoldingDataBean> typedQuery = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n   423→        typedQuery.setParameter(\"p_userid\", userID);\n   424→        return typedQuery.getResultList();\n   425→    }\n   426→\n   427→    @Override\n   428→    public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) {\n   429→      return entityManager.find(HoldingDataBean.class, holdingID);\n   430→    }\n   431→\n   432→    @Override\n   433→    public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) {\n   434→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   435→        AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   436→\n   437→        // Added to populate transient field for account\n   438→        account.setProfileID(profile.getUserID());\n   439→\n   440→        return account;\n   441→    }\n   442→\n   443→    @Override\n   444→    public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) {\n   445→        return entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   446→    }\n   447→\n   448→    @Override\n   449→    public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) {\n   450→        AccountProfileDataBean temp = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, profileData.getUserID());\n   451→        temp.setAddress(profileData.getAddress());\n   452→        temp.setPassword(profileData.getPassword());\n   453→        temp.setFullName(profileData.getFullName());\n   454→        temp.setCreditCard(profileData.getCreditCard());\n   455→        temp.setEmail(profileData.getEmail());\n   456→\n   457→        entityManager.merge(temp);\n   458→\n   459→        return temp;\n   460→    }\n   461→\n   462→    @Override\n   463→    public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws RollbackException {\n   464→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   465→        if (profile == null) {\n   466→            throw new EJBException(\"No such user: \" + userID);\n   467→        }\n   468→\n   469→        AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   470→        account.login(password);\n   471→\n   472→        Log.trace(\"TradeSLSBBean:login(\" + userID + \",\" + password + \") success\" + account);\n   473→\n   474→        return account;\n   475→    }\n   476→\n   477→    @Override\n   478→    public void logout(String userID) {\n   479→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   480→        AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   481→        account.logout();\n   482→\n   483→        Log.trace(\"TradeSLSBBean:logout(\" + userID + \") success\");\n   484→    }\n   485→\n   486→    @Override\n   487→    public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   488→        AccountDataBean account = null;\n   489→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = null;\n   490→\n   491→        // Check to see if a profile with the desired userID already exists\n   492→        profile = entityManager.find(AccountProfileDataBean.class, userID);\n   493→\n   494→        if (profile != null) {\n   495→            Log.error(\"Failed to register new Account - AccountProfile with userID(\" + userID + \") already exists\");\n   496→            return null;\n   497→        } else {\n   498→            profile = new AccountProfileDataBean(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard);\n   499→            account = new AccountDataBean(0, 0, null, new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()), openBalance, openBalance, userID);\n   500→\n   501→            profile.setAccount(account);\n   502→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   503→\n   504→            entityManager.persist(profile);\n   505→            entityManager.persist(account);\n   506→        }\n   507→\n   508→        return account;\n   509→    }\n   510→\n   511→    @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRES_NEW)\n   512→    public void publishQuotePriceChange(QuoteDataBean quote, BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n   513→        if (!TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange()) {\n   514→            return;\n   515→        }\n   516→\n   517→        try (JMSContext topicContext = topicConnectionFactory.createContext();) {\n   518→            TextMessage message = topicContext.createTextMessage();\n   519→\n   520→            message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"updateQuote\");\n   521→            message.setStringProperty(\"symbol\", quote.getSymbol());\n   522→            message.setStringProperty(\"company\", quote.getCompanyName());\n   523→            message.setStringProperty(\"price\", quote.getPrice().toString());\n   524→            message.setStringProperty(\"oldPrice\", oldPrice.toString());\n   525→            message.setStringProperty(\"open\", quote.getOpen().toString());\n   526→            message.setStringProperty(\"low\", quote.getLow().toString());\n   527→            message.setStringProperty(\"high\", quote.getHigh().toString());\n   528→            message.setDoubleProperty(\"volume\", quote.getVolume());\n   529→            message.setStringProperty(\"changeFactor\", changeFactor.toString());\n   530→            message.setDoubleProperty(\"sharesTraded\", sharesTraded);\n   531→            message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   532→            message.setText(\"Update Stock price for \" + quote.getSymbol() + \" old price = \" + oldPrice + \" new price = \" + quote.getPrice());\n   533→\n   534→            topicContext.createProducer().send(tradeStreamerTopic, message);\n   535→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   536→             throw new EJBException(e.getMessage(), e); // pass the exception\n   537→        }\n   538→    }\n   539→\n   540→    public OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType, double quantity) {\n   541→        OrderDataBean order;\n   542→\n   543→        try {\n   544→            order = new OrderDataBean(orderType, \"open\", new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()), null, quantity, quote.getPrice().setScale(\n   545→                    FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND), TradeConfig.getOrderFee(orderType), account, quote, holding);\n   546→            entityManager.persist(order);\n   547→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   548→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean:createOrder -- failed to create Order. The stock/quote may not exist in the database.\", e);\n   549→            throw new EJBException(\"TradeSLSBBean:createOrder -- failed to create Order. Check that the symbol exists in the database.\", e);\n   550→        }\n   551→        return order;\n   552→    }\n   553→\n   554→    private HoldingDataBean createHolding(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice) throws Exception {\n   555→        HoldingDataBean newHolding = new HoldingDataBean(quantity, purchasePrice, new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()), account, quote);\n   556→        entityManager.persist(newHolding);\n   557→        return newHolding;\n   558→    }\n   559→\n   560→    @Override\n   561→    public double investmentReturn(double investment, double NetValue) throws Exception {\n   562→        double diff = NetValue - investment;\n   563→        double ir = diff / investment;\n   564→        return ir;\n   565→    }\n   566→\n   567→    @Override\n   568→    public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   569→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   570→\n   571→        try (JMSContext queueContext = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();) {\n   572→            // Get a Quote and send a JMS message in a 2-phase commit\n   573→            quoteData = entityManager.find(QuoteDataBean.class, symbol);\n   574→            \n   575→            double sharesTraded = (Math.random() * 100) + 1 ;\n   576→            BigDecimal oldPrice = quoteData.getPrice();\n   577→            BigDecimal openPrice = quoteData.getOpen();\n   578→            BigDecimal changeFactor = new BigDecimal (Math.random() * 100);\n   579→\n   580→            BigDecimal newPrice = changeFactor.multiply(oldPrice).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n   581→\n   582→            quoteData.setPrice(newPrice);\n   583→            quoteData.setChange(newPrice.subtract(openPrice).doubleValue());\n   584→            quoteData.setVolume(quoteData.getVolume() + sharesTraded);\n   585→            entityManager.merge(quoteData);\n   586→\n   587→            TextMessage message = queueContext.createTextMessage();\n   588→\n   589→            message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"ping\");\n   590→            message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   591→            message.setText(\"Ping message for queue java:comp/env/jms/TradeBrokerQueue sent from TradeSLSBBean:pingTwoPhase at \" + new java.util.Date());\n   592→            queueContext.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n   593→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   594→            Log.error(\"TradeSLSBBean:pingTwoPhase -- exception caught\", e);\n   595→        }\n   596→\n   597→        return quoteData;\n   598→    }\n   599→\n   600→    class quotePriceComparator implements Comparator<QuoteDataBean> {\n   601→        @Override\n   602→        public int compare(QuoteDataBean quote1, QuoteDataBean quote2) {\n   603→            double change1 = quote1.getChange();\n   604→            double change2 = quote2.getChange();\n   605→            return new Double(change2).compareTo(change1);\n   606→        }\n   607→    }\n   608→\n   609→    @Override\n   610→    public int getImpl() {\n   611→      return TradeConfig.EJB3;\n   612→    }\n   613→\n   614→    @Override\n   615→    public void setInSession(boolean inSession) {\n   616→      throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"TradeSLSBBean::setInGlobalTxn not supported\");\n   617→    }\n   618→}\n   619→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"c4d4cd5b-4ef0-4398-b9c6-1a7447b6242b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EgQPNmRjK5sTt6buXedMqG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.sql.Connection;\n    21→import java.sql.PreparedStatement;\n    22→import java.sql.ResultSet;\n    23→import java.sql.SQLException;\n    24→import java.sql.Statement;\n    25→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    26→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    27→import java.util.Collection;\n    28→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    29→\n    30→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    31→import javax.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedExecutorService;\n    32→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    33→import javax.enterprise.event.Event;\n    34→import javax.enterprise.event.NotificationOptions;\n    35→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    36→import javax.jms.JMSContext;\n    37→import javax.jms.JMSException;\n    38→import javax.jms.Queue;\n    39→import javax.jms.QueueConnectionFactory;\n    40→import javax.jms.TextMessage;\n    41→import javax.jms.Topic;\n    42→import javax.jms.TopicConnectionFactory;\n    43→import javax.sql.DataSource;\n    44→import javax.transaction.UserTransaction;\n    45→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    46→\n    47→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    48→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    49→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    50→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    51→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    52→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    53→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    54→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    55→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    56→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    57→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.RecentQuotePriceChangeList;\n    58→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    59→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    60→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    61→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    62→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    63→\n    64→/**\n    65→ * TradeDirect uses direct JDBC and JMS access to a\n    66→ * <code>javax.sql.DataSource</code> to implement the business methods of the\n    67→ * Trade online broker application. These business methods represent the\n    68→ * features and operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage\n    69→ * such as login, logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. and are\n    70→ * specified in the {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.TradeServices}\n    71→ * interface\n    72→ *\n    73→ * Note: In order for this class to be thread-safe, a new TradeJDBC must be\n    74→ * created for each call to a method from the TradeInterface interface.\n    75→ * Otherwise, pooled connections may not be released.\n    76→ *\n    77→ * @see com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.TradeServices\n    78→ *\n    79→ */\n    80→\n    81→@Dependent\n    82→@TradeJDBC\n    83→@RuntimeMode(\"Direct (JDBC)\")\n    84→@Trace\n    85→public class TradeDirect implements TradeServices, Serializable {\n    86→  /**\n    87→   * \n    88→   */\n    89→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -8089049090952927985L;\n    90→\n    91→  //This lock is used to serialize market summary operations.\n    92→  private static final Integer marketSummaryLock = new Integer(0);\n    93→  private static long nextMarketSummary = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    94→  private static MarketSummaryDataBean cachedMSDB = MarketSummaryDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    95→\n    96→  private static BigDecimal ZERO = new BigDecimal(0.0);\n    97→  private boolean inGlobalTxn = false;\n    98→  private boolean inSession = false;\n    99→\n   100→  // For Wildfly - add java:/ to these resource names.\n   101→\n   102→  @Resource(name = \"jms/QueueConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n   103→  //@Resource(name = \"java:/jms/QueueConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n   104→  private QueueConnectionFactory queueConnectionFactory;\n   105→\n   106→  @Resource(name = \"jms/TopicConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n   107→  //@Resource(name = \"java:/jms/TopicConnectionFactory\", authenticationType = javax.annotation.Resource.AuthenticationType.APPLICATION)\n   108→  private TopicConnectionFactory topicConnectionFactory;\n   109→\n   110→  @Resource(lookup = \"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\")\n   111→  //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jms/TradeStreamerTopic\")\n   112→  private Topic tradeStreamerTopic;\n   113→\n   114→  @Resource(lookup = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n   115→  //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jms/TradeBrokerQueue\")\n   116→  private Queue tradeBrokerQueue;\n   117→\n   118→  @Resource(lookup = \"jdbc/TradeDataSource\")\n   119→  //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jdbc/TradeDataSource\")\n   120→  private DataSource datasource;\n   121→\n   122→  @Resource\n   123→  private  UserTransaction txn;\n   124→\n   125→  @Inject\n   126→  RecentQuotePriceChangeList recentQuotePriceChangeList;\n   127→  \n   128→  @Inject \n   129→  AsyncOrderSubmitter asyncOrderSubmitter;  \n   130→  \n   131→  @Inject\n   132→  @MarketSummaryUpdate\n   133→  Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n   134→  \n   135→  @Resource\n   136→  private ManagedExecutorService mes;\n   137→  \n   138→\n   139→  @Override\n   140→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception {\n   141→\n   142→    if (TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() == 0) {\n   143→      return getMarketSummaryInternal();\n   144→    }\n   145→    if (TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() < 0) {\n   146→      return cachedMSDB;\n   147→    }\n   148→\n   149→    /**\n   150→     * This is a little funky. If its time to fetch a new Market summary\n   151→     * then we'll synchronize access to make sure only one requester does\n   152→     * it. Others will merely return the old copy until the new\n   153→     * MarketSummary has been executed.\n   154→     */\n   155→\n   156→    long currentTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   157→\n   158→    if (currentTime > nextMarketSummary) {\n   159→      long oldNextMarketSummary = nextMarketSummary;\n   160→      boolean fetch = false;\n   161→\n   162→      synchronized (marketSummaryLock) {\n   163→        /**\n   164→         * Is it still ahead or did we miss lose the race? If we lost\n   165→         * then let's get out of here as the work has already been done.\n   166→         */\n   167→        if (oldNextMarketSummary == nextMarketSummary) {\n   168→          fetch = true;\n   169→          nextMarketSummary += TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() * 1000;\n   170→\n   171→          /**\n   172→           * If the server has been idle for a while then its possible\n   173→           * that nextMarketSummary could be way off. Rather than try\n   174→           * and play catch up we'll simply get in sync with the\n   175→           * current time + the interval.\n   176→           */\n   177→          if (nextMarketSummary < currentTime) {\n   178→            nextMarketSummary = currentTime + TradeConfig.getMarketSummaryInterval() * 1000;\n   179→          }\n   180→        }\n   181→      }\n   182→\n   183→      /**\n   184→       * If we're the lucky one then let's update the MarketSummary\n   185→       */\n   186→      if (fetch) {\n   187→        cachedMSDB = getMarketSummaryInternal();\n   188→  \n   189→      }\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    return cachedMSDB;\n   193→  }\n   194→\n   195→\n   196→\n   197→  /**\n   198→   * @see TradeServices#getMarketSummary()\n   199→   */\n   200→\n   201→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryInternal() throws Exception {\n   202→\n   203→    MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryData = null;\n   204→    Connection conn = null;\n   205→    try {\n   206→\n   207→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getMarketSummary - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\");\n   208→\n   209→      conn = getConn();\n   210→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getTSIAQuotesOrderByChangeSQL, ResultSet.TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE, ResultSet.CONCUR_READ_ONLY);\n   211→\n   212→      ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainersData = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   213→      ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosersData = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   214→\n   215→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   216→\n   217→      int count = 0;\n   218→      while (rs.next() && (count++ < 5)) {\n   219→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   220→        topLosersData.add(quoteData);\n   221→      }\n   222→\n   223→      stmt.close();\n   224→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select * from quoteejb q order by q.change1 DESC\", ResultSet.TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE, ResultSet.CONCUR_READ_ONLY);\n   225→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   226→\n   227→      count = 0;\n   228→      while (rs.next() && (count++ < 5)) {\n   229→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   230→        topGainersData.add(quoteData);\n   231→      }\n   232→\n   233→      /*\n   234→       * rs.last(); count = 0; while (rs.previous() && (count++ < 5) ) {\n   235→       * QuoteDataBean quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   236→       * topGainersData.add(quoteData); }\n   237→       */\n   238→\n   239→      stmt.close();\n   240→\n   241→      BigDecimal TSIA = ZERO;\n   242→      BigDecimal openTSIA = ZERO;\n   243→      double volume = 0.0;\n   244→\n   245→      if ((topGainersData.size() > 0) || (topLosersData.size() > 0)) {\n   246→\n   247→        stmt = getStatement(conn, getTSIASQL);\n   248→        rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   249→\n   250→        if (!rs.next()) {\n   251→          Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getMarketSummary -- error w/ getTSIASQL -- no results\");\n   252→        } else {\n   253→          TSIA = rs.getBigDecimal(\"TSIA\");\n   254→        }\n   255→        stmt.close();\n   256→\n   257→        stmt = getStatement(conn, getOpenTSIASQL);\n   258→        rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   259→\n   260→        if (!rs.next()) {\n   261→          Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getMarketSummary -- error w/ getOpenTSIASQL -- no results\");\n   262→        } else {\n   263→          openTSIA = rs.getBigDecimal(\"openTSIA\");\n   264→        }\n   265→        stmt.close();\n   266→\n   267→        stmt = getStatement(conn, getTSIATotalVolumeSQL);\n   268→        rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   269→\n   270→        if (!rs.next()) {\n   271→          Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getMarketSummary -- error w/ getTSIATotalVolumeSQL -- no results\");\n   272→        } else {\n   273→          volume = rs.getDouble(\"totalVolume\");\n   274→        }\n   275→        stmt.close();\n   276→      }\n   277→      commit(conn);\n   278→\n   279→      marketSummaryData = new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, volume, topGainersData, topLosersData);\n   280→      mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\", NotificationOptions.builder().setExecutor(mes).build());\n   281→\n   282→    }\n   283→\n   284→    catch (Exception e) {\n   285→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:login -- error logging in user\", e);\n   286→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   287→    } finally {\n   288→      releaseConn(conn);\n   289→    }\n   290→    return marketSummaryData;\n   291→\n   292→  }\n   293→\n   294→  /**\n   295→   * @see TradeServices#buy(String, String, double)\n   296→   */\n   297→  @Override\n   298→  @NotNull\n   299→  public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n   300→\n   301→    final Connection conn = getConn();\n   302→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   303→\n   304→    BigDecimal total;\n   305→\n   306→    try {\n   307→\n   308→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:buy - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\");//, userID, symbol, new Double(quantity));\n   309→\n   310→\n   311→      if (!inSession && orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   312→\n   313→        Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:buy create/begin global transaction\");\n   314→\n   315→\n   316→        txn.begin();\n   317→        setInGlobalTxn(true);\n   318→      }\n   319→\n   320→      //conn = getConn();\n   321→\n   322→      AccountDataBean accountData = getAccountData(conn, userID);\n   323→      QuoteDataBean quoteData = getQuoteData(conn, symbol);\n   324→      HoldingDataBean holdingData = null; // the buy operation will create\n   325→      // the holding\n   326→\n   327→      orderData = createOrder(accountData, quoteData, holdingData, \"buy\", quantity);\n   328→\n   329→      // Update -- account should be credited during completeOrder\n   330→      BigDecimal price = quoteData.getPrice();\n   331→      BigDecimal orderFee = orderData.getOrderFee();\n   332→      total = (new BigDecimal(quantity).multiply(price)).add(orderFee);\n   333→      // subtract total from account balance\n   334→      creditAccountBalance(conn, accountData, total.negate());\n   335→      final Integer orderID = orderData.getOrderID();\n   336→\n   337→      try {\n   338→\n   339→        if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.SYNCH) {\n   340→          completeOrder(conn, orderData.getOrderID());\n   341→        } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n   342→          completeOrderAsync(orderID, true);\n   343→        } else  if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   344→          queueOrder(orderID, true); // 2-phase\n   345→        } \n   346→      } catch (JMSException je) {\n   347→        Log.error(\"TradeBean:buy(\" + userID + \",\" + symbol + \",\" + quantity + \") --> failed to queueOrder\", je);\n   348→\n   349→\n   350→        cancelOrder(conn, orderData.getOrderID());\n   351→      }\n   352→\n   353→      orderData = getOrderData(conn, orderData.getOrderID().intValue());\n   354→\n   355→      if (getInGlobalTxn()) {\n   356→        \n   357→        Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:buy committing global transaction\");\n   358→        \n   359→        if (!inSession && orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   360→          txn.commit();\n   361→          setInGlobalTxn(false);\n   362→        }\n   363→      } else {\n   364→        commit(conn);\n   365→      }\n   366→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   367→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:buy error - rolling back\", e);\n   368→      if (getInGlobalTxn()) {\n   369→        txn.rollback();\n   370→      } else {\n   371→        rollBack(conn, e);\n   372→      }\n   373→    } finally {\n   374→      releaseConn(conn);\n   375→    }\n   376→\n   377→    return orderData;\n   378→  }\n   379→\n   380→  /**\n   381→   * @see TradeServices#sell(String, Integer)\n   382→   */\n   383→  @Override\n   384→  @NotNull\n   385→  public OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n   386→    Connection conn = null;\n   387→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   388→    //UserTransaction txn = null;\n   389→\n   390→    /*\n   391→     * total = (quantity * purchasePrice) + orderFee\n   392→     */\n   393→    BigDecimal total;\n   394→\n   395→    try {\n   396→     \n   397→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:sell - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID, holdingID);\n   398→      \n   399→\n   400→      if (!inSession && orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   401→       \n   402→        Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:sell create/begin global transaction\");\n   403→        \n   404→        txn.begin();\n   405→        setInGlobalTxn(true);\n   406→      }\n   407→\n   408→      conn = getConn();\n   409→\n   410→      AccountDataBean accountData = getAccountData(conn, userID);\n   411→      HoldingDataBean holdingData = getHoldingData(conn, holdingID.intValue());\n   412→      QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   413→      if (holdingData != null) {\n   414→        quoteData = getQuoteData(conn, holdingData.getQuoteID());\n   415→      }\n   416→\n   417→      if ((accountData == null) || (holdingData == null) || (quoteData == null)) {\n   418→        String error = \"TradeDirect:sell -- error selling stock -- unable to find:  \\n\\taccount=\" + accountData + \"\\n\\tholding=\" + holdingData\n   419→            + \"\\n\\tquote=\" + quoteData + \"\\nfor user: \" + userID + \" and holdingID: \" + holdingID;\n   420→        Log.debug(error);\n   421→        if (getInGlobalTxn()) {\n   422→          txn.rollback();\n   423→        } else {\n   424→          rollBack(conn, new Exception(error));\n   425→        }\n   426→        orderData = new OrderDataBean();\n   427→        orderData.setOrderStatus(\"cancelled\");\n   428→        return orderData;\n   429→      }\n   430→\n   431→      double quantity = holdingData.getQuantity();\n   432→\n   433→      orderData = createOrder(accountData, quoteData, holdingData, \"sell\", quantity);\n   434→\n   435→      // Set the holdingSymbol purchaseDate to selling to signify the sell\n   436→      // is \"inflight\"\n   437→      updateHoldingStatus(conn, holdingData.getHoldingID(), holdingData.getQuoteID());\n   438→\n   439→      // UPDATE -- account should be credited during completeOrder\n   440→      BigDecimal price = quoteData.getPrice();\n   441→      BigDecimal orderFee = orderData.getOrderFee();\n   442→      total = (new BigDecimal(quantity).multiply(price)).subtract(orderFee);\n   443→      creditAccountBalance(conn, accountData, total);\n   444→\n   445→      try {\n   446→        if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.SYNCH) {\n   447→          completeOrder(conn, orderData.getOrderID());\n   448→        } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n   449→          this.completeOrderAsync(orderData.getOrderID(), true);\n   450→        } else if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   451→          queueOrder(orderData.getOrderID(), true);\n   452→        } \n   453→      } catch (JMSException je) {\n   454→        Log.error(\"TradeBean:sell(\" + userID + \",\" + holdingID + \") --> failed to queueOrder\", je);\n   455→\n   456→        cancelOrder(conn, orderData.getOrderID());\n   457→      }\n   458→\n   459→      orderData = getOrderData(conn, orderData.getOrderID().intValue());\n   460→\n   461→      if (!inSession && orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH_2PHASE) {\n   462→       \n   463→        Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:sell committing global transaction\");\n   464→        \n   465→        txn.commit();\n   466→        setInGlobalTxn(false);\n   467→      } else {\n   468→        commit(conn);\n   469→      }\n   470→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   471→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:sell error\", e);\n   472→      if (getInGlobalTxn()) {\n   473→        txn.rollback();\n   474→      } else {\n   475→        rollBack(conn, e);\n   476→      }\n   477→    } finally {\n   478→      releaseConn(conn);\n   479→    }\n   480→\n   481→    return orderData;\n   482→  }\n   483→\n   484→  /**\n   485→   * @see TradeServices#queueOrder(Integer)\n   486→   */\n   487→  @Override\n   488→  public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   489→\n   490→   \n   491→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:queueOrder - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", orderID);\n   492→    \n   493→\n   494→    try (JMSContext context = queueConnectionFactory.createContext();){\t\n   495→      TextMessage message = context.createTextMessage();\n   496→\n   497→      message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\");\n   498→      message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID.intValue());\n   499→      message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase);\n   500→      message.setBooleanProperty(\"direct\", true);\n   501→      message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   502→      message.setText(\"neworder: orderID=\" + orderID + \" runtimeMode=Direct twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n   503→\n   504→      context.createProducer().send(tradeBrokerQueue, message);\n   505→    } catch (Exception e) {            \n   506→      throw e; // pass the exception\n   507→    }\n   508→  }\n   509→\n   510→  /**\n   511→   * @see TradeServices#completeOrder(Integer)\n   512→   */\n   513→  @Override\n   514→  public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   515→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   516→    Connection conn = null;\n   517→\n   518→    try { // twoPhase\n   519→\n   520→    \n   521→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", orderID);\n   522→      \n   523→      setInGlobalTxn(!inSession && twoPhase);\n   524→      conn = getConn();\n   525→\n   526→      orderData = completeOrder(conn, orderID);\n   527→\n   528→      commit(conn);\n   529→\n   530→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   531→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder -- error completing order\", e);\n   532→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   533→      cancelOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   534→    } finally {\n   535→      releaseConn(conn);\n   536→    }\n   537→\n   538→    return orderData;\n   539→\n   540→  }\n   541→\n   542→  @Override\n   543→  public Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   544→    if (!inSession) {\n   545→      asyncOrderSubmitter.submitOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   546→    }\n   547→    return null;\n   548→  }\n   549→\n   550→\n   551→  private OrderDataBean completeOrder(Connection conn, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   552→    //conn = getConn();\n   553→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   554→   \n   555→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:completeOrderInternal - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", orderID);\n   556→    \n   557→\n   558→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getOrderSQL);\n   559→    stmt.setInt(1, orderID.intValue());\n   560→\n   561→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   562→\n   563→    if (!rs.next()) {\n   564→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder -- unable to find order: \" + orderID);\n   565→      stmt.close();\n   566→      return orderData;\n   567→    }\n   568→    orderData = getOrderDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   569→\n   570→    String orderType = orderData.getOrderType();\n   571→    String orderStatus = orderData.getOrderStatus();\n   572→\n   573→    // if (order.isCompleted())\n   574→    if ((orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"completed\") == 0) || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"alertcompleted\") == 0)\n   575→        || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"cancelled\") == 0)) {\n   576→      throw new Exception(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder -- attempt to complete Order that is already completed\");\n   577→    }\n   578→\n   579→    int accountID = rs.getInt(\"account_accountID\");\n   580→    String quoteID = rs.getString(\"quote_symbol\");\n   581→    int holdingID = rs.getInt(\"holding_holdingID\");\n   582→\n   583→    BigDecimal price = orderData.getPrice();\n   584→    double quantity = orderData.getQuantity();\n   585→\n   586→    // get the data for the account and quote\n   587→    // the holding will be created for a buy or extracted for a sell\n   588→\n   589→    /*\n   590→     * Use the AccountID and Quote Symbol from the Order AccountDataBean\n   591→     * accountData = getAccountData(accountID, conn); QuoteDataBean\n   592→     * quoteData = getQuoteData(conn, quoteID);\n   593→     */\n   594→    String userID = getAccountProfileData(conn, new Integer(accountID)).getUserID();\n   595→\n   596→    HoldingDataBean holdingData = null;\n   597→\n   598→   \n   599→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder--> Completing Order \" + orderData.getOrderID() + \"\\n\\t Order info: \" + orderData + \"\\n\\t Account info: \"\n   600→          + accountID + \"\\n\\t Quote info: \" + quoteID);\n   601→    \n   602→\n   603→    // if (order.isBuy())\n   604→    if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"buy\") == 0) {\n   605→      /*\n   606→       * Complete a Buy operation - create a new Holding for the Account -\n   607→       * deduct the Order cost from the Account balance\n   608→       */\n   609→\n   610→      holdingData = createHolding(conn, accountID, quoteID, quantity, price);\n   611→      updateOrderHolding(conn, orderID.intValue(), holdingData.getHoldingID().intValue());\n   612→      updateOrderStatus(conn, orderData.getOrderID(), \"closed\");\n   613→      updateQuotePriceVolume(orderData.getSymbol(), TradeConfig.getRandomPriceChangeFactor(), orderData.getQuantity());\n   614→    }\n   615→\n   616→    // if (order.isSell()) {\n   617→    if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"sell\") == 0) {\n   618→      /*\n   619→       * Complete a Sell operation - remove the Holding from the Account -\n   620→       * deposit the Order proceeds to the Account balance\n   621→       */\n   622→      holdingData = getHoldingData(conn, holdingID);\n   623→      if (holdingData == null) {\n   624→        Log.debug(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder:sell -- user: \" + userID + \" already sold holding: \" + holdingID);\n   625→        updateOrderStatus(conn, orderData.getOrderID(), \"cancelled\");\n   626→      } else {\n   627→        removeHolding(conn, holdingID, orderID.intValue());\n   628→        updateOrderStatus(conn, orderData.getOrderID(), \"closed\");\n   629→        updateQuotePriceVolume(orderData.getSymbol(), TradeConfig.getRandomPriceChangeFactor(), orderData.getQuantity());\n   630→      }\n   631→\n   632→    } \n   633→\n   634→\n   635→\n   636→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:completeOrder--> Completed Order \" + orderData.getOrderID() + \"\\n\\t Order info: \" + orderData + \"\\n\\t Account info: \"\n   637→          + accountID + \"\\n\\t Quote info: \" + quoteID + \"\\n\\t Holding info: \" + holdingData);\n   638→    \n   639→    stmt.close();\n   640→\n   641→    commit(conn);\n   642→\n   643→\n   644→\n   645→    return orderData;\n   646→  }\n   647→\n   648→  /**\n   649→   * @see TradeServices#cancelOrder(Integer, boolean)\n   650→   */\n   651→  @Override\n   652→  public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   653→\n   654→    Connection conn = null;\n   655→    try {\n   656→     \n   657→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:cancelOrder - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", orderID);\n   658→      \n   659→      setInGlobalTxn(!inSession && twoPhase);\n   660→      conn = getConn();\n   661→      cancelOrder(conn, orderID);\n   662→      commit(conn);\n   663→\n   664→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   665→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:cancelOrder -- error cancelling order: \" + orderID, e);\n   666→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   667→    } finally {\n   668→      releaseConn(conn);\n   669→    }\n   670→  }\n   671→\n   672→  private void cancelOrder(Connection conn, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   673→    updateOrderStatus(conn, orderID, \"cancelled\");\n   674→  }\n   675→\n   676→  @Override\n   677→  public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   678→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"TradeDirect:orderCompleted method not supported\");\n   679→  }\n   680→\n   681→  private HoldingDataBean createHolding(Connection conn, int accountID, String symbol, double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice) throws Exception {\n   682→\n   683→    Timestamp purchaseDate = new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis());\n   684→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, createHoldingSQL);\n   685→\n   686→    Integer holdingID = KeySequenceDirect.getNextID(conn, \"holding\", inSession, getInGlobalTxn());\n   687→    stmt.setInt(1, holdingID.intValue());\n   688→    stmt.setTimestamp(2, purchaseDate);\n   689→    stmt.setBigDecimal(3, purchasePrice);\n   690→    stmt.setDouble(4, quantity);\n   691→    stmt.setString(5, symbol);\n   692→    stmt.setInt(6, accountID);\n   693→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n   694→\n   695→    stmt.close();\n   696→\n   697→    return getHoldingData(conn, holdingID.intValue());\n   698→  }\n   699→\n   700→  private void removeHolding(Connection conn, int holdingID, int orderID) throws Exception {\n   701→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, removeHoldingSQL);\n   702→\n   703→    stmt.setInt(1, holdingID);\n   704→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n   705→    stmt.close();\n   706→\n   707→    // set the HoldingID to NULL for the purchase and sell order now that\n   708→    // the holding as been removed\n   709→    stmt = getStatement(conn, removeHoldingFromOrderSQL);\n   710→\n   711→    stmt.setInt(1, holdingID);\n   712→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n   713→    stmt.close();\n   714→\n   715→  }\n   716→\n   717→  public OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean accountData, QuoteDataBean quoteData, HoldingDataBean holdingData, String orderType,\n   718→      double quantity) throws Exception {\n   719→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   720→    Connection conn = null;\n   721→    try {\n   722→\n   723→      conn = getConn();\n   724→      Timestamp currentDate = new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis());\n   725→\n   726→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, createOrderSQL);\n   727→\n   728→      Integer orderID = KeySequenceDirect.getNextID(conn, \"order\", inSession, getInGlobalTxn());\n   729→      stmt.setInt(1, orderID.intValue());\n   730→      stmt.setString(2, orderType);\n   731→      stmt.setString(3, \"open\");\n   732→      stmt.setTimestamp(4, currentDate);\n   733→      stmt.setDouble(5, quantity);\n   734→      stmt.setBigDecimal(6, quoteData.getPrice().setScale(FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND));\n   735→      stmt.setBigDecimal(7, TradeConfig.getOrderFee(orderType));\n   736→      stmt.setInt(8, accountData.getAccountID().intValue());\n   737→      if (holdingData == null) {\n   738→        stmt.setNull(9, java.sql.Types.INTEGER);\n   739→      } else {\n   740→        stmt.setInt(9, holdingData.getHoldingID().intValue());\n   741→      }\n   742→      stmt.setString(10, quoteData.getSymbol());\n   743→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   744→\n   745→      orderData = getOrderData(conn, orderID.intValue());\n   746→\n   747→      stmt.close();\n   748→\n   749→      commit(conn);\n   750→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   751→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:createOrder -- error getting user orders\", e);\n   752→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   753→    } finally {\n   754→      releaseConn(conn);\n   755→    }\n   756→\n   757→    return orderData;\n   758→  }\n   759→\n   760→  /**\n   761→   * @see TradeServices#getOrders(String)\n   762→   */\n   763→  @Override\n   764→  public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   765→    Collection<OrderDataBean> orderDataBeans = new ArrayList<OrderDataBean>();\n   766→    Connection conn = null;\n   767→    try {\n   768→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getOrders - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n   769→      \n   770→\n   771→      conn = getConn();\n   772→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getOrdersByUserSQL);\n   773→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n   774→\n   775→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   776→\n   777→      // TODO: return top 5 orders for now -- next version will add a\n   778→      // getAllOrders method\n   779→      // also need to get orders sorted by order id descending\n   780→      int i = 0;\n   781→      while ((rs.next()) && (i++ < 5)) {\n   782→        OrderDataBean orderData = getOrderDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   783→        orderDataBeans.add(orderData);\n   784→      }\n   785→\n   786→      stmt.close();\n   787→      commit(conn);\n   788→\n   789→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   790→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getOrders -- error getting user orders\", e);\n   791→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   792→    } finally {\n   793→      releaseConn(conn);\n   794→    }\n   795→    return orderDataBeans;\n   796→  }\n   797→\n   798→  /**\n   799→   * @see TradeServices#getClosedOrders(String)\n   800→   */\n   801→  @Override\n   802→  public Collection<OrderDataBean> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   803→    Collection<OrderDataBean> orderDataBeans = new ArrayList<OrderDataBean>();\n   804→    Connection conn = null;\n   805→    try {\n   806→\n   807→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getClosedOrders - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n   808→      \n   809→\n   810→      conn = getConn();\n   811→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getClosedOrdersSQL);\n   812→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n   813→\n   814→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   815→\n   816→      while (rs.next()) {\n   817→        OrderDataBean orderData = getOrderDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   818→        orderData.setOrderStatus(\"completed\");\n   819→        updateOrderStatus(conn, orderData.getOrderID(), orderData.getOrderStatus());\n   820→        orderDataBeans.add(orderData);\n   821→\n   822→      }\n   823→\n   824→      stmt.close();\n   825→      commit(conn);\n   826→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   827→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getOrders -- error getting user orders\", e);\n   828→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   829→    } finally {\n   830→      releaseConn(conn);\n   831→    }\n   832→    return orderDataBeans;\n   833→  }\n   834→\n   835→  /**\n   836→   * @see TradeServices#createQuote(String, String, BigDecimal)\n   837→   */\n   838→  @Override\n   839→  public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception {\n   840→\n   841→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   842→    Connection conn = null;\n   843→    try {\n   844→\n   845→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:createQuote - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\");\n   846→      \n   847→\n   848→      price = price.setScale(FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   849→      double volume = 0.0, change = 0.0;\n   850→\n   851→      conn = getConn();\n   852→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, createQuoteSQL);\n   853→      stmt.setString(1, symbol); // symbol\n   854→      stmt.setString(2, companyName); // companyName\n   855→      stmt.setDouble(3, volume); // volume\n   856→      stmt.setBigDecimal(4, price); // price\n   857→      stmt.setBigDecimal(5, price); // open\n   858→      stmt.setBigDecimal(6, price); // low\n   859→      stmt.setBigDecimal(7, price); // high\n   860→      stmt.setDouble(8, change); // change\n   861→\n   862→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   863→      stmt.close();\n   864→      commit(conn);\n   865→\n   866→      quoteData = new QuoteDataBean(symbol, companyName, volume, price, price, price, price, change);\n   867→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   868→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:createQuote -- error creating quote\", e);\n   869→    } finally {\n   870→      releaseConn(conn);\n   871→    }\n   872→    return quoteData;\n   873→  }\n   874→\n   875→  /**\n   876→   * @see TradeServices#getQuote(String)\n   877→   */\n   878→\n   879→  @Override\n   880→  public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   881→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   882→    Connection conn = null;\n   883→\n   884→    try {\n   885→     \n   886→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getQuote - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", symbol);\n   887→    \n   888→\n   889→      conn = getConn();\n   890→      quoteData = getQuote(conn, symbol);\n   891→      commit(conn);\n   892→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   893→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getQuote -- error getting quote\", e);\n   894→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   895→    } finally {\n   896→      releaseConn(conn);\n   897→    }\n   898→    return quoteData;\n   899→  }\n   900→\n   901→  private QuoteDataBean getQuote(Connection conn, String symbol) throws Exception {\n   902→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   903→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getQuoteSQL);\n   904→    stmt.setString(1, symbol); // symbol\n   905→\n   906→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   907→\n   908→    if (!rs.next()) {\n   909→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getQuote -- failure no result.next() for symbol: \" + symbol);\n   910→    } else {\n   911→      quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   912→    }\n   913→\n   914→    stmt.close();\n   915→\n   916→    return quoteData;\n   917→  }\n   918→\n   919→  private QuoteDataBean getQuoteForUpdate(Connection conn, String symbol) throws Exception {\n   920→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   921→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getQuoteForUpdateSQL);\n   922→    stmt.setString(1, symbol); // symbol\n   923→\n   924→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   925→\n   926→    if (!rs.next()) {\n   927→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getQuote -- failure no result.next()\");\n   928→    } else {\n   929→      quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   930→    }\n   931→\n   932→    stmt.close();\n   933→\n   934→    return quoteData;\n   935→  }\n   936→\n   937→  /**\n   938→   * @see TradeServices#getAllQuotes(String)\n   939→   */\n   940→  @Override\n   941→  public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getAllQuotes() throws Exception {\n   942→    Collection<QuoteDataBean> quotes = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n   943→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n   944→\n   945→    Connection conn = null;\n   946→    try {\n   947→      conn = getConn();\n   948→\n   949→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAllQuotesSQL);\n   950→\n   951→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   952→\n   953→      while (!rs.next()) {\n   954→        quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   955→        quotes.add(quoteData);\n   956→      }\n   957→\n   958→      stmt.close();\n   959→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   960→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAllQuotes\", e);\n   961→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   962→    } finally {\n   963→      releaseConn(conn);\n   964→    }\n   965→\n   966→    return quotes;\n   967→  }\n   968→\n   969→  /**\n   970→   * @see TradeServices#getHoldings(String)\n   971→   */\n   972→  @Override\n   973→  public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception {\n   974→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdingDataBeans = new ArrayList<HoldingDataBean>();\n   975→    Connection conn = null;\n   976→    try {\n   977→    \n   978→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getHoldings - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n   979→      \n   980→\n   981→      conn = getConn();\n   982→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getHoldingsForUserSQL);\n   983→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n   984→\n   985→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   986→\n   987→      while (rs.next()) {\n   988→        HoldingDataBean holdingData = getHoldingDataFromResultSet(rs);\n   989→        holdingDataBeans.add(holdingData);\n   990→      }\n   991→\n   992→      stmt.close();\n   993→      commit(conn);\n   994→\n   995→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   996→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getHoldings -- error getting user holings\", e);\n   997→      rollBack(conn, e);\n   998→    } finally {\n   999→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1000→    }\n  1001→    return holdingDataBeans;\n  1002→  }\n  1003→\n  1004→  /**\n  1005→   * @see TradeServices#getHolding(Integer)\n  1006→   */\n  1007→  @Override\n  1008→  public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception {\n  1009→    HoldingDataBean holdingData = null;\n  1010→    Connection conn = null;\n  1011→    try {\n  1012→\n  1013→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getHolding - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", holdingID);\n  1014→      \n  1015→\n  1016→      conn = getConn();\n  1017→      holdingData = getHoldingData(holdingID.intValue());\n  1018→\n  1019→      commit(conn);\n  1020→\n  1021→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1022→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getHolding -- error getting holding \" + holdingID + \"\", e);\n  1023→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1024→    } finally {\n  1025→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1026→    }\n  1027→    return holdingData;\n  1028→  }\n  1029→\n  1030→  /**\n  1031→   * @see TradeServices#getAccountData(String)\n  1032→   */\n  1033→  @Override\n  1034→  public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception {\n  1035→    try {\n  1036→      AccountDataBean accountData = null;\n  1037→      Connection conn = null;\n  1038→      try {\n  1039→\n  1040→        Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getAccountData - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n  1041→        \n  1042→\n  1043→        conn = getConn();\n  1044→        accountData = getAccountData(conn, userID);\n  1045→        commit(conn);\n  1046→\n  1047→      } catch (Exception e) {\n  1048→        Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountData -- error getting account data\", e);\n  1049→        rollBack(conn, e);\n  1050→      } finally {\n  1051→        releaseConn(conn);\n  1052→      }\n  1053→      return accountData;\n  1054→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1055→      throw new Exception(e.getMessage(), e);\n  1056→    }\n  1057→  }\n  1058→\n  1059→  private AccountDataBean getAccountData(Connection conn, String userID) throws Exception {\n  1060→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountForUserSQL);\n  1061→    stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1062→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1063→    AccountDataBean accountData = getAccountDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1064→    stmt.close();\n  1065→    return accountData;\n  1066→  }\n  1067→\n  1068→  /**\n  1069→   * @see TradeServices#getAccountData(String)\n  1070→   */\n  1071→  public AccountDataBean getAccountData(int accountID) throws Exception {\n  1072→    AccountDataBean accountData = null;\n  1073→    Connection conn = null;\n  1074→    try {\n  1075→     \n  1076→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getAccountData - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", new Integer(accountID));\n  1077→\n  1078→      conn = getConn();\n  1079→      accountData = getAccountData(accountID, conn);\n  1080→      commit(conn);\n  1081→\n  1082→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1083→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountData -- error getting account data\", e);\n  1084→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1085→    } finally {\n  1086→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1087→    }\n  1088→    return accountData;\n  1089→  }\n  1090→\n  1091→  private AccountDataBean getAccountData(int accountID, Connection conn) throws Exception {\n  1092→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountSQL);\n  1093→    stmt.setInt(1, accountID);\n  1094→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1095→    AccountDataBean accountData = getAccountDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1096→    stmt.close();\n  1097→    return accountData;\n  1098→  }\n  1099→\n  1100→  private QuoteDataBean getQuoteData(Connection conn, String symbol) throws Exception {\n  1101→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n  1102→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getQuoteSQL);\n  1103→    stmt.setString(1, symbol);\n  1104→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1105→    if (!rs.next()) {\n  1106→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getQuoteData -- could not find quote for symbol=\" + symbol);\n  1107→    } else {\n  1108→      quoteData = getQuoteDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1109→    }\n  1110→    stmt.close();\n  1111→    return quoteData;\n  1112→  }\n  1113→\n  1114→  private HoldingDataBean getHoldingData(int holdingID) throws Exception {\n  1115→    HoldingDataBean holdingData = null;\n  1116→    Connection conn = null;\n  1117→    try {\n  1118→      conn = getConn();\n  1119→      holdingData = getHoldingData(conn, holdingID);\n  1120→      commit(conn);\n  1121→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1122→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getHoldingData -- error getting data\", e);\n  1123→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1124→    } finally {\n  1125→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1126→    }\n  1127→    return holdingData;\n  1128→  }\n  1129→\n  1130→  private HoldingDataBean getHoldingData(Connection conn, int holdingID) throws Exception {\n  1131→    HoldingDataBean holdingData = null;\n  1132→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getHoldingSQL);\n  1133→    stmt.setInt(1, holdingID);\n  1134→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1135→    if (!rs.next()) {\n  1136→      // already sold\n  1137→      Log.debug(\"TradeDirect:getHoldingData -- no results -- holdingID=\" + holdingID);\n  1138→    } else {\n  1139→      holdingData = getHoldingDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1140→    }\n  1141→\n  1142→    stmt.close();\n  1143→    return holdingData;\n  1144→  }\n  1145→  \n  1146→  private OrderDataBean getOrderData(Connection conn, int orderID) throws Exception {\n  1147→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n  1148→    \n  1149→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getOrderData(conn, \" + orderID + \")\");\n  1150→   \n  1151→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getOrderSQL);\n  1152→    stmt.setInt(1, orderID);\n  1153→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1154→    if (!rs.next()) {\n  1155→      // already sold\n  1156→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getOrderData -- no results for orderID:\" + orderID);\n  1157→    } else {\n  1158→      orderData = getOrderDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1159→    }\n  1160→    stmt.close();\n  1161→    return orderData;\n  1162→  }\n  1163→\n  1164→  /**\n  1165→   * @see TradeServices#getAccountProfileData(String)\n  1166→   */\n  1167→  @Override\n  1168→  public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception {\n  1169→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = null;\n  1170→    Connection conn = null;\n  1171→\n  1172→    try {\n  1173→     \n  1174→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getAccountProfileData - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n  1175→      \n  1176→\n  1177→      conn = getConn();\n  1178→      accountProfileData = getAccountProfileData(conn, userID);\n  1179→      commit(conn);\n  1180→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1181→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountProfileData -- error getting profile data\", e);\n  1182→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1183→    } finally {\n  1184→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1185→    }\n  1186→    return accountProfileData;\n  1187→  }\n  1188→\n  1189→  private AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(Connection conn, String userID) throws Exception {\n  1190→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountProfileSQL);\n  1191→    stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1192→\n  1193→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1194→\n  1195→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = getAccountProfileDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1196→    stmt.close();\n  1197→    return accountProfileData;\n  1198→  }\n  1199→  \n  1200→  private AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(Connection conn, Integer accountID) throws Exception {\n  1201→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountProfileForAccountSQL);\n  1202→    stmt.setInt(1, accountID.intValue());\n  1203→\n  1204→    ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1205→\n  1206→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = getAccountProfileDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1207→    stmt.close();\n  1208→    return accountProfileData;\n  1209→  }\n  1210→\n  1211→  /**\n  1212→   * @see TradeServices#updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean)\n  1213→   */\n  1214→  @Override\n  1215→  public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n  1216→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = null;\n  1217→    Connection conn = null;\n  1218→\n  1219→    try {\n  1220→      \n  1221→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:updateAccountProfileData - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", profileData.getUserID());\n  1222→\n  1223→      conn = getConn();\n  1224→      updateAccountProfile(conn, profileData);\n  1225→\n  1226→      accountProfileData = getAccountProfileData(conn, profileData.getUserID());\n  1227→      commit(conn);\n  1228→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1229→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountProfileData -- error getting profile data\", e);\n  1230→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1231→    } finally {\n  1232→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1233→    }\n  1234→    return accountProfileData;\n  1235→  }\n  1236→\n  1237→  private void creditAccountBalance(Connection conn, AccountDataBean accountData, BigDecimal credit) throws Exception {\n  1238→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, creditAccountBalanceSQL);\n  1239→\n  1240→    stmt.setBigDecimal(1, credit);\n  1241→    stmt.setInt(2, accountData.getAccountID().intValue());\n  1242→\n  1243→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1244→    stmt.close();\n  1245→\n  1246→  }\n  1247→\n  1248→  // Set Timestamp to zero to denote sell is inflight\n  1249→  // UPDATE -- could add a \"status\" attribute to holding\n  1250→  private void updateHoldingStatus(Connection conn, Integer holdingID, String symbol) throws Exception {\n  1251→    Timestamp ts = new Timestamp(0);\n  1252→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, \"update holdingejb set purchasedate= ? where holdingid = ?\");\n  1253→\n  1254→    stmt.setTimestamp(1, ts);\n  1255→    stmt.setInt(2, holdingID.intValue());\n  1256→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1257→    stmt.close();\n  1258→  }\n  1259→\n  1260→  private void updateOrderStatus(Connection conn, Integer orderID, String status) throws Exception {\n  1261→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, updateOrderStatusSQL);\n  1262→\n  1263→    stmt.setString(1, status);\n  1264→    stmt.setTimestamp(2, new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n  1265→    stmt.setInt(3, orderID.intValue());\n  1266→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1267→    stmt.close();\n  1268→  }\n  1269→\n  1270→  private void updateOrderHolding(Connection conn, int orderID, int holdingID) throws Exception {\n  1271→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, updateOrderHoldingSQL);\n  1272→\n  1273→    stmt.setInt(1, holdingID);\n  1274→    stmt.setInt(2, orderID);\n  1275→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1276→    stmt.close();\n  1277→  }\n  1278→\n  1279→  private void updateAccountProfile(Connection conn, AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n  1280→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, updateAccountProfileSQL);\n  1281→\n  1282→    stmt.setString(1, profileData.getPassword());\n  1283→    stmt.setString(2, profileData.getFullName());\n  1284→    stmt.setString(3, profileData.getAddress());\n  1285→    stmt.setString(4, profileData.getEmail());\n  1286→    stmt.setString(5, profileData.getCreditCard());\n  1287→    stmt.setString(6, profileData.getUserID());\n  1288→\n  1289→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1290→    stmt.close();\n  1291→  }\n  1292→\n  1293→  @Override\n  1294→  public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) throws Exception {\n  1295→    return updateQuotePriceVolumeInt(symbol, changeFactor, sharesTraded, TradeConfig.getPublishQuotePriceChange());\n  1296→  }\n  1297→\n  1298→  /**\n  1299→   * Update a quote's price and volume\n  1300→   *\n  1301→   * @param symbol\n  1302→   *            The PK of the quote\n  1303→   * @param changeFactor\n  1304→   *            the percent to change the old price by (between 50% and 150%)\n  1305→   * @param sharedTraded\n  1306→   *            the ammount to add to the current volume\n  1307→   * @param publishQuotePriceChange\n  1308→   *            used by the PingJDBCWrite Primitive to ensure no JMS is used,\n  1309→   *            should be true for all normal calls to this API\n  1310→   */\n  1311→  public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolumeInt(String symbol, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded, boolean publishQuotePriceChange)\n  1312→      throws Exception {\n  1313→\n  1314→    if (TradeConfig.getUpdateQuotePrices() == false) {\n  1315→      return new QuoteDataBean();\n  1316→    }\n  1317→\n  1318→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n  1319→    Connection conn = null;\n  1320→\n  1321→    try {\n  1322→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:updateQuotePriceVolume - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", symbol, changeFactor, new Double(sharesTraded));\n  1323→\n  1324→      conn = getConn();\n  1325→\n  1326→      quoteData = getQuoteForUpdate(conn, symbol);\n  1327→      BigDecimal oldPrice = quoteData.getPrice();\n  1328→      BigDecimal openPrice = quoteData.getOpen();\n  1329→\n  1330→      double newVolume = quoteData.getVolume() + sharesTraded;\n  1331→\n  1332→      if (oldPrice.equals(TradeConfig.PENNY_STOCK_PRICE)) {\n  1333→        changeFactor = TradeConfig.PENNY_STOCK_RECOVERY_MIRACLE_MULTIPLIER;\n  1334→      } else if (oldPrice.compareTo(TradeConfig.MAXIMUM_STOCK_PRICE) > 0) {\n  1335→        changeFactor = TradeConfig.MAXIMUM_STOCK_SPLIT_MULTIPLIER;\n  1336→      }\n  1337→\n  1338→      BigDecimal newPrice = changeFactor.multiply(oldPrice).setScale(2, BigDecimal.ROUND_HALF_UP);\n  1339→      double change = newPrice.subtract(openPrice).doubleValue();\n  1340→\n  1341→      updateQuotePriceVolume(conn, quoteData.getSymbol(), newPrice, newVolume, change);\n  1342→      quoteData = getQuote(conn, symbol);\n  1343→\n  1344→      commit(conn);\n  1345→\n  1346→      if (publishQuotePriceChange) {\n  1347→        publishQuotePriceChange(quoteData, oldPrice, changeFactor, sharesTraded);\n  1348→      }\n  1349→\n  1350→      recentQuotePriceChangeList.add(quoteData);\n  1351→      \n  1352→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1353→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:updateQuotePriceVolume -- error updating quote price/volume for symbol:\" + symbol);\n  1354→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1355→      throw e;\n  1356→    } finally {\n  1357→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1358→    }\n  1359→    return quoteData;\n  1360→  }\n  1361→\n  1362→  private void updateQuotePriceVolume(Connection conn, String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double newVolume, double change) throws Exception {\n  1363→\n  1364→    PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, updateQuotePriceVolumeSQL);\n  1365→\n  1366→    stmt.setBigDecimal(1, newPrice);\n  1367→    stmt.setDouble(2, change);\n  1368→    stmt.setDouble(3, newVolume);\n  1369→    stmt.setString(4, symbol);\n  1370→\n  1371→    stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1372→    stmt.close();\n  1373→  }\n  1374→\n  1375→  private void publishQuotePriceChange(QuoteDataBean quoteData, BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) throws Exception {\n  1376→\n  1377→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:publishQuotePrice PUBLISHING to MDB quoteData = \" + quoteData);       \n  1378→\n  1379→    try (JMSContext context = topicConnectionFactory.createContext();){\n  1380→      TextMessage message = context.createTextMessage();\n  1381→\n  1382→      message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"updateQuote\");\n  1383→      message.setStringProperty(\"symbol\", quoteData.getSymbol());\n  1384→      message.setStringProperty(\"company\", quoteData.getCompanyName());\n  1385→      message.setStringProperty(\"price\", quoteData.getPrice().toString());\n  1386→      message.setStringProperty(\"oldPrice\", oldPrice.toString());\n  1387→      message.setStringProperty(\"open\", quoteData.getOpen().toString());\n  1388→      message.setStringProperty(\"low\", quoteData.getLow().toString());\n  1389→      message.setStringProperty(\"high\", quoteData.getHigh().toString());\n  1390→      message.setDoubleProperty(\"volume\", quoteData.getVolume());\n  1391→\n  1392→      message.setStringProperty(\"changeFactor\", changeFactor.toString());\n  1393→      message.setDoubleProperty(\"sharesTraded\", sharesTraded);\n  1394→      message.setLongProperty(\"publishTime\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n  1395→      message.setText(\"Update Stock price for \" + quoteData.getSymbol() + \" old price = \" + oldPrice + \" new price = \" + quoteData.getPrice());\n  1396→\n  1397→\n  1398→      context.createProducer().send(tradeStreamerTopic, message);\n  1399→\n  1400→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1401→      throw e; // pass exception back\n  1402→\n  1403→    }\n  1404→  }\n  1405→\n  1406→  /**\n  1407→   * @see TradeServices#login(String, String)\n  1408→   */\n  1409→\n  1410→  @Override\n  1411→  public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception {\n  1412→\n  1413→    AccountDataBean accountData = null;\n  1414→    Connection conn = null;\n  1415→    try {\n  1416→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:login - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID, password);\n  1417→\n  1418→      conn = getConn();\n  1419→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountProfileSQL);\n  1420→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1421→\n  1422→      ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1423→      if (!rs.next()) {\n  1424→        Log.error(\"TradeDirect:login -- failure to find account for\" + userID);\n  1425→        throw new javax.ejb.FinderException(\"Cannot find account for\" + userID);\n  1426→      }\n  1427→\n  1428→      String pw = rs.getString(\"passwd\");\n  1429→      stmt.close();\n  1430→      if ((pw == null) || (pw.equals(password) == false)) {\n  1431→        String error = \"TradeDirect:Login failure for user: \" + userID + \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + userID + \":\" + password;\n  1432→        Log.error(error);\n  1433→        throw new Exception(error);\n  1434→      }\n  1435→\n  1436→      stmt = getStatement(conn, loginSQL);\n  1437→      stmt.setTimestamp(1, new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n  1438→      stmt.setString(2, userID);\n  1439→\n  1440→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1441→      stmt.close();\n  1442→\n  1443→      stmt = getStatement(conn, getAccountForUserSQL);\n  1444→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1445→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n  1446→\n  1447→      accountData = getAccountDataFromResultSet(rs);\n  1448→\n  1449→      stmt.close();\n  1450→\n  1451→      commit(conn);\n  1452→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1453→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:login -- error logging in user\", e);\n  1454→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1455→    } finally {\n  1456→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1457→    }\n  1458→    return accountData;\n  1459→\n  1460→    /*\n  1461→     * setLastLogin( new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()) );\n  1462→     * setLoginCount( getLoginCount() + 1 );\n  1463→     */\n  1464→  }\n  1465→\n  1466→  /**\n  1467→   * @see TradeServices#logout(String)\n  1468→   */\n  1469→  @Override\n  1470→  public void logout(String userID) throws Exception {\n  1471→    Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:logout - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\", userID);\n  1472→    \n  1473→    Connection conn = null;\n  1474→    try {\n  1475→      conn = getConn();\n  1476→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, logoutSQL);\n  1477→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1478→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1479→      stmt.close();\n  1480→\n  1481→      commit(conn);\n  1482→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1483→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:logout -- error logging out user\", e);\n  1484→      rollBack(conn, e);\n  1485→    } finally {\n  1486→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1487→    }\n  1488→  }\n  1489→\n  1490→  /**\n  1491→   * @see TradeServices#register(String, String, String, String, String,\n  1492→   *      String, BigDecimal, boolean)\n  1493→   */\n  1494→\n  1495→  @Override\n  1496→  public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n  1497→      throws Exception {\n  1498→\n  1499→    AccountDataBean accountData = null;\n  1500→    Connection conn = null;\n  1501→    try {\n  1502→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:register - inSession(\" + this.inSession + \")\");  \n  1503→\n  1504→      conn = getConn();\n  1505→      PreparedStatement stmt = getStatement(conn, createAccountSQL);\n  1506→\n  1507→      Integer accountID = KeySequenceDirect.getNextID(conn, \"account\", inSession, getInGlobalTxn());\n  1508→      BigDecimal balance = openBalance;\n  1509→      Timestamp creationDate = new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis());\n  1510→      Timestamp lastLogin = creationDate;\n  1511→      int loginCount = 0;\n  1512→      int logoutCount = 0;\n  1513→\n  1514→      stmt.setInt(1, accountID.intValue());\n  1515→      stmt.setTimestamp(2, creationDate);\n  1516→      stmt.setBigDecimal(3, openBalance);\n  1517→      stmt.setBigDecimal(4, balance);\n  1518→      stmt.setTimestamp(5, lastLogin);\n  1519→      stmt.setInt(6, loginCount);\n  1520→      stmt.setInt(7, logoutCount);\n  1521→      stmt.setString(8, userID);\n  1522→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1523→      stmt.close();\n  1524→\n  1525→      stmt = getStatement(conn, createAccountProfileSQL);\n  1526→      stmt.setString(1, userID);\n  1527→      stmt.setString(2, password);\n  1528→      stmt.setString(3, fullname);\n  1529→      stmt.setString(4, address);\n  1530→      stmt.setString(5, email);\n  1531→      stmt.setString(6, creditcard);\n  1532→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n  1533→      stmt.close();\n  1534→\n  1535→      commit(conn);\n  1536→\n  1537→      accountData = new AccountDataBean(accountID, loginCount, logoutCount, lastLogin, creationDate, balance, openBalance, userID);\n  1538→\n  1539→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1540→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:register -- error registering new user\", e);\n  1541→    } finally {\n  1542→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1543→    }\n  1544→    return accountData;\n  1545→  }\n  1546→\n  1547→  private AccountDataBean getAccountDataFromResultSet(ResultSet rs) throws Exception {\n  1548→    AccountDataBean accountData = null;\n  1549→\n  1550→    if (!rs.next()) {\n  1551→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountDataFromResultSet -- cannot find account data\");\n  1552→    } else {\n  1553→      accountData = new AccountDataBean(new Integer(rs.getInt(\"accountID\")), rs.getInt(\"loginCount\"), rs.getInt(\"logoutCount\"),\n  1554→          rs.getTimestamp(\"lastLogin\"), rs.getTimestamp(\"creationDate\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"balance\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"openBalance\"),\n  1555→          rs.getString(\"profile_userID\"));\n  1556→    }\n  1557→    return accountData;\n  1558→  }\n  1559→\n  1560→  private AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileDataFromResultSet(ResultSet rs) throws Exception {\n  1561→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = null;\n  1562→\n  1563→    if (!rs.next()) {\n  1564→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:getAccountProfileDataFromResultSet -- cannot find accountprofile data\");\n  1565→    } else {\n  1566→      accountProfileData = new AccountProfileDataBean(rs.getString(\"userID\"), rs.getString(\"passwd\"), rs.getString(\"fullName\"), rs.getString(\"address\"),\n  1567→          rs.getString(\"email\"), rs.getString(\"creditCard\"));\n  1568→    }\n  1569→\n  1570→    return accountProfileData;\n  1571→  }\n  1572→\n  1573→  private HoldingDataBean getHoldingDataFromResultSet(ResultSet rs) throws Exception {\n  1574→    HoldingDataBean holdingData = null;\n  1575→\n  1576→    holdingData = new HoldingDataBean(new Integer(rs.getInt(\"holdingID\")), rs.getDouble(\"quantity\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"purchasePrice\"),\n  1577→        rs.getTimestamp(\"purchaseDate\"), rs.getString(\"quote_symbol\"));\n  1578→    return holdingData;\n  1579→  }\n  1580→\n  1581→  private QuoteDataBean getQuoteDataFromResultSet(ResultSet rs) throws Exception {\n  1582→    QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n  1583→\n  1584→    quoteData = new QuoteDataBean(rs.getString(\"symbol\"), rs.getString(\"companyName\"), rs.getDouble(\"volume\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"price\"),\n  1585→        rs.getBigDecimal(\"open1\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"low\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"high\"), rs.getDouble(\"change1\"));\n  1586→    return quoteData;\n  1587→  }\n  1588→\n  1589→  private OrderDataBean getOrderDataFromResultSet(ResultSet rs) throws Exception {\n  1590→    OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n  1591→\n  1592→    orderData = new OrderDataBean(new Integer(rs.getInt(\"orderID\")), rs.getString(\"orderType\"), rs.getString(\"orderStatus\"), rs.getTimestamp(\"openDate\"),\n  1593→        rs.getTimestamp(\"completionDate\"), rs.getDouble(\"quantity\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"price\"), rs.getBigDecimal(\"orderFee\"),\n  1594→        rs.getString(\"quote_symbol\"));\n  1595→    return orderData;\n  1596→  }\n  1597→\n  1598→  public boolean recreateDBTables(Object[] sqlBuffer, java.io.PrintWriter out) throws Exception {\n  1599→    // Clear MDB Statistics\n  1600→    MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n  1601→\n  1602→    Connection conn = null;\n  1603→    boolean success = false;\n  1604→    try {\n  1605→     \n  1606→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:recreateDBTables\");\n  1607→\n  1608→      conn = getConn();\n  1609→      Statement stmt = conn.createStatement();\n  1610→      int bufferLength = sqlBuffer.length;\n  1611→      for (int i = 0; i < bufferLength; i++) {\n  1612→        try {\n  1613→          stmt.executeUpdate((String) sqlBuffer[i]);\n  1614→          // commit(conn);\n  1615→        } catch (SQLException ex) {\n  1616→          // Ignore DROP statements as tables won't always exist.\n  1617→          if (((String) sqlBuffer[i]).indexOf(\"DROP \") < 0) {\n  1618→            Log.error(\"TradeDirect:recreateDBTables SQL Exception thrown on executing the foll sql command: \" + sqlBuffer[i], ex);\n  1619→            out.println(\"<BR>SQL Exception thrown on executing the foll sql command: <I>\" + sqlBuffer[i] + \"</I> . Check log for details.</BR>\");\n  1620→          }\n  1621→        }\n  1622→      }\n  1623→      stmt.close();\n  1624→      commit(conn);\n  1625→      success = true;\n  1626→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1627→      Log.error(e, \"TradeDirect:recreateDBTables() -- Error dropping and recreating the database tables\");\n  1628→    } finally {\n  1629→      releaseConn(conn);\n  1630→    }\n  1631→    return success;\n  1632→  }\n  1633→\n  1634→  ;\n  1635→\n  1636→\n  1637→\n  1638→  private void releaseConn(Connection conn) throws Exception {\n  1639→    try {\n  1640→      if (conn != null) {\n  1641→        conn.close();\n  1642→        if (Log.doTrace()) {\n  1643→          synchronized (lock) {\n  1644→            connCount--;\n  1645→          }\n  1646→          Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:releaseConn -- connection closed, connCount=\" + connCount);\n  1647→        }\n  1648→      }\n  1649→    } catch (Exception e) {\n  1650→      Log.error(\"TradeDirect:releaseConnection -- failed to close connection\", e);\n  1651→    }\n  1652→  }\n  1653→\n  1654→\n  1655→  /*\n  1656→   * Allocate a new connection to the datasource\n  1657→   */\n  1658→  private static int connCount = 0;\n  1659→\n  1660→  private static Integer lock = new Integer(0);\n  1661→\n  1662→  private Connection getConn() throws Exception {\n  1663→\n  1664→    Connection conn = datasource.getConnection();      \n  1665→\n  1666→    if (!this.inGlobalTxn) {\n  1667→      conn.setAutoCommit(false);\n  1668→    }\n  1669→    if (Log.doTrace()) {\n  1670→      synchronized (lock) {\n  1671→        connCount++;\n  1672→      }\n  1673→      Log.trace(\"TradeDirect:getConn -- new connection allocated, IsolationLevel=\" + conn.getTransactionIsolation() + \" connectionCount = \" + connCount);\n  1674→    }\n  1675→\n  1676→    return conn;\n  1677→  }\n  1678→\n  1679→  public Connection getConnPublic() throws Exception {\n  1680→    return getConn();\n  1681→  }\n  1682→\n  1683→  /*\n  1684→   * Commit the provided connection if not under Global Transaction scope -\n  1685→   * conn.commit() is not allowed in a global transaction. the txn manager\n  1686→   * will perform the commit\n  1687→   */\n  1688→  private void commit(Connection conn) throws Exception {\n  1689→    if (!inSession) {\n  1690→      if ((getInGlobalTxn() == false) && (conn != null)) {\n  1691→        conn.commit();\n  1692→      }\n  1693→    }\n  1694→  }\n  1695→\n  1696→  /*\n  1697→   * Rollback the statement for the given connection\n  1698→   */\n  1699→  private void rollBack(Connection conn, Exception e) throws Exception {\n  1700→    if (!inSession) {\n  1701→      Log.log(\"TradeDirect:rollBack -- rolling back conn due to previously caught exception -- inGlobalTxn=\" + getInGlobalTxn());\n  1702→      if ((getInGlobalTxn() == false) && (conn != null)) {\n  1703→        conn.rollback();\n  1704→      } else {\n  1705→        throw e; // Throw the exception\n  1706→        // so the Global txn manager will rollBack\n  1707→      }\n  1708→    }\n  1709→  }\n  1710→\n  1711→  /*\n  1712→   * Allocate a new prepared statment for this connection\n  1713→   */\n  1714→  private PreparedStatement getStatement(Connection conn, String sql) throws Exception {\n  1715→    return conn.prepareStatement(sql);\n  1716→  }\n  1717→\n  1718→  private PreparedStatement getStatement(Connection conn, String sql, int type, int concurrency) throws Exception {\n  1719→    return conn.prepareStatement(sql, type, concurrency);\n  1720→  }\n  1721→\n  1722→  private static final String createQuoteSQL = \"insert into quoteejb \" + \"( symbol, companyName, volume, price, open1, low, high, change1 ) \"\n  1723→      + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  )\";\n  1724→\n  1725→  private static final String createAccountSQL = \"insert into accountejb \"\n  1726→      + \"( accountid, creationDate, openBalance, balance, lastLogin, loginCount, logoutCount, profile_userid) \"\n  1727→      + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  )\";\n  1728→\n  1729→  private static final String createAccountProfileSQL = \"insert into accountprofileejb \" + \"( userid, passwd, fullname, address, email, creditcard ) \"\n  1730→      + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  )\";\n  1731→\n  1732→  private static final String createHoldingSQL = \"insert into holdingejb \"\n  1733→      + \"( holdingid, purchaseDate, purchasePrice, quantity, quote_symbol, account_accountid ) \" + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ? )\";\n  1734→\n  1735→  private static final String createOrderSQL = \"insert into orderejb \"\n  1736→      + \"( orderid, ordertype, orderstatus, opendate, quantity, price, orderfee, account_accountid,  holding_holdingid, quote_symbol) \"\n  1737→      + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  ,  ?  , ? , ? , ?)\";\n  1738→\n  1739→  private static final String removeHoldingSQL = \"delete from holdingejb where holdingid = ?\";\n  1740→\n  1741→  private static final String removeHoldingFromOrderSQL = \"update orderejb set holding_holdingid=null where holding_holdingid = ?\";\n  1742→\n  1743→  private static final String updateAccountProfileSQL = \"update accountprofileejb set \" + \"passwd = ?, fullname = ?, address = ?, email = ?, creditcard = ? \"\n  1744→      + \"where userid = (select profile_userid from accountejb a \" + \"where a.profile_userid=?)\";\n  1745→\n  1746→  private static final String loginSQL = \"update accountejb set lastLogin=?, logincount=logincount+1 \" + \"where profile_userid=?\";\n  1747→\n  1748→  private static final String logoutSQL = \"update accountejb set logoutcount=logoutcount+1 \" + \"where profile_userid=?\";\n  1749→\n  1750→  private static final String getAccountSQL = \"select * from accountejb a where a.accountid = ?\";\n  1751→\n  1752→  private static final String getAccountProfileSQL = \"select * from accountprofileejb ap where ap.userid = \"\n  1753→      + \"(select profile_userid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid=?)\";\n  1754→\n  1755→  private static final String getAccountProfileForAccountSQL = \"select * from accountprofileejb ap where ap.userid = \"\n  1756→      + \"(select profile_userid from accountejb a where a.accountid=?)\";\n  1757→\n  1758→  private static final String getAccountForUserSQL = \"select * from accountejb a where a.profile_userid = \"\n  1759→      + \"( select userid from accountprofileejb ap where ap.userid = ?)\";\n  1760→\n  1761→  private static final String getHoldingSQL = \"select * from holdingejb h where h.holdingid = ?\";\n  1762→\n  1763→  private static final String getHoldingsForUserSQL = \"select * from holdingejb h where h.account_accountid = \"\n  1764→      + \"(select a.accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid = ?)\";\n  1765→\n  1766→  private static final String getOrderSQL = \"select * from orderejb o where o.orderid = ?\";\n  1767→\n  1768→  private static final String getOrdersByUserSQL = \"select * from orderejb o where o.account_accountid = \"\n  1769→      + \"(select a.accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid = ?)\";\n  1770→\n  1771→  private static final String getClosedOrdersSQL = \"select * from orderejb o \" + \"where o.orderstatus = 'closed' AND o.account_accountid = \"\n  1772→      + \"(select a.accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid = ?)\";\n  1773→\n  1774→  private static final String getQuoteSQL = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=?\";\n  1775→\n  1776→  private static final String getAllQuotesSQL = \"select * from quoteejb q\";\n  1777→\n  1778→  private static final String getQuoteForUpdateSQL = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=? For Update\";\n  1779→\n  1780→  private static final String getTSIAQuotesOrderByChangeSQL = \"select * from quoteejb q order by q.change1\";\n  1781→\n  1782→  private static final String getTSIASQL = \"select SUM(price)/count(*) as TSIA from quoteejb q \";\n  1783→\n  1784→  private static final String getOpenTSIASQL = \"select SUM(open1)/count(*) as openTSIA from quoteejb q \";\n  1785→\n  1786→  private static final String getTSIATotalVolumeSQL = \"select SUM(volume) as totalVolume from quoteejb q \";\n  1787→\n  1788→  private static final String creditAccountBalanceSQL = \"update accountejb set \" + \"balance = balance + ? \" + \"where accountid = ?\";\n  1789→\n  1790→  private static final String updateOrderStatusSQL = \"update orderejb set \" + \"orderstatus = ?, completiondate = ? \" + \"where orderid = ?\";\n  1791→\n  1792→  private static final String updateOrderHoldingSQL = \"update orderejb set \" + \"holding_holdingID = ? \" + \"where orderid = ?\";\n  1793→\n  1794→  private static final String updateQuotePriceVolumeSQL = \"update quoteejb set \" + \"price = ?, change1 = ?, volume = ? \" + \"where symbol = ?\";\n  1795→\n  1796→  /**\n  1797→   * Gets the inGlobalTxn\n  1798→   *\n  1799→   * @return Returns a boolean\n  1800→   */\n  1801→  private boolean getInGlobalTxn() {\n  1802→    return inGlobalTxn;\n  1803→  }\n  1804→\n  1805→  /**\n  1806→   * Sets the inGlobalTxn\n  1807→   *\n  1808→   * @param inGlobalTxn\n  1809→   *            The inGlobalTxn to set\n  1810→   */\n  1811→  private void setInGlobalTxn(boolean inGlobalTxn) {\n  1812→    this.inGlobalTxn = inGlobalTxn;\n  1813→  }\n  1814→  \n  1815→  public void setInSession(boolean inSession) {\n  1816→    this.inSession = inSession;\n  1817→  }\n  1818→\n  1819→  @Override\n  1820→  public int getImpl() {\n  1821→    return TradeConfig.DIRECT;\n  1822→  }\n  1823→\n  1824→\n  1825→\n  1826→  @Override\n  1827→  public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) {\n  1828→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n  1829→  }\n  1830→\n  1831→\n  1832→\n  1833→  @Override\n  1834→  public double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) {\n  1835→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n  1836→  }   \n  1837→}\n  1838→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"d204ca3c-55bc-4582-9806-651393395aed"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XUsqMeQaZNv6czLFTVpW6p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.io.Serializable;\n    20→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    21→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    22→import java.util.Collection;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n    26→import javax.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    27→import javax.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    28→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    29→import javax.servlet.ServletContext;\n    30→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    31→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    32→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    33→import javax.servlet.http.HttpSession;\n    34→\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    45→\n    46→\n    47→/**\n    48→ * TradeServletAction provides servlet specific client side access to each of\n    49→ * the Trade brokerage user operations. These include login, logout, buy, sell,\n    50→ * getQuote, etc. TradeServletAction manages a web interface to Trade handling\n    51→ * HttpRequests/HttpResponse objects and forwarding results to the appropriate\n    52→ * JSP page for the web interface. TradeServletAction invokes\n    53→ * {@link TradeAction} methods to actually perform each trading operation.\n    54→ *\n    55→ */\n    56→@SessionScoped\n    57→@Trace\n    58→public class TradeServletAction implements Serializable {\n    59→\n    60→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 7732313125198761455L;\n    61→\n    62→  private TradeServices tAction;  \n    63→\n    64→  @Inject \n    65→  public TradeServletAction(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    66→    tAction = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public TradeServletAction() {\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  /**\n    73→   * Display User Profile information such as address, email, etc. for the\n    74→   * given Trader Dispatch to the Trade Account JSP for display\n    75→   *\n    76→   * @param userID\n    77→   *            The User to display profile info\n    78→   * @param ctx\n    79→   *            the servlet context\n    80→   * @param req\n    81→   *            the HttpRequest object\n    82→   * @param resp\n    83→   *            the HttpResponse object\n    84→   * @param results\n    85→   *            A short description of the results/success of this web request\n    86→   *            provided on the web page\n    87→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n    88→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n    89→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n    90→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n    91→   *                user\n    92→   *\n    93→   */\n    94→  void doAccount(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String results) throws javax.servlet.ServletException,\n    95→  java.io.IOException {\n    96→    try {\n    97→\n    98→      AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.getAccountData(userID);\n    99→      AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = tAction.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   100→      Collection<?> orderDataBeans = (TradeConfig.getLongRun() ? new ArrayList<Object>() : (Collection<?>) tAction.getOrders(userID));\n   101→\n   102→      req.setAttribute(\"accountData\", accountData);\n   103→      req.setAttribute(\"accountProfileData\", accountProfileData);\n   104→      req.setAttribute(\"orderDataBeans\", orderDataBeans);\n   105→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   106→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ACCOUNT_PAGE));\n   107→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   108→      // error so I will\n   109→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   110→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"could not find account for userID = \" + userID);\n   111→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   112→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   113→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   114→      Log.error(\"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\", e);\n   115→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   116→      // log the exception with error page\n   117→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  /**\n   123→   * Update User Profile information such as address, email, etc. for the\n   124→   * given Trader Dispatch to the Trade Account JSP for display If any in put\n   125→   * is incorrect revert back to the account page w/ an appropriate message\n   126→   *\n   127→   * @param userID\n   128→   *            The User to upddate profile info\n   129→   * @param password\n   130→   *            The new User password\n   131→   * @param cpassword\n   132→   *            Confirm password\n   133→   * @param fullname\n   134→   *            The new User fullname info\n   135→   * @param address\n   136→   *            The new User address info\n   137→   * @param cc\n   138→   *            The new User credit card info\n   139→   * @param email\n   140→   *            The new User email info\n   141→   * @param ctx\n   142→   *            the servlet context\n   143→   * @param req\n   144→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   145→   * @param resp\n   146→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   147→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   148→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   149→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   150→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   151→   *                user\n   152→   *\n   153→   */\n   154→  void doAccountUpdate(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String password, String cpassword,\n   155→      String fullName, String address, String creditcard, String email) throws javax.servlet.ServletException, java.io.IOException {\n   156→    String results = \"\";\n   157→\n   158→    // First verify input data\n   159→    boolean doUpdate = true;\n   160→    if (password.equals(cpassword) == false) {\n   161→      results = \"Update profile error: passwords do not match\";\n   162→      doUpdate = false;\n   163→    } else if (password.length() <= 0 || fullName.length() <= 0 || address.length() <= 0 || creditcard.length() <= 0 || email.length() <= 0) {\n   164→      results = \"Update profile error: please fill in all profile information fields\";\n   165→      doUpdate = false;\n   166→    }\n   167→    AccountProfileDataBean accountProfileData = new AccountProfileDataBean(userID, password, fullName, address, email, creditcard);\n   168→    try {\n   169→      if (doUpdate) {\n   170→        accountProfileData = tAction.updateAccountProfile(accountProfileData);\n   171→        results = \"Account profile update successful\";\n   172→      }\n   173→\n   174→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   175→      // error so I will\n   176→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   177→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"invalid argument, check userID is correct, and the database is populated\" + userID);\n   178→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doAccount(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   179→          \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   180→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   181→      // log the exception with error page\n   182→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doAccountUpdate(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   183→    }\n   184→    doAccount(ctx, req, resp, userID, results);\n   185→  }\n   186→\n   187→  /**\n   188→   * Buy a new holding of shares for the given trader Dispatch to the Trade\n   189→   * Portfolio JSP for display\n   190→   *\n   191→   * @param userID\n   192→   *            The User buying shares\n   193→   * @param symbol\n   194→   *            The stock to purchase\n   195→   * @param amount\n   196→   *            The quantity of shares to purchase\n   197→   * @param ctx\n   198→   *            the servlet context\n   199→   * @param req\n   200→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   201→   * @param resp\n   202→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   203→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   204→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   205→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   206→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   207→   *                user\n   208→   *\n   209→   */\n   210→  void doBuy(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String symbol, String quantity) throws ServletException,\n   211→  IOException {\n   212→\n   213→    String results = \"\";\n   214→\n   215→    try {\n   216→\n   217→      OrderDataBean orderData = tAction.buy(userID, symbol, new Double(quantity).doubleValue(), TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   218→\n   219→      req.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   220→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   221→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   222→      // error so I will\n   223→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   224→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"illegal argument:\");\n   225→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   226→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   227→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   228→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doBuy(...)\", \"illegal argument. userID = \" + userID, \"symbol = \" + symbol);\n   229→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   230→      // log the exception with error page\n   231→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.buy(...)\" + \" exception buying stock \" + symbol + \" for user \" + userID, e);\n   232→    }\n   233→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ORDER_PAGE));\n   234→  }\n   235→\n   236→  /**\n   237→   * Create the Trade Home page with personalized information such as the\n   238→   * traders account balance Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   239→   *\n   240→   * @param ctx\n   241→   *            the servlet context\n   242→   * @param req\n   243→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   244→   * @param resp\n   245→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   246→   * @param results\n   247→   *            A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   248→   *            provided on the web page\n   249→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   250→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   251→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   252→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   253→   *                user\n   254→   *\n   255→   */\n   256→  void doHome(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String results) throws javax.servlet.ServletException,\n   257→  java.io.IOException {\n   258→\n   259→    try {\n   260→      AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.getAccountData(userID);\n   261→      Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = tAction.getHoldings(userID);\n   262→\n   263→      // Edge Caching:\n   264→      // Getting the MarketSummary has been moved to the JSP\n   265→      // MarketSummary.jsp. This makes the MarketSummary a\n   266→      // standalone \"fragment\", and thus is a candidate for\n   267→      // Edge caching.\n   268→      // marketSummaryData = tAction.getMarketSummary();\n   269→\n   270→      req.setAttribute(\"accountData\", accountData);\n   271→      req.setAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\", holdingDataBeans);\n   272→      // See Edge Caching above\n   273→      // req.setAttribute(\"marketSummaryData\", marketSummaryData);\n   274→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   275→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   276→      // error so I will\n   277→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   278→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"check userID = \" + userID + \" and that the database is populated\");\n   279→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   280→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   281→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   282→      Log.error(\"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" + \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\"\n   283→          + \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\", e);\n   284→    } catch (javax.ejb.FinderException e) {\n   285→      // this is a user error so I will\n   286→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   287→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"\\nCould not find account for + \" + userID);\n   288→      // requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp,\n   289→      // TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   290→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   291→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   292→      Log.error(\"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" + \"Error finding account for user \" + userID\n   293→          + \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\", e);\n   294→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   295→      // log the exception with error page\n   296→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doHome(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   297→    }\n   298→\n   299→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.HOME_PAGE));\n   300→  }\n   301→\n   302→  /**\n   303→   * Login a Trade User. Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   304→   *\n   305→   * @param userID\n   306→   *            The User to login\n   307→   * @param passwd\n   308→   *            The password supplied by the trader used to authenticate\n   309→   * @param ctx\n   310→   *            the servlet context\n   311→   * @param req\n   312→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   313→   * @param resp\n   314→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   315→   * @param results\n   316→   *            A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   317→   *            provided on the web page\n   318→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   319→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   320→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   321→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   322→   *                user\n   323→   *\n   324→   */\n   325→  void doLogin(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String passwd) throws javax.servlet.ServletException,\n   326→  java.io.IOException {\n   327→\n   328→    String results = \"\";\n   329→    try {\n   330→      // Got a valid userID and passwd, attempt login\n   331→      if (tAction==null) {\n   332→        System.out.println(\"null\");          }\n   333→      AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.login(userID, passwd);\n   334→\n   335→      if (accountData != null) {\n   336→        HttpSession session = req.getSession(true);\n   337→        session.setAttribute(\"uidBean\", userID);\n   338→        session.setAttribute(\"sessionCreationDate\", new java.util.Date());\n   339→\n   340→        results = \"Ready to Trade\";\n   341→        doHome(ctx, req, resp, userID, results);\n   342→        return;\n   343→      } else {\n   344→        req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"\\nCould not find account for + \" + userID);\n   345→        // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means,\n   346→        // handled exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   347→        Log.log(\"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\", \"Error finding account for user \" + userID + \"\",\n   348→            \"user entered a bad username or the database is not populated\");\n   349→      }\n   350→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   351→      // error so I will\n   352→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   353→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   354→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   355→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   356→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   357→          \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   358→\n   359→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   360→      // log the exception with error page\n   361→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doLogin(...)\" + \"Exception logging in user \" + userID + \"with password\" + passwd, e);\n   362→    }\n   363→\n   364→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   365→\n   366→  }\n   367→\n   368→  /**\n   369→   * Logout a Trade User Dispatch to the Trade Welcome JSP for display\n   370→   *\n   371→   * @param userID\n   372→   *            The User to logout\n   373→   * @param ctx\n   374→   *            the servlet context\n   375→   * @param req\n   376→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   377→   * @param resp\n   378→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   379→   * @param results\n   380→   *            A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   381→   *            provided on the web page\n   382→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   383→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   384→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   385→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   386→   *                user\n   387→   *\n   388→   */\n   389→  void doLogout(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   390→    String results = \"\";\n   391→\n   392→    try {\n   393→      tAction.logout(userID);\n   394→\n   395→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   396→      // error so I will\n   397→      // forward them to another page, at the end of the page.\n   398→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   399→\n   400→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   401→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   402→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\",\n   403→          \"treating this as a user error and forwarding on to a new page\");\n   404→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   405→      // log the exception and foward to a error page\n   406→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...):\", \"Error logging out\" + userID, \"fowarding to an error page\");\n   407→      // set the status_code to 500\n   408→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doLogout(...)\" + \"exception logging out user \" + userID, e);\n   409→    }\n   410→    HttpSession session = req.getSession();\n   411→    if (session != null) {\n   412→      session.invalidate();\n   413→    }\n   414→\n   415→    // Added to actually remove a user from the authentication cache\n   416→    req.logout();\n   417→\n   418→    Object o = req.getAttribute(\"TSS-RecreateSessionInLogout\");\n   419→    if (o != null && ((Boolean) o).equals(Boolean.TRUE)) {\n   420→      // Recreate Session object before writing output to the response\n   421→      // Once the response headers are written back to the client the\n   422→      // opportunity\n   423→      // to create a new session in this request may be lost\n   424→      // This is to handle only the TradeScenarioServlet case\n   425→      session = req.getSession(true);\n   426→    }\n   427→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   428→  }\n   429→\n   430→  /**\n   431→   * Retrieve the current portfolio of stock holdings for the given trader\n   432→   * Dispatch to the Trade Portfolio JSP for display\n   433→   *\n   434→   * @param userID\n   435→   *            The User requesting to view their portfolio\n   436→   * @param ctx\n   437→   *            the servlet context\n   438→   * @param req\n   439→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   440→   * @param resp\n   441→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   442→   * @param results\n   443→   *            A short description of the results/success of this web request\n   444→   *            provided on the web page\n   445→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   446→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   447→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   448→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   449→   *                user\n   450→   *\n   451→   */\n   452→  void doPortfolio(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String results) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   453→\n   454→    try {\n   455→      // Get the holdiings for this user\n   456→\n   457→      Collection<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n   458→      Collection<?> holdingDataBeans = tAction.getHoldings(userID);\n   459→\n   460→      // Walk through the collection of user\n   461→      // holdings and creating a list of quotes\n   462→      if (holdingDataBeans.size() > 0) {\n   463→\n   464→        Iterator<?> it = holdingDataBeans.iterator();\n   465→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   466→          HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) it.next();\n   467→          QuoteDataBean quoteData = tAction.getQuote(holdingData.getQuoteID());\n   468→          quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n   469→        }\n   470→      } else {\n   471→        results = results + \".  Your portfolio is empty.\";\n   472→      }\n   473→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   474→      req.setAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\", holdingDataBeans);\n   475→      req.setAttribute(\"quoteDataBeans\", quoteDataBeans);\n   476→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.PORTFOLIO_PAGE));\n   477→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   478→      // error so I will\n   479→      // forward them to another page rather than throw a 500\n   480→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results + \"illegal argument:\" + e.getMessage());\n   481→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.PORTFOLIO_PAGE));\n   482→      // log the exception with an error level of 3 which means, handled\n   483→      // exception but would invalidate a automation run\n   484→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doPortfolio(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\", \"user error\");\n   485→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   486→      // log the exception with error page\n   487→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doPortfolio(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   488→    }\n   489→  }\n   490→\n   491→  /**\n   492→   * Retrieve the current Quote for the given stock symbol Dispatch to the\n   493→   * Trade Quote JSP for display\n   494→   *\n   495→   * @param userID\n   496→   *            The stock symbol used to get the current quote\n   497→   * @param ctx\n   498→   *            the servlet context\n   499→   * @param req\n   500→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   501→   * @param resp\n   502→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   503→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   504→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   505→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   506→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   507→   *                user\n   508→   *\n   509→   */\n   510→  void doQuotes(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String symbols) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   511→\n   512→    try {\n   513→      Collection<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n   514→      String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n   515→      for (String symbol: symbolsSplit) {\n   516→        QuoteDataBean quoteData = tAction.getQuote(symbol.trim());\n   517→        quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n   518→      } \n   519→      req.setAttribute(\"quoteDataBeans\", quoteDataBeans);\n   520→      requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.QUOTE_PAGE));\n   521→\n   522→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   523→      // log the exception with error page\n   524→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doQuotes(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   525→    } \n   526→  }\n   527→\n   528→  /**\n   529→   * Register a new trader given the provided user Profile information such as\n   530→   * address, email, etc. Dispatch to the Trade Home JSP for display\n   531→   *\n   532→   * @param userID\n   533→   *            The User to create\n   534→   * @param passwd\n   535→   *            The User password\n   536→   * @param fullname\n   537→   *            The new User fullname info\n   538→   * @param ccn\n   539→   *            The new User credit card info\n   540→   * @param money\n   541→   *            The new User opening account balance\n   542→   * @param address\n   543→   *            The new User address info\n   544→   * @param email\n   545→   *            The new User email info\n   546→   * @return The userID of the new trader\n   547→   * @param ctx\n   548→   *            the servlet context\n   549→   * @param req\n   550→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   551→   * @param resp\n   552→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   553→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   554→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   555→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   556→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   557→   *                user\n   558→   *\n   559→   */\n   560→  void doRegister(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String passwd, String cpasswd, String fullname,\n   561→      String ccn, String openBalanceString, String email, String address) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   562→    String results = \"\";\n   563→\n   564→    try {\n   565→      // Validate user passwords match and are atleast 1 char in length\n   566→      if ((passwd.equals(cpasswd)) && (passwd.length() >= 1)) {\n   567→\n   568→        AccountDataBean accountData = tAction.register(userID, passwd, fullname, address, email, ccn, new BigDecimal(openBalanceString));\n   569→        if (accountData == null) {\n   570→          results = \"Registration operation failed;\";\n   571→          System.out.println(results);\n   572→          req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   573→          requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.REGISTER_PAGE));\n   574→        } else {\n   575→          doLogin(ctx, req, resp, userID, passwd);\n   576→          results = \"Registration operation succeeded;  Account \" + accountData.getAccountID() + \" has been created.\";\n   577→          req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   578→\n   579→        }\n   580→      } else {\n   581→        // Password validation failed\n   582→        results = \"Registration operation failed, your passwords did not match\";\n   583→        System.out.println(results);\n   584→        req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   585→        requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.REGISTER_PAGE));\n   586→      }\n   587→\n   588→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   589→      // log the exception with error page\n   590→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doRegister(...)\" + \" exception user =\" + userID, e);\n   591→    }\n   592→  }\n   593→\n   594→  /**\n   595→   * Sell a current holding of stock shares for the given trader. Dispatch to\n   596→   * the Trade Portfolio JSP for display\n   597→   *\n   598→   * @param userID\n   599→   *            The User buying shares\n   600→   * @param symbol\n   601→   *            The stock to sell\n   602→   * @param indx\n   603→   *            The unique index identifying the users holding to sell\n   604→   * @param ctx\n   605→   *            the servlet context\n   606→   * @param req\n   607→   *            the HttpRequest object\n   608→   * @param resp\n   609→   *            the HttpResponse object\n   610→   * @exception javax.servlet.ServletException\n   611→   *                If a servlet specific exception is encountered\n   612→   * @exception javax.io.IOException\n   613→   *                If an exception occurs while writing results back to the\n   614→   *                user\n   615→   *\n   616→   */\n   617→  void doSell(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, Integer holdingID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   618→    String results = \"\";\n   619→    try {\n   620→      OrderDataBean orderData = tAction.sell(userID, holdingID, TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   621→\n   622→      req.setAttribute(\"orderData\", orderData);\n   623→      req.setAttribute(\"results\", results);\n   624→    } catch (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException e) { // this is a user\n   625→      // error so I will\n   626→      // just log the exception and then later on I will redisplay the\n   627→      // portfolio page\n   628→      // because this is just a user exception\n   629→      Log.error(e, \"TradeServletAction.doSell(...)\", \"illegal argument, information should be in exception string\", \"user error\");\n   630→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   631→      // log the exception with error page\n   632→      throw new ServletException(\"TradeServletAction.doSell(...)\" + \" exception selling holding \" + holdingID + \" for user =\" + userID, e);\n   633→    }\n   634→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.ORDER_PAGE));\n   635→  }\n   636→\n   637→  void doWelcome(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String status) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   638→\n   639→    req.setAttribute(\"results\", status);\n   640→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, null, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.WELCOME_PAGE));\n   641→  }\n   642→\n   643→  private void requestDispatch(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID, String page) throws ServletException,\n   644→  IOException {\n   645→\n   646→    ctx.getRequestDispatcher(page).include(req, resp);\n   647→  }\n   648→\n   649→  void doMarketSummary(ServletContext ctx, HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp, String userID) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   650→    req.setAttribute(\"results\", \"test\");\n   651→    requestDispatch(ctx, req, resp, userID, TradeConfig.getPage(TradeConfig.MARKET_SUMMARY_PAGE));\n   652→\n   653→  }\n   654→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_