{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MA2o75q5yBKxtpLRhFahYh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!-- \n     3→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     4→ *\n     5→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     6→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     7→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     8→ *\n     9→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n    10→ *\n    11→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    12→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    13→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    14→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    15→ * limitations under the License.\n    16→-->\n    17→<faces-config xmlns=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee\"\n    18→              xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n    19→              xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-facesconfig_2_3.xsd\"\n    20→              version=\"2.3\">\n    21→     <navigation-rule>\n    22→      <from-view-id>/welcome.xhtml</from-view-id>\n    23→        <navigation-case>\n    24→            <from-outcome>Ready to Trade</from-outcome>\n    25→            <to-view-id>/tradehome.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    26→        </navigation-case>\n    27→        <navigation-case>\n    28→            <from-outcome>welcome</from-outcome>\n    29→            <to-view-id>/welcome.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    30→        </navigation-case>         \n    31→    </navigation-rule> \n    32→    <navigation-rule>\n    33→        <from-view-id>/register.xhtml</from-view-id>\n    34→        <navigation-case>\n    35→            <from-outcome>Registration operation succeeded</from-outcome>\n    36→            <to-view-id>/tradehome.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    37→        </navigation-case>\n    38→        <navigation-case>\n    39→            <from-outcome>Registration operation failed</from-outcome>\n    40→            <to-view-id>/register.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    41→        </navigation-case>        \n    42→    </navigation-rule>  \n    43→    <navigation-rule>\n    44→        <from-view-id>/tradehome.xhtml</from-view-id>\n    45→        <navigation-case>\n    46→            <from-outcome>quotes</from-outcome>\n    47→            <to-view-id>/quote.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    48→        </navigation-case>\n    49→        <navigation-case>\n    50→            <from-outcome>Registration operation failed</from-outcome>\n    51→            <to-view-id>/register.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    52→        </navigation-case>        \n    53→    </navigation-rule>\n    54→     <navigation-rule>\n    55→        <from-view-id>/account.xhtml</from-view-id>        \n    56→       <navigation-case>\n    57→            <from-outcome>quotes</from-outcome>\n    58→            <to-view-id>/quote.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    59→        </navigation-case>  \n    60→       <navigation-case>\n    61→            <from-outcome>Go to account</from-outcome>\n    62→            <to-view-id>/account.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    63→        </navigation-case> \n    64→        <navigation-case>\n    65→            <from-outcome>welcome</from-outcome>\n    66→            <to-view-id>/welcome.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    67→        </navigation-case>                \n    68→    </navigation-rule> \n    69→    <navigation-rule>\n    70→        <from-view-id>/portfolio.xhtml</from-view-id>       \n    71→        <navigation-case>\n    72→            <from-outcome>quotes</from-outcome>\n    73→            <to-view-id>/quote.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    74→        </navigation-case>\n    75→        <navigation-case>\n    76→            <from-outcome>sell</from-outcome>\n    77→            <to-view-id>/order.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    78→        </navigation-case>          \n    79→    </navigation-rule>\n    80→    <navigation-rule>\n    81→        <from-view-id>/marketSummary.xhtml</from-view-id>       \n    82→        <navigation-case>\n    83→            <from-outcome>quotes</from-outcome>\n    84→            <to-view-id>/quote.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    85→        </navigation-case>    \n    86→    </navigation-rule>            \n    87→    <navigation-rule>\n    88→        <from-view-id>/configure.xhtml</from-view-id>\n    89→        <navigation-case>\n    90→            <from-outcome>welcome</from-outcome>\n    91→            <to-view-id>/welcome.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    92→        </navigation-case>\n    93→        <navigation-case>\n    94→            <from-outcome>config</from-outcome>\n    95→            <to-view-id>/config.xhtml</to-view-id>\n    96→        </navigation-case>\n    97→        <navigation-case>\n    98→            <from-outcome>database</from-outcome>\n    99→            <to-view-id>/configure.xhtml</to-view-id>\n   100→        </navigation-case>\n   101→        <navigation-case>\n   102→            <from-outcome>stats</from-outcome>\n   103→            <to-view-id>/configure.xhtml</to-view-id>\n   104→        </navigation-case>\n   105→    </navigation-rule>\n   106→    <navigation-rule>\n   107→        <from-view-id>/order.xhtml</from-view-id>        \n   108→       <navigation-case>\n   109→            <from-outcome>quotes</from-outcome>\n   110→            <to-view-id>/quote.xhtml</to-view-id>\n   111→        </navigation-case>             \n   112→    </navigation-rule>\n   113→    <navigation-rule>\n   114→        <from-view-id>/quote.xhtml</from-view-id>        \n   115→       <navigation-case>\n   116→            <from-outcome>buy</from-outcome>\n   117→            <to-view-id>/order.xhtml</to-view-id>\n   118→        </navigation-case>             \n   119→    </navigation-rule>\n   120→</faces-config>\n   121→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"7ce9e94f-d32e-413d-a915-8a8f2580b954"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BNm8ZViuZU6c6i58qrE8uN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server>\n     3→   <featureManager>\n     4→      <feature>ejb-3.2</feature>\n     5→      <feature>servlet-4.0</feature>\n     6→      <feature>jsf-2.3</feature>\n     7→      <feature>jpa-2.2</feature>\n     8→      <feature>mdb-3.2</feature>\n     9→      <feature>wasJmsServer-1.0</feature>\n    10→      <feature>wasJmsClient-2.0</feature>\n    11→      <feature>cdi-2.0</feature>\n    12→      <feature>websocket-1.1</feature>\n    13→      <feature>concurrent-1.0</feature>\n    14→      <feature>jsonp-1.1</feature>\n    15→      <feature>jsonb-1.0</feature>\n    16→      <feature>beanValidation-2.0</feature>\n    17→      <feature>jaxrs-2.1</feature>\n    18→      <feature>ssl-1.0</feature>\n    19→   </featureManager>\n    20→\n    21→   <keyStore id=\"defaultKeyStore\" password=\"yourPassword\" />\n    22→\n    23→   <!--<logging traceSpecification=\"daytrader=fine\"/>-->\n    24→\n    25→   <!-- allow reuse of 'busy' ports for fast server recycling on linux (where ports remain blocked for up to 2 mins after server stops) ${tradelite.http.port} set in bootstrap.properties -->\n    26→   <httpEndpoint host=\"*\" httpPort=\"${default.http.port}\" httpsPort=\"${default.https.port}\" id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\">\n    27→      <tcpOptions soReuseAddr=\"true\" />\n    28→      <httpOptions maxKeepAliveRequests=\"-1\" />\n    29→   </httpEndpoint>\n    30→  \n    31→   <application location=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8.war\" type=\"war\" context-root=\"/daytrader\" />\n    32→   \n    33→   <library id=\"h2Library\">\n    34→      <fileset dir=\"${shared.resource.dir}\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    35→   </library>\n    36→\n    37→   <authData id=\"TradeDataSourceAuthData\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    38→   <authData id=\"TradeAdminAuthData\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    39→\n    40→   <connectionManager agedTimeout=\"-1\" connectionTimeout=\"0\" id=\"conMgr1\" maxIdleTime=\"-1\" maxPoolSize=\"100\" minPoolSize=\"100\" purgePolicy=\"FailingConnectionOnly\" reapTime=\"-1\" />  \n    41→   <dataSource connectionManagerRef=\"conMgr1\" id=\"DefaultDataSource\" isolationLevel=\"TRANSACTION_READ_COMMITTED\"  jndiName=\"jdbc/TradeDataSource\" statementCacheSize=\"60\">\n    42→      <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Library\" />\n    43→      <properties URL=\"jdbc:h2:file:${shared.resource.dir}/data/tradedb\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    44→   </dataSource>\n    45→   \n    46→   <messagingEngine id=\"defaultME\">\n    47→      <queue id=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    48→      <topicSpace id=\"TradeTopicSpace\" />\n    49→   </messagingEngine>\n    50→   \n    51→   <connectionManager id=\"ConMgr2\" maxPoolSize=\"20\" />\n    52→   <jmsQueueConnectionFactory connectionManagerRef=\"ConMgr2\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeBrokerQCF\">\n    53→      <properties.wasJms />\n    54→   </jmsQueueConnectionFactory>\n    55→   \n    56→   <connectionManager id=\"ConMgr3\" maxPoolSize=\"20\" />\n    57→   <jmsTopicConnectionFactory connectionManagerRef=\"ConMgr3\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeStreamerTCF\">\n    58→      <properties.wasJms />\n    59→   </jmsTopicConnectionFactory> \n    60→   \n    61→   <jmsQueue id=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\">\n    62→      <properties.wasJms deliveryMode=\"NonPersistent\" queueName=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    63→   </jmsQueue>\n    64→   \n    65→   <jmsTopic id=\"TradeStreamerTopic\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\">\n    66→      <properties.wasJms deliveryMode=\"NonPersistent\" topicSpace=\"TradeTopicSpace\" />\n    67→   </jmsTopic>\n    68→  \n    69→  <jmsActivationSpec id=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8/DTBroker3MDB\">\n    70→      <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    71→   </jmsActivationSpec>\n    72→   \n    73→   <jmsActivationSpec id=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8/DTStreamer3MDB\">\n    74→      <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"TradeStreamerTopic\" destinationType=\"javax.jms.Topic\" />\n    75→   </jmsActivationSpec>\n    76→</server>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"90f85957-53f7-4849-9952-ede5c2fba4d9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G1qjpnZzTrRnPrGdksBn3M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.BufferedReader;\n    19→import java.io.IOException;\n    20→import java.io.InputStream;\n    21→import java.io.InputStreamReader;\n    22→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    23→import java.sql.Connection;\n    24→import java.sql.DatabaseMetaData;\n    25→import java.sql.PreparedStatement;\n    26→import java.sql.ResultSet;\n    27→import java.sql.SQLException;\n    28→import java.sql.Statement;\n    29→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    30→\n    31→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    32→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    33→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    34→import javax.sql.DataSource;\n    35→\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeDB;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    44→\n    45→/**\n    46→ * TradeBuildDB uses operations provided by the TradeApplication to (a) create the Database tables\n    47→ * (b)populate a DayTrader database without creating the tables. Specifically, a\n    48→ * new DayTrader User population is created using UserIDs of the form \"uid:xxx\"\n    49→ * where xxx is a sequential number (e.g. uid:0, uid:1, etc.). New stocks are also created of the\n    50→ * form \"s:xxx\", again where xxx represents sequential numbers (e.g. s:1, s:2, etc.)\n    51→ */\n    52→@ApplicationScoped\n    53→public class TradeDirectDBUtils implements TradeDB {\n    54→\n    55→  // For Wildfly - add java:/ to this resource.\n    56→  \n    57→  @Resource(lookup = \"jdbc/TradeDataSource\")\n    58→  //@Resource(lookup = \"java:/jdbc/TradeDataSource\")\n    59→  private DataSource datasource;\n    60→\n    61→  @Inject \n    62→  @TradeJDBC\n    63→  TradeServices ts;\n    64→\n    65→  public String checkDBProductName() throws Exception {\n    66→    Connection conn = null;\n    67→    String dbProductName = null;\n    68→\n    69→    try {\n    70→\n    71→      conn = datasource.getConnection();\n    72→      DatabaseMetaData dbmd = conn.getMetaData();\n    73→      dbProductName = dbmd.getDatabaseProductName();\n    74→    } catch (SQLException e) {\n    75→      Log.error(e, \"TradeDirect:checkDBProductName() -- Error checking the Daytrader Database Product Name\");\n    76→    } finally {\n    77→      conn.close();\n    78→    }\n    79→    return dbProductName;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→\n    83→  /**\n    84→   * Re-create the DayTrader db tables and populate them OR just populate a DayTrader DB, logging to the provided output stream\n    85→   */\n    86→  public void buildDB(java.io.PrintWriter out, InputStream ddlFile) throws Exception {\n    87→    String symbol, companyName;\n    88→    int errorCount = 0; // Give up gracefully after 10 errors\n    89→\n    90→    //  TradeStatistics.statisticsEnabled=false;  // disable statistics\n    91→    out.println(\"<HEAD><BR><EM> TradeBuildDB: Building DayTrader Database...</EM><BR> This operation will take several minutes. Please wait...</HEAD>\");\n    92→    out.println(\"<BODY>\");\n    93→\n    94→    if (ddlFile != null) {\n    95→      //out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** warPath= \"+warPath+\" ****</BR></BODY>\");\n    96→\n    97→      boolean success = false;\n    98→\n    99→      Object[] sqlBuffer = null;\n   100→\n   101→      //parse the DDL file and fill the SQL commands into a buffer\n   102→      try {\n   103→        sqlBuffer = parseDDLToBuffer(ddlFile);\n   104→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   105→        Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to parse DDL file\");\n   106→        out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to parse DDL file for the specified database ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   107→        return;\n   108→      }\n   109→      if ((sqlBuffer == null) || (sqlBuffer.length == 0)) {\n   110→        out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Parsing DDL file returned empty buffer, please check that a valid DB specific DDL file is available and retry ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   111→        return;\n   112→      }\n   113→\n   114→      // send the sql commands buffer to drop and recreate the Daytrader tables\n   115→      out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Dropping and Recreating the DayTrader tables... ****</BR>\");\n   116→      try {\n   117→        success = recreateDBTables(sqlBuffer, out);\n   118→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   119→        Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to drop and recreate DayTrader Db Tables, please check for database consistency before continuing\");\n   120→        out.println(\"TradeBuildDB: Unable to drop and recreate DayTrader Db Tables, please check for database consistency before continuing\");\n   121→        return;\n   122→      }\n   123→      if (!success) {\n   124→        out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Unable to drop and recreate DayTrader Db Tables, please check for database consistency before continuing ****</BR></BODY>\");\n   125→        return;\n   126→      }\n   127→      out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** DayTrader tables successfully created! ****</BR><BR><b> Please Stop and Re-start your Daytrader application (or your application server) and then use the \\\"Repopulate Daytrader Database\\\" link to populate your database.</b></BR><BR><BR></BODY>\");\n   128→      return;\n   129→    } // end of createDBTables\n   130→\n   131→    out.println(\"<BR>TradeBuildDB: **** Creating \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() + \" Quotes ****</BR>\");\n   132→    //Attempt to delete all of the Trade users and Trade Quotes first\n   133→    try {\n   134→      resetTrade(true);\n   135→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   136→      Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Unable to delete Trade users (uid:0, uid:1, ...) and Trade Quotes (s:0, s:1, ...)\");\n   137→    }\n   138→    for (int i = 0; i < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES(); i++) {\n   139→      symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n   140→      companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n   141→      try {\n   142→        ts.createQuote(symbol, companyName, new java.math.BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice()));\n   143→        if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   144→          out.print(\".....\" + symbol);\n   145→          if (i % 100 == 0) {\n   146→            out.println(\" -<BR>\");\n   147→            out.flush();\n   148→          }\n   149→        }\n   150→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   151→        if (errorCount++ >= 10) {\n   152→          String error = \"Populate Trade DB aborting after 10 create quote errors. Check the EJB datasource configuration. Check the log for details <BR><BR> Exception is: <BR> \"\n   153→              + e.toString();\n   154→          Log.error(e, error);\n   155→          throw e;\n   156→        }\n   157→      }\n   158→    }\n   159→    out.println(\"<BR>\");\n   160→    out.println(\"<BR>**** Registering \" + TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS() + \" Users **** \");\n   161→    errorCount = 0; //reset for user registrations\n   162→\n   163→    // Registration is a formal operation in Trade 2.\n   164→    for (int i = 0; i < TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS(); i++) {\n   165→      String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   166→      String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   167→      String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   168→      String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   169→      String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   170→      double initialBalance = (double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000;\n   171→      if (i == 0) {\n   172→        initialBalance = 1000000; // uid:0 starts with a cool million.\n   173→      }\n   174→      try {\n   175→        AccountDataBean accountData = ts.register(userID, \"xxx\", fullname, address, email, creditcard, new BigDecimal(initialBalance));\n   176→\n   177→        if (accountData != null) {\n   178→          if (i % 50 == 0) {\n   179→            out.print(\"<BR>Account# \" + accountData.getAccountID() + \" userID=\" + userID);\n   180→          } // end-if\n   181→\n   182→          int holdings = TradeConfig.rndInt(TradeConfig.getMAX_HOLDINGS() + 1); // 0-MAX_HOLDING (inclusive), avg holdings per user = (MAX-0)/2\n   183→          double quantity = 0;\n   184→\n   185→          for (int j = 0; j < holdings; j++) {\n   186→            symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n   187→            quantity = TradeConfig.rndQuantity();\n   188→            ts.buy(userID, symbol, quantity, TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   189→          } // end-for\n   190→          if (i % 50 == 0) {\n   191→            out.println(\" has \" + holdings + \" holdings.\");\n   192→            out.flush();\n   193→          } // end-if\n   194→        } else {\n   195→          out.println(\"<BR>UID \" + userID + \" already registered.</BR>\");\n   196→          out.flush();\n   197→        } // end-if\n   198→\n   199→      } catch (Exception e) {\n   200→        if (errorCount++ >= 10) {\n   201→          String error = \"Populate Trade DB aborting after 10 user registration errors. Check the log for details. <BR><BR> Exception is: <BR>\"\n   202→              + e.toString();\n   203→          Log.error(e, error);\n   204→          throw e;\n   205→        }\n   206→      }\n   207→    } // end-for\n   208→    out.println(\"</BODY>\");\n   209→  }\n   210→\n   211→  private boolean recreateDBTables(Object[] sqlBuffer, java.io.PrintWriter out) throws Exception {\n   212→    // Clear MDB Statistics\n   213→    MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n   214→\n   215→    Connection conn = null;\n   216→    boolean success = false;\n   217→    try {\n   218→      conn = datasource.getConnection();\n   219→      Statement stmt = conn.createStatement();\n   220→      int bufferLength = sqlBuffer.length;\n   221→      for (int i = 0; i < bufferLength; i++) {\n   222→        try {\n   223→          stmt.executeUpdate((String) sqlBuffer[i]);\n   224→          // commit(conn);\n   225→        } catch (SQLException ex) {\n   226→          // Ignore DROP statements as tables won't always exist.\n   227→          if (((String) sqlBuffer[i]).indexOf(\"DROP \") < 0) {\n   228→            Log.error(\"TradeDirect:recreateDBTables SQL Exception thrown on executing the foll sql command: \" + sqlBuffer[i], ex);\n   229→            out.println(\"<BR>SQL Exception thrown on executing the foll sql command: <I>\" + sqlBuffer[i] + \"</I> . Check log for details.</BR>\");\n   230→          }\n   231→        }\n   232→      }\n   233→      stmt.close();\n   234→      conn.commit();\n   235→      success = true;\n   236→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   237→      Log.error(e, \"TradeDirect:recreateDBTables() -- Error dropping and recreating the database tables\");\n   238→    } finally {\n   239→      conn.close();\n   240→    }\n   241→    return success;\n   242→  }\n   243→\n   244→\n   245→  public RunStatsDataBean resetTrade(boolean deleteAll) throws Exception {\n   246→    // Clear MDB Statistics\n   247→    MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n   248→    // Reset Trade\n   249→\n   250→    RunStatsDataBean runStatsData = new RunStatsDataBean();\n   251→    Connection conn = null;\n   252→    try {\n   253→\n   254→      conn = datasource.getConnection();\n   255→      conn.setAutoCommit(false);\n   256→      PreparedStatement stmt = null;\n   257→      ResultSet rs = null;\n   258→\n   259→      if (deleteAll) {\n   260→        try {\n   261→          stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from quoteejb\");\n   262→          stmt.executeUpdate();\n   263→          stmt.close();\n   264→          stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from accountejb\");\n   265→          stmt.executeUpdate();\n   266→          stmt.close();\n   267→          stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from accountprofileejb\");\n   268→          stmt.executeUpdate();\n   269→          stmt.close();\n   270→          stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from holdingejb\");\n   271→          stmt.executeUpdate();\n   272→          stmt.close();\n   273→          stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from orderejb\");\n   274→          stmt.executeUpdate();\n   275→          stmt.close();\n   276→          // FUTURE: - DuplicateKeyException - For now, don't start at\n   277→          // zero as KeySequenceDirect and KeySequenceBean will still\n   278→          // give out\n   279→          // the cached Block and then notice this change. Better\n   280→          // solution is\n   281→          // to signal both classes to drop their cached blocks\n   282→          // stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from keygenejb\");\n   283→          // stmt.executeUpdate();\n   284→          // stmt.close();\n   285→          conn.commit();\n   286→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   287→          Log.error(e, \"TradeDirect:resetTrade(deleteAll) -- Error deleting Trade users and stock from the Trade database\");\n   288→        }\n   289→        return runStatsData;\n   290→      }\n   291→\n   292→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from holdingejb where holdingejb.account_accountid is null\");\n   293→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   294→      stmt.close();\n   295→\n   296→      // Count and Delete newly registered users (users w/ id that start\n   297→      // \"ru:%\":\n   298→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from accountprofileejb where userid like 'ru:%'\");\n   299→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   300→      stmt.close();\n   301→\n   302→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from orderejb where account_accountid in (select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'ru:%')\");\n   303→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   304→      stmt.close();\n   305→\n   306→      stmt = getStatement(conn,\n   307→          \"delete from holdingejb where account_accountid in (select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'ru:%')\");\n   308→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   309→      stmt.close();\n   310→\n   311→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from accountejb where profile_userid like 'ru:%'\");\n   312→      int newUserCount = stmt.executeUpdate();\n   313→      runStatsData.setNewUserCount(newUserCount);\n   314→      stmt.close();\n   315→\n   316→      // Count of trade users\n   317→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(accountid) as \\\"tradeUserCount\\\" from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%'\");\n   318→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   319→      rs.next();\n   320→      int tradeUserCount = rs.getInt(\"tradeUserCount\");\n   321→      runStatsData.setTradeUserCount(tradeUserCount);\n   322→      stmt.close();\n   323→\n   324→      rs.close();\n   325→      // Count of trade stocks\n   326→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(symbol) as \\\"tradeStockCount\\\" from quoteejb a where a.symbol like 's:%'\");\n   327→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   328→      rs.next();\n   329→      int tradeStockCount = rs.getInt(\"tradeStockCount\");\n   330→      runStatsData.setTradeStockCount(tradeStockCount);\n   331→      stmt.close();\n   332→\n   333→      // Count of trade users login, logout\n   334→      stmt = getStatement(conn,\n   335→          \"select sum(loginCount) as \\\"sumLoginCount\\\", sum(logoutCount) as \\\"sumLogoutCount\\\" from accountejb a where  a.profile_userID like 'uid:%'\");\n   336→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   337→      rs.next();\n   338→      int sumLoginCount = rs.getInt(\"sumLoginCount\");\n   339→      int sumLogoutCount = rs.getInt(\"sumLogoutCount\");\n   340→      runStatsData.setSumLoginCount(sumLoginCount);\n   341→      runStatsData.setSumLogoutCount(sumLogoutCount);\n   342→      stmt.close();\n   343→\n   344→      rs.close();\n   345→      // Update logoutcount and loginCount back to zero\n   346→\n   347→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"update accountejb set logoutCount=0,loginCount=0 where profile_userID like 'uid:%'\");\n   348→      stmt.executeUpdate();\n   349→      stmt.close();\n   350→\n   351→      // count holdings for trade users\n   352→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(holdingid) as \\\"holdingCount\\\" from holdingejb h where h.account_accountid in \"\n   353→          + \"(select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%')\");\n   354→\n   355→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   356→      rs.next();\n   357→      int holdingCount = rs.getInt(\"holdingCount\");\n   358→      runStatsData.setHoldingCount(holdingCount);\n   359→      stmt.close();\n   360→      rs.close();\n   361→\n   362→      // count orders for trade users\n   363→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(orderid) as \\\"orderCount\\\" from orderejb o where o.account_accountid in \"\n   364→          + \"(select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%')\");\n   365→\n   366→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   367→      rs.next();\n   368→      int orderCount = rs.getInt(\"orderCount\");\n   369→      runStatsData.setOrderCount(orderCount);\n   370→      stmt.close();\n   371→      rs.close();\n   372→\n   373→      // count orders by type for trade users\n   374→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(orderid) \\\"buyOrderCount\\\"from orderejb o where (o.account_accountid in \"\n   375→          + \"(select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%')) AND \" + \" (o.orderType='buy')\");\n   376→\n   377→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   378→      rs.next();\n   379→      int buyOrderCount = rs.getInt(\"buyOrderCount\");\n   380→      runStatsData.setBuyOrderCount(buyOrderCount);\n   381→      stmt.close();\n   382→      rs.close();\n   383→\n   384→      // count orders by type for trade users\n   385→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(orderid) \\\"sellOrderCount\\\"from orderejb o where (o.account_accountid in \"\n   386→          + \"(select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%')) AND \" + \" (o.orderType='sell')\");\n   387→\n   388→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   389→      rs.next();\n   390→      int sellOrderCount = rs.getInt(\"sellOrderCount\");\n   391→      runStatsData.setSellOrderCount(sellOrderCount);\n   392→      stmt.close();\n   393→      rs.close();\n   394→\n   395→      // Delete cancelled orders\n   396→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from orderejb where orderStatus='cancelled'\");\n   397→      int cancelledOrderCount = stmt.executeUpdate();\n   398→      runStatsData.setCancelledOrderCount(cancelledOrderCount);\n   399→      stmt.close();\n   400→      rs.close();\n   401→\n   402→      // count open orders by type for trade users\n   403→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"select count(orderid) \\\"openOrderCount\\\"from orderejb o where (o.account_accountid in \"\n   404→          + \"(select accountid from accountejb a where a.profile_userid like 'uid:%')) AND \" + \" (o.orderStatus='open')\");\n   405→\n   406→      rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n   407→      rs.next();\n   408→      int openOrderCount = rs.getInt(\"openOrderCount\");\n   409→      runStatsData.setOpenOrderCount(openOrderCount);\n   410→\n   411→      stmt.close();\n   412→      rs.close();\n   413→      // Delete orders for holding which have been purchased and sold\n   414→      stmt = getStatement(conn, \"delete from orderejb where holding_holdingid is null\");\n   415→      int deletedOrderCount = stmt.executeUpdate();\n   416→      runStatsData.setDeletedOrderCount(deletedOrderCount);\n   417→      stmt.close();\n   418→      rs.close();\n   419→\n   420→      conn.commit();\n   421→\n   422→      System.out.println(\"TradeDirect:reset Run stats data\\n\\n\" + runStatsData);\n   423→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   424→      Log.error(e, \"Failed to reset Trade\");\n   425→      conn.rollback();\n   426→      throw e;\n   427→    } finally {\n   428→      conn.close();\n   429→    }\n   430→    return runStatsData;\n   431→\n   432→  }\n   433→\n   434→  private PreparedStatement getStatement(Connection conn, String sql) throws Exception {\n   435→    return conn.prepareStatement(sql);\n   436→  }\n   437→\n   438→  public Object[] parseDDLToBuffer(InputStream ddlFile) throws Exception {\n   439→    BufferedReader br = null;\n   440→    ArrayList<String> sqlBuffer = new ArrayList<String>(30); //initial capacity 30 assuming we have 30 ddl-sql statements to read\n   441→\n   442→    try {\n   443→      br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(ddlFile));\n   444→      String s;\n   445→      String sql = new String();\n   446→      while ((s = br.readLine()) != null) {\n   447→        s = s.trim();\n   448→        if ((s.length() != 0) && (s.charAt(0) != '#')) // Empty lines or lines starting with \"#\" are ignored\n   449→        {\n   450→          sql = sql + \" \" + s;\n   451→          if (s.endsWith(\";\")) { // reached end of sql statement\n   452→            sql = sql.replace(';', ' '); //remove the semicolon\n   453→            sqlBuffer.add(sql);\n   454→            sql = \"\";\n   455→          }\n   456→        }\n   457→      }\n   458→    } catch (IOException ex) {\n   459→      Log.error(\"TradeBuildDB:parseDDLToBuffer Exeception during open/read of File: \" + ddlFile, ex);\n   460→      throw ex;\n   461→    } finally {\n   462→      if (br != null) {\n   463→        try {\n   464→          br.close();\n   465→        } catch (IOException ex) {\n   466→          Log.error(\"TradeBuildDB:parseDDLToBuffer Failed to close BufferedReader\", ex);\n   467→        }\n   468→      }\n   469→    }\n   470→    return sqlBuffer.toArray();\n   471→  }\n   472→}\n   473→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"bdadab2c-b107-4847-8c16-bb377c437b7a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VU9NV4VANA9YwCk2PoSr74","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.sql.Connection;\n    19→import java.sql.PreparedStatement;\n    20→import java.sql.ResultSet;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.HashMap;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.KeyBlock;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    28→\n    29→public class KeySequenceDirect {\n    30→\n    31→    private static HashMap<String, Collection<?>> keyMap = new HashMap<String, Collection<?>>();\n    32→\n    33→    public static synchronized Integer getNextID(Connection conn, String keyName, boolean inSession, boolean inGlobalTxn) throws Exception {\n    34→        Integer nextID = null;\n    35→        // First verify we have allocated a block of keys\n    36→        // for this key name\n    37→        // Then verify the allocated block has not been depleted\n    38→        // allocate a new block if necessary\n    39→        if (keyMap.containsKey(keyName) == false) {\n    40→            allocNewBlock(conn, keyName, inSession, inGlobalTxn);\n    41→        }\n    42→        Collection<?> block = keyMap.get(keyName);\n    43→\n    44→        Iterator<?> ids = block.iterator();\n    45→        if (ids.hasNext() == false) {\n    46→            ids = allocNewBlock(conn, keyName, inSession, inGlobalTxn).iterator();\n    47→        }\n    48→        // get and return a new unique key\n    49→        nextID = (Integer) ids.next();\n    50→\n    51→        \n    52→        Log.trace(\"KeySequenceDirect:getNextID inSession(\" + inSession + \") - return new PK ID for Entity type: \" + keyName + \" ID=\" + nextID);\n    53→        \n    54→        return nextID;\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    private static Collection<?> allocNewBlock(Connection conn, String keyName, boolean inSession, boolean inGlobalTxn) throws Exception {\n    58→        try {\n    59→\n    60→            if (inGlobalTxn == false && !inSession) {\n    61→                conn.commit(); // commit any pending txns\n    62→            }\n    63→\n    64→            PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement(getKeyForUpdateSQL);\n    65→            stmt.setString(1, keyName);\n    66→            ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n    67→\n    68→            if (!rs.next()) {\n    69→                // No keys found for this name - create a new one\n    70→                PreparedStatement stmt2 = conn.prepareStatement(createKeySQL);\n    71→                int keyVal = 0;\n    72→                stmt2.setString(1, keyName);\n    73→                stmt2.setInt(2, keyVal);\n    74→                stmt2.executeUpdate();\n    75→                stmt2.close();\n    76→                stmt.close();\n    77→                stmt = conn.prepareStatement(getKeyForUpdateSQL);\n    78→                stmt.setString(1, keyName);\n    79→                rs = stmt.executeQuery();\n    80→                rs.next();\n    81→            }\n    82→\n    83→            int keyVal = rs.getInt(\"keyval\");\n    84→\n    85→            stmt.close();\n    86→\n    87→            stmt = conn.prepareStatement(updateKeyValueSQL);\n    88→            stmt.setInt(1, keyVal + TradeConfig.KEYBLOCKSIZE);\n    89→            stmt.setString(2, keyName);\n    90→            stmt.executeUpdate();\n    91→            stmt.close();\n    92→\n    93→            Collection<?> block = new KeyBlock(keyVal, keyVal + TradeConfig.KEYBLOCKSIZE - 1);\n    94→            keyMap.put(keyName, block);\n    95→\n    96→            if (inGlobalTxn == false && !inSession) {\n    97→                conn.commit();\n    98→            }\n    99→\n   100→            return block;\n   101→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   102→            String error = \"KeySequenceDirect:allocNewBlock - failure to allocate new block of keys for Entity type: \" + keyName;\n   103→            Log.error(e, error);\n   104→            throw new Exception(error + e.toString());\n   105→        }\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    private static final String getKeyForUpdateSQL = \"select * from keygenejb kg where kg.keyname = ?  for update\";\n   109→\n   110→    private static final String createKeySQL = \"insert into keygenejb \" + \"( keyname, keyval ) \" + \"VALUES (  ?  ,  ? )\";\n   111→\n   112→    private static final String updateKeyValueSQL = \"update keygenejb set keyval = ? \" + \"where keyname = ?\";\n   113→\n   114→}\n   115→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"a8a3cfe2-f912-4f23-bf6c-1f7eaa75c0b3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NPCs5GjnfQ2yhyDnZ5G6Ka","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    19→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    20→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    21→import javax.transaction.UserTransaction;\n    22→\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    25→\n    26→@Dependent\n    27→public class AsyncOrder implements Runnable {\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  @TradeJDBC\n    31→  TradeServices tradeService;\n    32→\n    33→  @Resource\n    34→  UserTransaction ut;\n    35→      \n    36→  Integer orderID;\n    37→  boolean twoPhase;\n    38→  \n    39→  public void setProperties(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    40→    this.orderID = orderID;\n    41→    this.twoPhase =  twoPhase;\n    42→  }     \n    43→  \n    44→  @Override\n    45→  public void run() {\n    46→        \n    47→        \n    48→    try {  \n    49→      ut.begin();\n    50→      tradeService.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);      \n    51→      ut.commit();\n    52→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    53→      \n    54→      try {\n    55→        ut.rollback();\n    56→      } catch (Exception e1) {\n    57→        try {\n    58→          throw new Exception(e1);\n    59→        } catch (Exception e2) {\n    60→          e2.printStackTrace();\n    61→        }\n    62→      } \n    63→      try {\n    64→        throw new Exception(e);\n    65→      } catch (Exception e1) {\n    66→        // TODO Auto-generated catch block\n    67→        e1.printStackTrace();\n    68→      }\n    69→    } \n    70→  }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"73c387a6-46e8-49f4-a384-ed745f703c28"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EDwn7mfMx7oPbRdttcoS5S","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    21→import javax.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedExecutorService;\n    22→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    23→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    24→\n    25→@RequestScoped\n    26→public class AsyncOrderSubmitter {\n    27→  \n    28→  \n    29→  @Resource\n    30→  private ManagedExecutorService mes;\n    31→\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private AsyncOrder asyncOrder;\n    34→  \n    35→  \n    36→  public Future<?> submitOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    37→    asyncOrder.setProperties(orderID,twoPhase);\n    38→    return mes.submit(asyncOrder);\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"8f80a179-45bc-46a8-a939-c260e3585ea7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016hfB2rd6kHNWu5Fmgx4D6Z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→\n    19→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    20→import javax.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    21→import javax.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    22→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    23→\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    27→\n    28→\n    29→@Dependent\n    30→public class AsyncScheduledOrder implements Runnable {\n    31→\n    32→  TradeServices tradeService;\n    33→\n    34→  Integer orderID;\n    35→  boolean twoPhase;\n    36→\n    37→  @Inject \n    38→  public AsyncScheduledOrder(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    39→    tradeService = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setProperties(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    43→    this.orderID = orderID;\n    44→    this.twoPhase =  twoPhase;\n    45→  }     \n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public void run() {\n    49→\n    50→\n    51→    try {  \n    52→      tradeService.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);      \n    53→\n    54→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    55→\n    56→      e.printStackTrace();\n    57→    }\n    58→  }\n    59→}\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"4a9cd3e9-4c9c-4ef6-8730-64e574ed287f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RjnuNQ34HFNdpJDhTioEM1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    22→import javax.enterprise.concurrent.ManagedScheduledExecutorService;\n    23→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    24→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    25→\n    26→@RequestScoped\n    27→public class AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter {\n    28→  \n    29→  \n    30→  @Resource\n    31→  private ManagedScheduledExecutorService mes;\n    32→\n    33→  @Inject\n    34→  private AsyncScheduledOrder asyncOrder;\n    35→  \n    36→  \n    37→  public Future<?> submitOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    38→    asyncOrder.setProperties(orderID,twoPhase);\n    39→    return mes.schedule(asyncOrder,500,TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);\n    40→  }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"292da971-43f6-4eed-896e-18102303ccf4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EeXN216LejwBeZdwA9fo2v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.session2direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n    23→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    24→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    25→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagement;\n    26→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\n    27→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    28→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→\n    44→@Stateless\n    45→@TradeSession2Direct\n    46→@RuntimeMode(\"Session to Direct\")\n    47→@Trace\n    48→@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    49→@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    50→public class DirectSLSBBean implements TradeServices {\n    51→\n    52→  @Inject\n    53→  @TradeJDBC\n    54→  TradeServices tradeDirect;\n    55→  \n    56→  @Inject \n    57→  AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter asyncEJBOrderSubmitter; \n    58→\n    59→  @Override\n    60→  public int getImpl() {\n    61→    return TradeConfig.SESSION_TO_DIRECT;\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  @Override\n    65→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception {\n    66→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    67→    return tradeDirect.getMarketSummary();\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  @Override\n    71→  public OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding,\n    72→      String orderType, double quantity) throws Exception {\n    73→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    74→    return tradeDirect.createOrder(account, quote, holding, orderType, quantity);\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  @Override\n    78→  @NotNull\n    79→  public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n    80→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    81→     OrderDataBean orderdata = tradeDirect.buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode);\n    82→    \n    83→    if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n    84→      this.completeOrderAsync(orderdata.getOrderID(), false);\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    return orderdata; \n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  @Override\n    91→  @NotNull\n    92→  public OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n    93→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    94→    OrderDataBean orderdata =  tradeDirect.sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode);\n    95→    \n    96→    if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n    97→      this.completeOrderAsync(orderdata.getOrderID(), false);\n    98→    }\n    99→    return orderdata;\n   100→    \n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  @Override\n   104→  public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   105→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   106→    tradeDirect.queueOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   107→\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  @Override\n   111→  public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   112→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   113→    return tradeDirect.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→  @Override\n   117→  public Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   118→    asyncEJBOrderSubmitter.submitOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   119→    return null;\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  @Override\n   123→  public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   124→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   125→    tradeDirect.cancelOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   126→\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  @Override\n   130→  public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   131→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   132→    tradeDirect.orderCompleted(userID, orderID);\n   133→\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→  @Override\n   137→  public Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   138→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   139→    return tradeDirect.getOrders(userID);\n   140→  }\n   141→\n   142→  @Override\n   143→  public Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   144→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   145→    return tradeDirect.getClosedOrders(userID);\n   146→  }\n   147→\n   148→  @Override\n   149→  public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception {\n   150→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   151→    return tradeDirect.createQuote(symbol, companyName, price);\n   152→  }\n   153→\n   154→  @Override\n   155→  public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   156→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   157→    return tradeDirect.getQuote(symbol); \n   158→  }\n   159→\n   160→  @Override\n   161→  public Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception {\n   162→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   163→    return tradeDirect.getAllQuotes();\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  @Override\n   167→  public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded)\n   168→      throws Exception {\n   169→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   170→    return tradeDirect.updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, newPrice, sharesTraded);\n   171→  }\n   172→\n   173→  @Override\n   174→  public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception {\n   175→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   176→    return tradeDirect.getHoldings(userID);\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  @Override\n   180→  public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception {\n   181→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   182→    return tradeDirect.getHolding(holdingID);\n   183→  }\n   184→\n   185→  @Override\n   186→  public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   187→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   188→    return tradeDirect.getAccountData(userID);\n   189→  }\n   190→\n   191→  @Override\n   192→  public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   193→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   194→    return tradeDirect.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   195→  }\n   196→\n   197→  @Override\n   198→  public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n   199→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   200→    return tradeDirect.updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  @Override\n   204→  public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception {\n   205→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   206→    return tradeDirect.login(userID, password);\n   207→  }\n   208→\n   209→  @Override\n   210→  public void logout(String userID) throws Exception {\n   211→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   212→    tradeDirect.logout(userID);\n   213→  }\n   214→\n   215→  @Override\n   216→  public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email,\n   217→      String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) throws Exception {\n   218→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   219→    return tradeDirect.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n   220→  }\n   221→\n   222→  @Override\n   223→  public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   224→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n   225→  }\n   226→\n   227→  @Override\n   228→  public double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception {\n   229→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n   230→  }\n   231→\n   232→\n   233→  @Override\n   234→  public void setInSession(boolean inSession) {\n   235→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"DirectSLSBBean::setInGlobalTxn not supported\");\n   236→  }\n   237→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"bcc08e72-f84d-4d19-9f9b-c93746cedec7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017up4CVJoWJ1p9Z3aZ4X7TK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    19→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    20→import javax.ejb.ActivationConfigProperty;\n    21→import javax.ejb.MessageDriven;\n    22→import javax.ejb.MessageDrivenContext;\n    23→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    24→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    25→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagement;\n    26→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\n    27→import javax.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    28→import javax.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    29→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    30→import javax.jms.Message;\n    31→import javax.jms.MessageListener;\n    32→import javax.jms.TextMessage;\n    33→\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    41→\n    42→// For Glassfish/Payara - take jms/ off of the destination name\n    43→\n    44→@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    45→@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    46→@MessageDriven(activationConfig = { @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"acknowledgeMode\", propertyValue = \"Auto-acknowledge\"),\n    47→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Queue\"),\n    48→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\"),\n    49→    //@ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"TradeBrokerQueue\"),\n    50→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"subscriptionDurability\", propertyValue = \"NonDurable\") })\n    51→@Trace\n    52→public class DTBroker3MDB implements MessageListener {\n    53→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    54→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    55→\n    56→  @Resource\n    57→  public MessageDrivenContext mdc;\n    58→\n    59→  @Inject @Any\n    60→  Instance<TradeServices> services;\n    61→  \n    62→  private TradeServices trade;\n    63→\n    64→  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    65→\n    66→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    67→      statInterval = 10000;\n    68→    }\n    69→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    70→  }   \n    71→\n    72→  @PostConstruct\n    73→  void boostrapTradeServices() {\n    74→    trade = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    75→  } \n    76→  \n    77→  @Override\n    78→  public void onMessage(Message message) {\n    79→    try {\n    80→\n    81→      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText() + \"command-->\"\n    82→          + message.getStringProperty(\"command\") + \"<--\");\n    83→\n    84→      if (message.getJMSRedelivered()) {\n    85→        Log.log(\"DTBroker3MDB: The following JMS message was redelivered due to a rollback:\\n\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText());\n    86→        // Order has been cancelled -- ignore returned messages\n    87→        return;\n    88→      }\n    89→      String command = message.getStringProperty(\"command\");\n    90→      if (command == null) {\n    91→        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n    92→        return;\n    93→      }\n    94→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n    95→        /* Get the Order ID and complete the Order */\n    96→        Integer orderID = new Integer(message.getIntProperty(\"orderID\"));\n    97→        boolean twoPhase = message.getBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\");\n    98→        boolean direct = message.getBooleanProperty(\"direct\");\n    99→        long publishTime = message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\");\n   100→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   101→\n   102→        try {\n   103→          //TODO: why direct?\n   104→          //trade = getTrade(direct);\n   105→\n   106→          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase + \" direct=\" + direct);\n   107→\n   108→          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   109→\n   110→          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   111→\n   112→          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   113→            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n   114→                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   115→                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n   116→                \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   117→                \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   118→                \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   119→          }\n   120→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   121→          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n   122→          mdc.setRollbackOnly();\n   123→          /*\n   124→           * UPDATE - order is cancelled in trade if an error is\n   125→           * caught try { trade.cancelOrder(orderID, twoPhase); }\n   126→           * catch (Exception e2) { Log.error(\"order cancel failed\",\n   127→           * e); }\n   128→           */\n   129→        }\n   130→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n   131→\n   132→        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + ((TextMessage) message).getText());\n   133→\n   134→        long publishTime = message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\");\n   135→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   136→\n   137→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   138→\n   139→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   140→          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n   141→              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   142→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   143→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   144→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   145→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   146→        }\n   147→      } else {\n   148→        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText());\n   149→      }\n   150→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   151→      // JMS onMessage should handle all exceptions\n   152→      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Error rolling back transaction\", t);\n   153→      mdc.setRollbackOnly();\n   154→    }\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→\n   158→\n   159→}\n   160→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"6dffbdfa-ae3b-4f93-8869-81f0ac76c495"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016U4m2Crju4HJtYmQasBu72","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import javax.annotation.Resource;\n    19→import javax.ejb.ActivationConfigProperty;\n    20→import javax.ejb.MessageDriven;\n    21→import javax.ejb.MessageDrivenContext;\n    22→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    23→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    24→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagement;\n    25→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\n    26→import javax.jms.Message;\n    27→import javax.jms.MessageListener;\n    28→import javax.jms.TextMessage;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    35→\n    36→//For Glassfish/Payara - take jms/ off of the destination name\n    37→\n    38→@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    39→@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.CONTAINER)\n    40→@MessageDriven(activationConfig = { @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"acknowledgeMode\", propertyValue = \"Auto-acknowledge\"),\n    41→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destinationType\", propertyValue = \"javax.jms.Topic\"),\n    42→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\"),\n    43→    //@ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"destination\", propertyValue = \"TradeStreamerTopic\"),\n    44→    @ActivationConfigProperty(propertyName = \"subscriptionDurability\", propertyValue = \"NonDurable\") })\n    45→@Trace\n    46→public class DTStreamer3MDB implements MessageListener {\n    47→\n    48→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    49→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    50→\n    51→  @Resource\n    52→  public MessageDrivenContext mdc;\n    53→ \n    54→\n    55→  /** Creates a new instance of TradeSteamerMDB */\n    56→  public DTStreamer3MDB() {\n    57→    Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:DTStreamer3MDB()\");\n    58→    \n    59→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    60→      statInterval = 10000;\n    61→    }\n    62→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  @Override\n    66→  public void onMessage(Message message) {\n    67→\n    68→    try {\n    69→      Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText() + \"command-->\"\n    70→          + message.getStringProperty(\"command\") + \"<--\");\n    71→      \n    72→      String command = message.getStringProperty(\"command\");\n    73→      if (command == null) {\n    74→        Log.debug(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n    75→        return;\n    76→      }\n    77→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"updateQuote\")) {\n    78→        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage -- received message -->\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText() + \"\\n\\t symbol = \"\n    79→              + message.getStringProperty(\"symbol\") + \"\\n\\t current price =\" + message.getStringProperty(\"price\") + \"\\n\\t old price =\"\n    80→              + message.getStringProperty(\"oldPrice\"));\n    81→        \n    82→        long publishTime = message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\");\n    83→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    84→\n    85→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:udpateQuote\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n    86→\n    87→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n    88→          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: \" + statInterval + \" prices updated:\" +\n    89→              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n    90→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n    91→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n    92→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n    93→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs() );\n    94→        }\n    95→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n    96→        Log.trace(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage  received ping command -- message: \" + ((TextMessage) message).getText());\n    97→        \n    98→\n    99→        long publishTime = message.getLongProperty(\"publishTime\");\n   100→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n   101→\n   102→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n   103→\n   104→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n   105→          Log.log(\" DTStreamer3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n   106→              \" Total message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   107→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   108→              \" min: \" +currentStats.getMinSecs()+\n   109→              \" max: \" +currentStats.getMaxSecs()+\n   110→              \" avg: \" +currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   111→        }\n   112→      } else {\n   113→        Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + ((TextMessage) message).getText());\n   114→      }\n   115→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   116→      // JMS onMessage should handle all exceptions\n   117→      Log.error(\"DTStreamer3MDB: Exception\", t);\n   118→      //UPDATE - Not rolling back for now -- so error messages are not redelivered\n   119→      mdc.setRollbackOnly();\n   120→    }\n   121→  }\n   122→\n   123→}\n   124→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"8485811c-58fb-4a06-bf0f-807a56ec8366"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Fk32f9UdeLDb2C5pKpte4q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    22→import javax.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    23→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    24→import javax.servlet.Filter;\n    25→import javax.servlet.FilterChain;\n    26→import javax.servlet.FilterConfig;\n    27→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    28→import javax.servlet.ServletRequest;\n    29→import javax.servlet.ServletResponse;\n    30→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebFilter;\n    31→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Diagnostics;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    39→\n    40→@WebFilter(filterName = \"OrdersAlertFilter\", urlPatterns = \"/app\")\n    41→@Trace\n    42→public class OrdersAlertFilter implements Filter {\n    43→\t\n    44→  private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    45→\n    46→  @Inject \n    47→  public OrdersAlertFilter(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    48→    super();\n    49→    tradeAction = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→\n    53→  /**\n    54→   * @see Filter#init(FilterConfig)\n    55→   */\n    56→  private FilterConfig filterConfig = null;\n    57→\n    58→  @Override\n    59→  public void init(FilterConfig filterConfig) throws ServletException {\n    60→    this.filterConfig = filterConfig;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  /**\n    64→   * @see Filter#doFilter(ServletRequest, ServletResponse, FilterChain)\n    65→   */\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse resp, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    68→    if (filterConfig == null) {\n    69→      return;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    if (TradeConfig.getDisplayOrderAlerts() == true) {\n    73→\n    74→      try {\n    75→        String action = req.getParameter(\"action\");\n    76→        if (action != null) {\n    77→          action = action.trim();\n    78→          if ((action.length() > 0) && (!action.equals(\"logout\"))) {\n    79→            String userID;\n    80→            if (action.equals(\"login\")) {\n    81→              userID = req.getParameter(\"uid\");\n    82→            } else {\n    83→              userID = (String) ((HttpServletRequest) req).getSession().getAttribute(\"uidBean\");\n    84→            }\n    85→\n    86→            if ((userID != null) && (userID.trim().length() > 0)) {\n    87→\n    88→              Collection<?> closedOrders = tradeAction.getClosedOrders(userID);\n    89→              if ((closedOrders != null) && (closedOrders.size() > 0)) {\n    90→                req.setAttribute(\"closedOrders\", closedOrders);\n    91→              }\n    92→              if (Log.doTrace()) {\n    93→                Log.printCollection(\"OrderAlertFilter: userID=\" + userID + \" closedOrders=\", closedOrders);\n    94→              }\n    95→            }\n    96→          }\n    97→        }\n    98→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    99→        Log.error(e, \"OrdersAlertFilter - Error checking for closedOrders\");\n   100→      }\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    Diagnostics.checkDiagnostics();\n   104→\n   105→    chain.doFilter(req, resp/* wrapper */);\n   106→  }\n   107→\n   108→  /**\n   109→   * @see Filter#destroy()\n   110→   */\n   111→  @Override\n   112→  public void destroy() {\n   113→    this.filterConfig = null;\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→}\n   117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"de322445-bfa0-4c7e-aba9-e4fe99340f5e"}
