{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PX4VH9ZfbtrXVva8Qt8R5H","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    21→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    22→import javax.servlet.ServletOutputStream;\n    23→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    24→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    26→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    29→\n    30→/**\n    31→ *\n    32→ * PingServlet tests fundamental dynamic HTML creation functionality through\n    33→ * server side servlet processing.\n    34→ *\n    35→ */\n    36→\n    37→@WebServlet(name = \"PingServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingServlet\" })\n    38→public class PingServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    39→\n    40→\tprivate static final long serialVersionUID = 7097023236709683760L;\n    41→\tprivate static String initTime;\n    42→    private static int hitCount;\n    43→\n    44→    /**\n    45→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n    46→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    47→     *\n    48→     * @param res\n    49→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    50→     * @param res2\n    51→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    52→     */\n    53→    @Override\n    54→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    55→        doGet(req, res);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    /**\n    59→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    60→     * requests.\n    61→     *\n    62→     * @param request\n    63→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    64→     * @param responce\n    65→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    66→     **/\n    67→    @Override\n    68→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    69→        try {\n    70→            res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    71→\n    72→            // The following 2 lines are the difference between PingServlet and\n    73→            // PingServletWriter\n    74→            // the latter uses a PrintWriter for output versus a binary output\n    75→            // stream.\n    76→            ServletOutputStream out = res.getOutputStream();\n    77→            // java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    78→            hitCount++;\n    79→            out.println(\"<html><head><title>Ping Servlet</title></head>\"\n    80→                    + \"<body><HR><BR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping Servlet<BR></FONT><FONT size=\\\"+1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \" + initTime\n    81→                    + \"<BR><BR></FONT>  <B>Hit Count: \" + hitCount + \"</B></body></html>\");\n    82→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    83→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet.doGet(...): general exception caught\");\n    84→            res.sendError(500, e.toString());\n    85→\n    86→        }\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    /**\n    90→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n    91→     *\n    92→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n    93→     **/\n    94→    @Override\n    95→    public String getServletInfo() {\n    96→        return \"Basic dynamic HTML generation through a servlet\";\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    /**\n   100→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   101→     *\n   102→     * @param config\n   103→     *            ServletConfig:\n   104→     **/\n   105→    @Override\n   106→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   107→        super.init(config);\n   108→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   109→        hitCount = 0;\n   110→\n   111→    }\n   112→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"4c73507f-418e-424d-96e6-3745ce3b9fc8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LJeZfwKYmQQtJcr2wq6Cpb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    21→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    22→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    23→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    24→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirect;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    29→\n    30→/**\n    31→ *\n    32→ * PingServlet2DB tests the path of a servlet making a JDBC connection to a\n    33→ * database\n    34→ *\n    35→ */\n    36→\n    37→@WebServlet(name = \"PingServlet2DB\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingServlet2DB\" })\n    38→public class PingServlet2DB extends HttpServlet {\n    39→\n    40→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -6456675185605592049L;\n    41→    private static String initTime;\n    42→    private static int hitCount;\n    43→\n    44→    /**\n    45→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n    46→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    47→     *\n    48→     * @param res\n    49→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    50→     * @param res2\n    51→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    52→     */\n    53→    @Override\n    54→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    55→        doGet(req, res);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    /**\n    59→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    60→     * requests.\n    61→     *\n    62→     * @param request\n    63→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    64→     * @param responce\n    65→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    66→     **/\n    67→    @Override\n    68→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    69→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    70→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    71→        String symbol = null;\n    72→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    73→\n    74→        try {\n    75→            // TradeJDBC uses prepared statements so I am going to make use of\n    76→            // it's code.\n    77→            TradeDirect trade = new TradeDirect();\n    78→            trade.getConnPublic();\n    79→\n    80→            output.append(\"<html><head><title>PingServlet2DB.</title></head>\"\n    81→                    + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">PingServlet2DB:</FONT><HR><FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \" + initTime);\n    82→            hitCount++;\n    83→            output.append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \" + hitCount);\n    84→            output.append(\"<HR></body></html>\");\n    85→            out.println(output.toString());\n    86→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    87→            Log.error(e, \"PingServlet2DB -- error getting connection to the database\", symbol);\n    88→            res.sendError(500, \"PingServlet2DB Exception caught: \" + e.toString());\n    89→        }\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    /**\n    93→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n    94→     *\n    95→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n    96→     **/\n    97→    @Override\n    98→    public String getServletInfo() {\n    99→        return \"Basic JDBC Read using a prepared statment, makes use of TradeJDBC class\";\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    /**\n   103→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   104→     *\n   105→     * @param config\n   106→     *            ServletConfig:\n   107→     **/\n   108→    @Override\n   109→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   110→        super.init(config);\n   111→        hitCount = 0;\n   112→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   113→    }\n   114→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"25b3c349-21f1-4106-a20b-9bd10cc51064"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014sue9AcjKxmPMSFRr6o4cD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    21→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    22→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    23→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    24→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    26→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→/**\n    35→ *\n    36→ * PingJDBCReadPrepStmt uses a prepared statement for database read access. This\n    37→ * primative uses\n    38→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirect} to set the\n    39→ * price of a random stock (generated by\n    40→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig}) through the use\n    41→ * of prepared statements.\n    42→ *\n    43→ */\n    44→\n    45→@WebServlet(name = \"PingJDBCRead\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingJDBCRead\" })\n    46→public class PingJDBCRead extends HttpServlet {\n    47→\n    48→  @Inject\n    49→  @TradeJDBC\n    50→  TradeServices trade;\n    51→  \n    52→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -8810390150632488526L;\n    53→    private static String initTime;\n    54→    private static int hitCount;\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n    58→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n    59→     *\n    60→     * @param res\n    61→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n    62→     * @param res2\n    63→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n    64→     */\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    67→        doGet(req, res);\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    /**\n    71→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    72→     * requests.\n    73→     *\n    74→     * @param request\n    75→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    76→     * @param responce\n    77→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    78→     **/\n    79→    @Override\n    80→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    81→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    82→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    83→        String symbol = null;\n    84→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    85→\n    86→        try {\n    87→            // TradeJDBC uses prepared statements so I am going to make use of\n    88→            // it's code.\n    89→            \n    90→            symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n    91→\n    92→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n    93→            int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    94→            for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    95→                quoteData = trade.getQuote(symbol);\n    96→            }\n    97→\n    98→            output.append(\"<html><head><title>Ping JDBC Read w/ Prepared Stmt.</title></head>\"\n    99→                    + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping JDBC Read w/ Prep Stmt:</FONT><HR><FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Init time : \"\n   100→                    + initTime);\n   101→            hitCount++;\n   102→            output.append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \" + hitCount);\n   103→            output.append(\"<HR>Quote Information <BR><BR>: \" + quoteData.toHTML());\n   104→            output.append(\"<HR></body></html>\");\n   105→            out.println(output.toString());\n   106→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   107→            Log.error(e, \"PingJDBCRead w/ Prep Stmt -- error getting quote for symbol\", symbol);\n   108→            res.sendError(500, \"PingJDBCRead Exception caught: \" + e.toString());\n   109→        }\n   110→\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n   115→     *\n   116→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n   117→     **/\n   118→    @Override\n   119→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   120→        return \"Basic JDBC Read using a prepared statment, makes use of TradeJDBC class\";\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @param config\n   127→     *            ServletConfig:\n   128→     **/\n   129→    @Override\n   130→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   131→        super.init(config);\n   132→        hitCount = 0;\n   133→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   134→    }\n   135→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"f21e6f4c-3ac6-464a-810d-ef785d248673"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019uUmzeqgtVyhTRDDM6nNAz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.prims;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    22→import javax.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    23→import javax.servlet.ServletException;\n    24→import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    25→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    26→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    27→import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirect;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    34→\n    35→/**\n    36→ *\n    37→ * PingJDBCReadPrepStmt uses a prepared statement for database update. Statement\n    38→ * parameters are set dynamically on each request. This primative uses\n    39→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirect} to set the\n    40→ * price of a random stock (generated by\n    41→ * {@link com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig}) through the use\n    42→ * of prepared statements.\n    43→ *\n    44→ */\n    45→@WebServlet(name = \"PingJDBCWrite\", urlPatterns = { \"/servlet/PingJDBCWrite\" })\n    46→public class PingJDBCWrite extends HttpServlet {\n    47→\n    48→  @Inject\n    49→  @TradeJDBC\n    50→  TradeDirect trade;\n    51→  \n    52→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -4938035109655376503L;\n    53→    private static String initTime;\n    54→    private static int hitCount;\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * this is the main method of the servlet that will service all get\n    58→     * requests.\n    59→     *\n    60→     * @param request\n    61→     *            HttpServletRequest\n    62→     * @param responce\n    63→     *            HttpServletResponce\n    64→     **/\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    67→\n    68→        String symbol = null;\n    69→        BigDecimal newPrice;\n    70→        StringBuffer output = new StringBuffer(100);\n    71→        res.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n    72→        java.io.PrintWriter out = res.getWriter();\n    73→\n    74→        try {\n    75→            // get a random symbol to update and a random price.\n    76→            symbol = TradeConfig.rndSymbol();\n    77→            newPrice = TradeConfig.getRandomPriceChangeFactor();\n    78→\n    79→            \n    80→            // update the price of our symbol\n    81→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = null;\n    82→            int iter = TradeConfig.getPrimIterations();\n    83→            for (int ii = 0; ii < iter; ii++) {\n    84→                quoteData = trade.updateQuotePriceVolumeInt(symbol, newPrice, 100.0, false);\n    85→            }\n    86→\n    87→            // write the output\n    88→            output.append(\"<html><head><title>Ping JDBC Write w/ Prepared Stmt.</title></head>\"\n    89→                    + \"<body><HR><FONT size=\\\"+2\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\">Ping JDBC Write w/ Prep Stmt:</FONT><FONT size=\\\"-1\\\" color=\\\"#000066\\\"><HR>Init time : \"\n    90→                    + initTime);\n    91→            hitCount++;\n    92→            output.append(\"<BR>Hit Count: \" + hitCount);\n    93→            output.append(\"<HR>Update Information<BR>\");\n    94→            output.append(\"<BR>\" + quoteData.toHTML() + \"<HR></FONT></BODY></HTML>\");\n    95→            out.println(output.toString());\n    96→\n    97→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    98→            Log.error(e, \"PingJDBCWrite -- error updating quote for symbol\", symbol);\n    99→            res.sendError(500, \"PingJDBCWrite Exception caught: \" + e.toString());\n   100→        }\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    /**\n   104→     * returns a string of information about the servlet\n   105→     *\n   106→     * @return info String: contains info about the servlet\n   107→     **/\n   108→    @Override\n   109→    public String getServletInfo() {\n   110→        return \"Basic JDBC Write using a prepared statment makes use of TradeJDBC code.\";\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * called when the class is loaded to initialize the servlet\n   115→     *\n   116→     * @param config\n   117→     *            ServletConfig:\n   118→     **/\n   119→    @Override\n   120→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n   121→        super.init(config);\n   122→        initTime = new java.util.Date().toString();\n   123→        hitCount = 0;\n   124→\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    /**\n   128→     * forwards post requests to the doGet method Creation date: (11/6/2000\n   129→     * 10:52:39 AM)\n   130→     *\n   131→     * @param res\n   132→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest\n   133→     * @param res2\n   134→     *            javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse\n   135→     */\n   136→    @Override\n   137→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   138→        doGet(req, res);\n   139→    }\n   140→}\n   141→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"cd46cac0-f7f0-49c7-b1eb-49f535b240de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DseLNkknB8GFZfACicXm7b","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Complete File Contents\n\nBelow are the complete contents of all 20 requested Java files from the DayTrader application:\n\n---\n\n### 1. TradeServices.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeServices.java`\n\nThis is the main interface defining all business methods for the Trade online broker application. It includes methods for:\n- Market operations: `getMarketSummary()`\n- Trading operations: `buy()`, `sell()`, `createOrder()`, `completeOrder()`, `cancelOrder()`\n- Quote operations: `createQuote()`, `getQuote()`, `getAllQuotes()`, `updateQuotePriceVolume()`\n- Account operations: `login()`, `logout()`, `register()`, `getAccountData()`, `getAccountProfileData()`, `updateAccountProfile()`\n- Portfolio operations: `getHoldings()`, `getHolding()`, `getOrders()`, `getClosedOrders()`\n\nThe interface has 338 lines and is implemented by both EJB and direct JDBC implementations.\n\n---\n\n### 2. AccountDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity (286 lines) representing a trading account with:\n- Fields: accountID, loginCount, logoutCount, lastLogin, creationDate, balance, openBalance, profileID\n- Relationships: OneToMany with Orders and Holdings, OneToOne with AccountProfile\n- Bean validation constraints: @NotNull, @PositiveOrZero, @PastOrPresent\n- Business logic: `login()` and `logout()` methods\n\n---\n\n### 3. AccountProfileDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountProfileDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity (185 lines) for user profile information:\n- Fields: userID (PK), password, fullName, address, email, creditCard\n- Validation: @NotNull, @NotBlank, @Email\n- OneToOne relationship with AccountDataBean\n\n---\n\n### 4. HoldingDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity (205 lines) representing stock holdings:\n- Fields: holdingID (PK), quantity, purchasePrice, purchaseDate, quoteID\n- Relationships: ManyToOne with Account (LAZY) and Quote (EAGER)\n- Validation: @NotNull, @Positive, @PastOrPresent\n\n---\n\n### 5. OrderDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity (340 lines) for buy/sell orders:\n- Fields: orderID (PK), orderType, orderStatus, openDate, completionDate, quantity, price, orderFee\n- Relationships: ManyToOne with Account and Quote, OneToOne with Holding\n- Named queries for finding orders by various criteria\n- Business methods: `isBuy()`, `isSell()`, `isOpen()`, `isCompleted()`, `isCancelled()`, `cancel()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. QuoteDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java`\n\nJPA entity (213 lines) for stock quotes:\n- Fields: symbol (PK), companyName, volume, price, open1, low, high, change1\n- Named queries: `allQuotes` and `quoteForUpdate` (with FOR UPDATE lock)\n- Validation: @NotNull, @NotBlank, @Positive\n\n---\n\n### 7. MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java`\n\nNon-entity bean (287 lines) for market summary data:\n- Fields: TSIA, openTSIA, volume, topGainers, topLosers, summaryDate, gainPercent\n- Methods: `toJSON()` for JSON serialization\n- Calculates market index and tracks top performing stocks\n\n---\n\n### 8. RunStatsDataBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java`\n\nSimple bean (295 lines) for runtime statistics:\n- Tracks: tradeUserCount, newUserCount, sumLoginCount, sumLogoutCount, holdingCount, orderCount, buyOrderCount, sellOrderCount, cancelledOrderCount, openOrderCount, deletedOrderCount\n\n---\n\n### 9. TradeSLSBBean.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java`\n\nStateless EJB implementation (619 lines) of TradeServices:\n- Uses JPA EntityManager for database operations\n- JMS integration for asynchronous order processing\n- Transaction management with @TransactionAttribute\n- Resources: QueueConnectionFactory, TopicConnectionFactory, EntityManager\n- Implements all TradeServices methods using EJB3 patterns\n\n---\n\n### 10. MarketSummarySingleton.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java`\n\nSingleton EJB (139 lines) for cached market summary:\n- @Schedule annotation for automatic updates every 20 seconds\n- Read/write locks for concurrent access\n- CDI events for notifications\n- Calculates TSIA, volume, top gainers/losers from database\n\n---\n\n### 11. TradeDirect.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirect.java`\n\nDirect JDBC implementation (1838 lines) of TradeServices:\n- Uses raw JDBC with DataSource\n- Manual connection and transaction management\n- JMS integration for messaging\n- All SQL statements as string constants\n- Implements same TradeServices interface as EJB version\n\n---\n\n### 12. QuoteResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java`\n\nJAX-RS REST endpoint (85 lines) for quote retrieval:\n- Path: `/quotes`\n- Supports GET and POST methods\n- Accepts comma-separated symbols\n- Returns JSON array of QuoteDataBean objects\n- Uses CDI injection for TradeServices\n\n---\n\n### 13. JAXRSApplication.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/JAXRSApplication.java`\n\nJAX-RS application configuration (28 lines):\n- @ApplicationPath(\"/rest\")\n- Extends javax.ws.rs.core.Application\n\n---\n\n### 14. BroadcastResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/BroadcastResource.java`\n\nJAX-RS SSE (Server-Sent Events) endpoint (71 lines):\n- Path: `/broadcastevents`\n- Implements real-time quote updates via SSE\n- Uses CDI async events with @ObservesAsync\n- Broadcasts recent quote price changes to registered clients\n\n---\n\n### 15. TradeAppServlet.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeAppServlet.java`\n\nMain application servlet (221 lines):\n- URL: `/app`\n- Handles actions: login, register, quotes, buy, sell, portfolio, logout, home, account, update_profile, mksummary\n- HTTP/2 push support for images\n- Session management\n- Dispatches to TradeServletAction for business logic\n\n---\n\n### 16. TradeConfigServlet.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeConfigServlet.java`\n\nConfiguration management servlet (293 lines):\n- URL: `/config`\n- Actions: updateConfig, resetTrade, buildDB, buildDBTables\n- Updates TradeConfig runtime parameters\n- Database initialization and table creation\n- Supports DB2, Derby, and Oracle DDL files\n\n---\n\n### 17. TradeScenarioServlet.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeScenarioServlet.java`\n\nBenchmark/load testing servlet (298 lines):\n- URL: `/scenario`\n- Emulates population of web users\n- Random operations based on scenario mix\n- Actions: quote, account, update profile, home, login, logout, portfolio, register, buy, sell\n- Maintains buy/sell deficit tracking\n\n---\n\n### 18. TradeServletAction.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeServletAction.java`\n\nServlet action handler (654 lines):\n- @SessionScoped CDI bean\n- Methods for all trading operations\n- JSP forwarding/dispatching\n- Error handling and validation\n- Injects TradeServices implementation based on runtime mode\n\n---\n\n### 19. TradeWebContextListener.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TradeWebContextListener.java`\n\nApplication lifecycle listener (117 lines):\n- Loads configuration from `daytrader.properties` file\n- Supports environment variable overrides\n- Initializes: RUNTIME_MODE, ORDER_PROCESSING_MODE, MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES, PUBLISH_QUOTES, DISPLAY_ORDER_ALERTS, WEB_INTERFACE, LIST_QUOTE_PRICE_CHANGE_FREQUENCY\n\n---\n\n### 20. TradeConfig.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeConfig.java`\n\nConfiguration management class (753 lines):\n- Runtime modes: EJB3, DIRECT, SESSION_TO_DIRECT\n- Order processing modes: SYNCH, ASYNCH, ASYNCH_2PHASE\n- Web interface types: JSP, JSP_Images, JSP_Images_HTTP2\n- Trade scenario mixes and action weights\n- Random data generation utilities\n- JSP page mappings\n- Global configuration parameters\n\n---\n\nAll files follow the Apache License 2.0 and are part of IBM's DayTrader sample application, demonstrating Jakarta EE/Java EE enterprise patterns and practices."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"fb55647e-d693-4930-9868-13ef7e8fe2ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017rnns7ck3qWyEfKqYWUHSE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI have successfully read and returned the complete contents of all requested files from the DayTrader project. Here's what was retrieved:\n\n### 1. **Interfaces Directory** (/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/)\n- **TradeJDBC.java** - Qualifier annotation for JDBC implementations\n- **TradeEJB.java** - Qualifier annotation for EJB implementations  \n- **TradeDB.java** - Interface for database operations (resetTrade, checkDBProductName)\n- **Trace.java** - Interceptor binding annotation for tracing\n- **QuotePriceChange.java** - Qualifier annotation for quote price change events\n- **MarketSummaryUpdate.java** - Qualifier annotation for market summary updates\n- **RuntimeMode.java** - Qualifier annotation with runtime mode value\n- **TradeSession2Direct.java** - Qualifier annotation for session-to-direct mode\n- **TradeServices.java** - Main business interface defining all trade operations (buy, sell, quotes, accounts, orders, etc.)\n\n### 2. **Util Directory** (/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/)\n- **TradeConfig.java** - Configuration class with runtime parameters, constants, and utility methods\n- **TraceInterceptor.java** - CDI interceptor for method tracing\n- **MDBStats.java** - Statistics tracking for message-driven beans\n- **RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java** - Maintains list of recent quote price changes for WebSocket/SSE\n- **TimerStat.java** - Timer statistics bean with min/max/avg calculations\n- **Diagnostics.java** - Diagnostic utilities for memory and latency testing\n- **FinancialUtils.java** - Financial calculation utilities (gains, percentages, HTML formatting)\n- **KeyBlock.java** - Iterator-based block of sequential keys\n- **Log.java** - Logging utility wrapper\n- **TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java** - CDI annotation literal for runtime mode selection\n\n### 3. **Web/JSF Directory** (/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/jsf/)\n- **QuoteJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for quote operations\n- **OrderDataJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for order data display\n- **PortfolioJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for portfolio display and sell operations\n- **QuoteData.java** - JSF data transfer object for quote information\n- **MarketSummaryJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for market summary display\n- **AccountDataJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for account home page\n- **HoldingData.java** - JSF data transfer object for holding information\n- **JSFLoginFilter.java** - Servlet filter for JSF authentication\n- **TradeAppJSF.java** - Session-scoped JSF bean for login/logout/register operations\n- **OrderData.java** - JSF data transfer object for order information\n- **TradeConfigJSF.java** - JSF managed bean for configuration management\n- **LoginValidator.java** - JSF validator for username format\n\n### 4. **Web/WebSocket Directory** (/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/websocket/)\n- **QuotePriceChangeListEncoder.java** - WebSocket encoder for quote price change lists\n- **JsonEncoder.java** - Generic JSON encoder for WebSocket messages\n- **JsonMessage.java** - Simple key-value message class\n- **MarketSummaryWebSocket.java** - WebSocket endpoint for market summary updates\n- **ActionDecoder.java** - WebSocket decoder for action messages\n- **JsonDecoder.java** - Generic JSON decoder for WebSocket messages\n- **ActionMessage.java** - Action message class with JSON parsing\n\n### 5. **Web/Prims Directory** (Sample files as requested)\n- **PingServlet.java** - Basic servlet testing HTML generation\n- **PingServlet2DB.java** - Servlet testing database connection\n- **PingJDBCRead.java** - Servlet testing JDBC read with prepared statements\n- **PingJDBCWrite.java** - Servlet testing JDBC write with prepared statements\n\nAll files have been read completely and contain the full source code including headers, imports, class definitions, methods, and implementation details. The project appears to be a Jakarta EE-based stock trading application with support for JSF, WebSockets, CDI, and multiple persistence strategies."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"4b14d559-9eed-4734-a99d-a84aec9e28b1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EhzWa66SQ2r21tetRU2sU1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Complete File Contents Report\n\nHere are the complete contents of all requested files from the DayTrader application:\n\n---\n\n### 1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml\n\nThis is the main web application deployment descriptor (215 lines). It configures:\n- JSF servlet and mappings (Faces Servlet)\n- JSF configuration parameters (PROJECT_STAGE, STATE_SAVING_METHOD, DEFAULT_SUFFIX)\n- Session timeout (30 minutes)\n- Welcome files (index.html, index.jsp, index.faces)\n- Error pages for exceptions and 500 errors\n- Security constraints and roles (commented out - includes testing, AllAuthenticated, grp1-5, webSecOnly roles)\n- BASIC authentication (commented out)\n\n---\n\n### 2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/beans.xml\n\nCDI beans configuration file (22 lines) using:\n- Jakarta EE namespace (http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee)\n- beans_1_1.xsd schema\n- Bean discovery mode: \"all\"\n\n---\n\n### 3. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/faces-config.xml\n\nJSF configuration file (120 lines) defining navigation rules for:\n- welcome.xhtml → tradehome.xhtml or welcome.xhtml\n- register.xhtml → tradehome.xhtml or register.xhtml\n- tradehome.xhtml → quote.xhtml or register.xhtml\n- account.xhtml → quote.xhtml, account.xhtml, or welcome.xhtml\n- portfolio.xhtml → quote.xhtml or order.xhtml\n- marketSummary.xhtml → quote.xhtml\n- configure.xhtml → welcome.xhtml, config.xhtml, configure.xhtml, or configure.xhtml\n- order.xhtml → quote.xhtml\n- quote.xhtml → order.xhtml\n\n---\n\n### 4. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml\n\nLiberty server configuration (76 lines) including:\n- **Features**: ejb-3.2, servlet-4.0, jsf-2.3, jpa-2.2, mdb-3.2, wasJmsServer-1.0, wasJmsClient-2.0, cdi-2.0, websocket-1.1, concurrent-1.0, jsonp-1.1, jsonb-1.0, beanValidation-2.0, jaxrs-2.1, ssl-1.0\n- **DataSource**: H2 database at jdbc/TradeDataSource with connection pool (100 connections)\n- **JMS Configuration**: \n  - TradeBrokerQueue (Queue)\n  - TradeStreamerTopic (Topic)\n  - Connection factories for both\n- **Activation specs** for DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB\n\n---\n\n### 5. Persistence Configuration\n\n**File**: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/classes/META-INF/persistence.xml\n\n(Also found at: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/classes/persistence.xml)\n\nJPA persistence unit configuration (34 lines):\n- Persistence unit name: \"daytrader\"\n- Transaction type: JTA\n- Data source: jdbc/TradeDataSource\n- Entity classes: AccountDataBean, AccountProfileDataBean, HoldingDataBean, OrderDataBean, QuoteDataBean\n- Exclude unlisted classes: true\n- Shared cache mode: NONE\n\n---\n\n### 6. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/TradeDirectDBUtils.java\n\nDatabase utility class (472 lines) that:\n- Implements TradeDB interface\n- Provides database initialization and population methods\n- Handles DDL file parsing and table recreation\n- Implements resetTrade() for database cleanup\n- Creates quotes and registers users for testing\n- Uses JDBC directly with injected DataSource\n- Scope: @ApplicationScoped\n\n---\n\n### 7. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/KeySequenceDirect.java\n\nKey sequence generator for primary keys (114 lines):\n- Manages blocks of primary keys for entities\n- Uses a HashMap to cache key blocks\n- Allocates keys in blocks (KEYBLOCKSIZE at a time)\n- Uses \"SELECT FOR UPDATE\" for database-level locking\n- Creates keygenejb entries if they don't exist\n- Synchronized method for thread safety\n\n---\n\n### 8. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrder.java\n\nAsynchronous order processing Runnable (71 lines):\n- Scope: @Dependent\n- Implements Runnable interface\n- Uses UserTransaction for transaction management\n- Completes orders asynchronously by calling tradeService.completeOrder()\n- Handles rollback on exceptions\n\n---\n\n### 9. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/direct/AsyncOrderSubmitter.java\n\nSubmitter for asynchronous orders (40 lines):\n- Scope: @RequestScoped\n- Uses ManagedExecutorService for async execution\n- Submits AsyncOrder tasks and returns Future\n- Sets order properties before submission\n\n---\n\n### 10. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrder.java\n\nScheduled asynchronous order processor (59 lines):\n- Scope: @Dependent\n- Implements Runnable interface\n- Uses CDI to select appropriate TradeServices implementation based on runtime mode\n- Completes orders without explicit transaction management (relies on container)\n\n---\n\n### 11. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java\n\nScheduled order submitter (41 lines):\n- Scope: @RequestScoped\n- Uses ManagedScheduledExecutorService\n- Schedules order completion with 500ms delay\n- Returns Future for tracking\n\n---\n\n### 12. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java\n\nStateless Session Bean wrapper (237 lines):\n- @Stateless EJB with container-managed transactions\n- Annotated with @TradeSession2Direct and @RuntimeMode(\"Session to Direct\")\n- Wraps TradeDirect implementation\n- Sets inSession flag on delegate calls\n- Implements all TradeServices methods\n- Uses AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter for async order completion\n- Throws UnsupportedOperationException for pingTwoPhase, investmentReturn, and setInSession\n\n---\n\n### 13. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java\n\nMessage-Driven Bean for order processing (159 lines):\n- Listens to jms/TradeBrokerQueue\n- Handles \"neworder\" and \"ping\" commands\n- Container-managed transactions with REQUIRED attribute\n- Uses CDI to select TradeServices implementation\n- Tracks MDB statistics (timing, count)\n- Logs statistics every 10,000 messages\n- Sets rollback on exceptions\n\n---\n\n### 14. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java\n\nMessage-Driven Bean for quote updates (123 lines):\n- Listens to jms/TradeStreamerTopic (Topic, non-durable)\n- Handles \"updateQuote\" and \"ping\" commands\n- Container-managed transactions with REQUIRED attribute\n- Tracks MDB statistics\n- Logs statistics every 10,000 messages\n- Sets rollback on exceptions\n\n---\n\n### 15. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/OrdersAlertFilter.java\n\nServlet filter for checking closed orders (116 lines):\n- @WebFilter on \"/app\" URL pattern\n- Checks for closed orders and adds to request attributes\n- Uses CDI to inject TradeServices implementation\n- Only runs when displayOrderAlerts is enabled\n- Runs diagnostics check on each request\n\n---\n\n### 16. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/PrimFilter.java\n\nSimple servlet filter (68 lines):\n- @WebFilter on \"/drive/*\" URL pattern\n- Only runs diagnostics check\n- Minimal implementation\n\n---\n\n### 17. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/servlet/TestServlet.java\n\nTest servlet for creating sample quotes (122 lines):\n- @WebServlet at \"/TestServlet\"\n- Creates 10 test quotes (s:0 through s:9)\n- Uses CDI to inject TradeServices\n- Contains commented-out test code for account and holdings\n\n---\n\n## Web Resources in src/main/webapp/\n\n### XHTML Files (15 files):\n1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/PingCDIJSF.xhtml\n2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader_