{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VCCb6z1pVtUmF2kE17n1tM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create REST controllers","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2. Create the following REST controller files with COMPLETE content. Write them using the Write tool.\n\nThe project root is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\nBase package: com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader\n\nThe application has a TradeService (in service package) that has methods:\n- getMarketSummary() returns MarketSummaryDataBean\n- buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode) returns OrderDataBean\n- sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode) returns OrderDataBean\n- completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase) returns OrderDataBean\n- createQuote(symbol, companyName, price) returns QuoteDataBean\n- getQuote(symbol) returns QuoteDataBean\n- getAllQuotes() returns Collection<QuoteDataBean>\n- updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, changeFactor, sharesTraded) returns QuoteDataBean\n- login(userID, password) returns AccountDataBean\n- logout(userID)\n- register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance) returns AccountDataBean\n- getOrders(userID) returns Collection<OrderDataBean>\n- getClosedOrders(userID) returns Collection<OrderDataBean>\n- getHoldings(userID) returns Collection<HoldingDataBean>\n- getHolding(holdingID) returns HoldingDataBean\n- getAccountData(userID) returns AccountDataBean\n- getAccountProfileData(userID) returns AccountProfileDataBean\n- updateAccountProfile(profileData) returns AccountProfileDataBean\n\nAlso TradeConfig is a utility class with static methods/fields for configuration. TradeConfig has:\n- static int MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES\n- static int SYNCH = 0\n- static methods: setRunTimeMode, getRunTimeModeNames, etc.\n- There is a TradeDBService (see below) with resetTrade() and buildDB() methods.\n\n### File 1: HealthController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/HealthController.java\nSimple health check:\n- GET /api/health -> {\"status\":\"UP\"}\n\n### File 2: QuoteController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/QuoteController.java\nQuote operations:\n- GET /api/quotes -> getAllQuotes()\n- GET /api/quotes/{symbol} -> getQuote(symbol)\n- POST /api/quotes -> createQuote (body: {\"symbol\",\"companyName\",\"price\"})\n\n### File 3: AccountController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/AccountController.java\nAccount operations:\n- POST /api/account/register -> register (body: {\"userID\",\"password\",\"fullname\",\"address\",\"email\",\"creditcard\",\"openBalance\"})\n- POST /api/account/login -> login (body: {\"userID\",\"password\"})\n- POST /api/account/logout -> logout (body: {\"userID\"})\n- GET /api/account/{userID} -> getAccountData\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/profile -> getAccountProfileData\n- PUT /api/account/{userID}/profile -> updateAccountProfile (body: AccountProfileDataBean fields)\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/holdings -> getHoldings\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/orders -> getOrders\n\n### File 4: TradeController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/TradeController.java\nTrade operations:\n- POST /api/trade/buy -> buy (body: {\"userID\",\"symbol\",\"quantity\"}) - use TradeConfig.SYNCH for orderProcessingMode\n- POST /api/trade/sell -> sell (body: {\"userID\",\"holdingID\"}) - use TradeConfig.SYNCH\n- GET /api/trade/orders/{userID}/closed -> getClosedOrders\n\n### File 5: MarketController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/MarketController.java\nMarket operations:\n- GET /api/market/summary -> getMarketSummary()\n\n### File 6: ConfigController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/ConfigController.java\nConfiguration:\n- GET /api/config -> return current config as JSON (runtimeMode, orderProcessingMode, maxUsers, maxQuotes, etc.)\n- POST /api/config/buildDB -> calls tradeDBService.buildDB() -> returns {\"status\":\"Success\",\"result\":\"...\"}\n- POST /api/config/resetTrade -> calls tradeDBService.resetTrade() -> returns RunStatsDataBean as JSON\n\nUse @Autowired for TradeService and TradeDBService. All controllers should use @RestController.\nHandle exceptions with try-catch returning appropriate error responses.\nUse @RequestBody for JSON input, Map<String,Object> for flexible input parsing.\n\nWrite all 6 files now using the Write tool. Use FULL absolute paths.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":511,"cache_read_input_tokens":97056,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":511,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4697},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"f37d77ba-da1b-49f5-8792-13b661e94230"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2. I need you to create the following files. Write each file COMPLETELY.\n\nThe project root is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\n\nThe source root for Java is: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/\n\n### File 1: Spring Boot Main Application\nCreate: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@EnableAsync\npublic class DayTraderApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### File 2: AccountDataBean.java entity\nMigrate from javax.persistence -> jakarta.persistence, remove javax.ejb.EJBException -> use RuntimeException.\nThe entity has: @Entity(name=\"accountejb\"), @Table(name=\"accountejb\"), fields: accountID (Integer, PK with @TableGenerator/@GeneratedValue TABLE), loginCount, logoutCount, lastLogin, creationDate, balance, openBalance. Relations: @OneToMany orders, @OneToMany holdings, @OneToOne profile. @Transient profileID. Methods: login(password), logout().\n\nReplace `import javax.ejb.EJBException` with `throw new RuntimeException(...)`.\nReplace all `javax.persistence.*` with `jakarta.persistence.*`.\nReplace all `javax.validation.*` with `jakarta.validation.*`.\nKeep the rest of the business logic identical.\n\n### File 3: AccountProfileDataBean.java entity\nMigrate javax -> jakarta. Fields: userID (PK, String), passwd, fullName, address, email, creditCard. @OneToOne(mappedBy=\"profile\") account.\n\n### File 4: QuoteDataBean.java entity\nMigrate javax -> jakarta. @Entity(name=\"quoteejb\"), @Table(name=\"quoteejb\"). Fields: symbol (PK, String), companyName, volume, price, open1, low, high, change1. Named queries: allQuotes, quoteForUpdate.\nAdd @JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown=true) from com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.\n\n### File 5: HoldingDataBean.java entity\nMigrate javax -> jakarta. @Entity(name=\"holdingejb\"), @Table(name=\"holdingejb\"). Fields: holdingID (Integer, PK with @TableGenerator), quantity, purchasePrice, purchaseDate, quoteID (@Transient). Relations: @ManyToOne account, @ManyToOne quote.\nAdd @JsonIgnoreProperties on relationships to avoid circular references:\n- account field: @JsonIgnoreProperties({\"orders\",\"holdings\",\"profile\"})\n- quote field: no change needed\n\n### File 6: OrderDataBean.java entity\nMigrate javax -> jakarta. @Entity(name=\"orderejb\"), @Table(name=\"orderejb\"). Fields: orderID (Integer, PK with @TableGenerator), orderType, orderStatus, openDate, completionDate, quantity, price, orderFee. Relations: @ManyToOne account, @ManyToOne quote, @OneToOne holding. @Transient symbol. Named queries for various finds.\nAdd @JsonIgnoreProperties on relationship fields to avoid circular refs:\n- account: @JsonIgnoreProperties({\"orders\",\"holdings\",\"profile\"})\n- quote: no change\n- holding: @JsonIgnoreProperties({\"account\",\"quote\"})\n\nWrite all 6 files now using the Write tool. Use FULL absolute paths."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UPUFVrPCXmmc5QZ5xD6j1Y","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"651af010-7ef1-4349-b4a2-bd6abfd7f30e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2. Create the following files with COMPLETE content. Write them using the Write tool.\n\nThe project root is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\nBase package: com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader\n\n### File 1: QuoteRepository.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/repositories/QuoteRepository.java\nSpring Data JPA repository for QuoteDataBean. The entity name is \"quoteejb\", table is \"quoteejb\", PK is String (symbol).\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Lock;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\nimport jakarta.persistence.LockModeType;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface QuoteRepository extends JpaRepository<QuoteDataBean, String> {\n    \n    @Lock(LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE)\n    @Query(\"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q WHERE q.symbol = :symbol\")\n    QuoteDataBean findBySymbolForUpdate(@Param(\"symbol\") String symbol);\n\n    @Query(\"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q ORDER BY q.change1 DESC\")\n    List<QuoteDataBean> findAllOrderByChangeDesc();\n}\n```\n\n### File 2: AccountRepository.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/repositories/AccountRepository.java\nFor AccountDataBean entity (name=\"accountejb\", table=\"accountejb\", PK Integer accountID).\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories;\n\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface AccountRepository extends JpaRepository<AccountDataBean, Integer> {\n}\n```\n\n### File 3: AccountProfileRepository.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/repositories/AccountProfileRepository.java\nFor AccountProfileDataBean entity (name=\"accountprofileejb\", table=\"accountprofileejb\", PK String userID).\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories;\n\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface AccountProfileRepository extends JpaRepository<AccountProfileDataBean, String> {\n}\n```\n\n### File 4: HoldingRepository.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/repositories/HoldingRepository.java\nFor HoldingDataBean entity (name=\"holdingejb\", table=\"holdingejb\", PK Integer holdingID).\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface HoldingRepository extends JpaRepository<HoldingDataBean, Integer> {\n    @Query(\"SELECT h FROM holdingejb h WHERE h.account.profile.userID = :userID\")\n    List<HoldingDataBean> findByAccountProfileUserID(@Param(\"userID\") String userID);\n}\n```\n\n### File 5: OrderRepository.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/repositories/OrderRepository.java\nFor OrderDataBean entity (name=\"orderejb\", table=\"orderejb\", PK Integer orderID).\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Modifying;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface OrderRepository extends JpaRepository<OrderDataBean, Integer> {\n    \n    @Query(\"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.account.profile.userID = :userID\")\n    List<OrderDataBean> findByAccountProfileUserID(@Param(\"userID\") String userID);\n    \n    @Query(\"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID = :userID\")\n    List<OrderDataBean> findClosedOrdersByUserID(@Param(\"userID\") String userID);\n    \n    @Modifying\n    @Query(\"UPDATE orderejb o SET o.orderStatus = 'completed' WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID = :userID\")\n    int completeClosedOrders(@Param(\"userID\") String userID);\n\n    @Query(\"SELECT COUNT(o) FROM orderejb o WHERE o.account.profile.userID = :userID\")\n    long countByUserID(@Param(\"userID\") String userID);\n}\n```\n\n### File 6: TradeService.java (the main Spring @Service replacing EJB TradeSLSBBean)\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/service/TradeService.java\n\nThis is the main service class, replacing the EJB TradeSLSBBean. It should be a @Service with @Transactional.\nIt implements all the business methods of the TradeServices interface.\n\nKey methods:\n- getMarketSummary() - queries top gainers/losers using QuoteRepository\n- buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode) - creates buy order, debits account\n- sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode) - creates sell order, credits account\n- completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase) - completes buy (creates holding) or sell (removes holding)\n- createQuote(symbol, companyName, price)\n- getQuote(symbol), getAllQuotes()\n- updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, changeFactor, sharesTraded)\n- login(userID, password), logout(userID)\n- register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance)\n- getOrders(userID), getClosedOrders(userID)\n- getHoldings(userID), getHolding(holdingID)\n- getAccountData(userID), getAccountProfileData(userID), updateAccountProfile(profileData)\n- createOrder(account, quote, holding, orderType, quantity) - helper\n- queueOrder, completeOrderAsync - simplified (just call completeOrder synchronously since we don't have JMS)\n- cancelOrder, orderCompleted\n- pingTwoPhase, investmentReturn, setInSession - stubs/simple implementations\n- getImpl() returns 0\n\nUse @Autowired for all repositories. Use @Transactional on all mutating methods.\nThe TradeConfig class is used for configuration constants.\nThe MarketSummaryDataBean is a simple POJO with TSIA, openTSIA, volume, topGainers, topLosers.\nThe FinancialUtils class has SCALE and ROUND constants.\n\nFor updateQuotePriceVolume, use the quoteRepository.findBySymbolForUpdate(symbol) method to get a pessimistic lock.\n\nFor order processing modes: since we don't have JMS, always complete synchronously regardless of mode (call completeOrder directly).\n\nFor the login method - find profile, find account, validate password, increment loginCount.\nFor register - create profile, create account, persist both.\nFor getClosedOrders - find closed orders, mark them completed.\n\nWrite the complete service implementation. It should be comprehensive and handle all the business logic from TradeSLSBBean.\n\nWrite all 6 files now using the Write tool. Use FULL absolute paths."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014yjAHiGRHG7kVwHegw58sv","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"644cd322-2051-4cef-ba84-1ac6a70f79b1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE DayTrader application to Spring Boot 3.2. Create the following REST controller files with COMPLETE content. Write them using the Write tool.\n\nThe project root is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output\nBase package: com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader\n\nThe application has a TradeService (in service package) that has methods:\n- getMarketSummary() returns MarketSummaryDataBean\n- buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode) returns OrderDataBean\n- sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode) returns OrderDataBean\n- completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase) returns OrderDataBean\n- createQuote(symbol, companyName, price) returns QuoteDataBean\n- getQuote(symbol) returns QuoteDataBean\n- getAllQuotes() returns Collection<QuoteDataBean>\n- updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, changeFactor, sharesTraded) returns QuoteDataBean\n- login(userID, password) returns AccountDataBean\n- logout(userID)\n- register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance) returns AccountDataBean\n- getOrders(userID) returns Collection<OrderDataBean>\n- getClosedOrders(userID) returns Collection<OrderDataBean>\n- getHoldings(userID) returns Collection<HoldingDataBean>\n- getHolding(holdingID) returns HoldingDataBean\n- getAccountData(userID) returns AccountDataBean\n- getAccountProfileData(userID) returns AccountProfileDataBean\n- updateAccountProfile(profileData) returns AccountProfileDataBean\n\nAlso TradeConfig is a utility class with static methods/fields for configuration. TradeConfig has:\n- static int MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES\n- static int SYNCH = 0\n- static methods: setRunTimeMode, getRunTimeModeNames, etc.\n- There is a TradeDBService (see below) with resetTrade() and buildDB() methods.\n\n### File 1: HealthController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/HealthController.java\nSimple health check:\n- GET /api/health -> {\"status\":\"UP\"}\n\n### File 2: QuoteController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/QuoteController.java\nQuote operations:\n- GET /api/quotes -> getAllQuotes()\n- GET /api/quotes/{symbol} -> getQuote(symbol)\n- POST /api/quotes -> createQuote (body: {\"symbol\",\"companyName\",\"price\"})\n\n### File 3: AccountController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/AccountController.java\nAccount operations:\n- POST /api/account/register -> register (body: {\"userID\",\"password\",\"fullname\",\"address\",\"email\",\"creditcard\",\"openBalance\"})\n- POST /api/account/login -> login (body: {\"userID\",\"password\"})\n- POST /api/account/logout -> logout (body: {\"userID\"})\n- GET /api/account/{userID} -> getAccountData\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/profile -> getAccountProfileData\n- PUT /api/account/{userID}/profile -> updateAccountProfile (body: AccountProfileDataBean fields)\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/holdings -> getHoldings\n- GET /api/account/{userID}/orders -> getOrders\n\n### File 4: TradeController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/TradeController.java\nTrade operations:\n- POST /api/trade/buy -> buy (body: {\"userID\",\"symbol\",\"quantity\"}) - use TradeConfig.SYNCH for orderProcessingMode\n- POST /api/trade/sell -> sell (body: {\"userID\",\"holdingID\"}) - use TradeConfig.SYNCH\n- GET /api/trade/orders/{userID}/closed -> getClosedOrders\n\n### File 5: MarketController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/MarketController.java\nMarket operations:\n- GET /api/market/summary -> getMarketSummary()\n\n### File 6: ConfigController.java\nPath: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/ConfigController.java\nConfiguration:\n- GET /api/config -> return current config as JSON (runtimeMode, orderProcessingMode, maxUsers, maxQuotes, etc.)\n- POST /api/config/buildDB -> calls tradeDBService.buildDB() -> returns {\"status\":\"Success\",\"result\":\"...\"}\n- POST /api/config/resetTrade -> calls tradeDBService.resetTrade() -> returns RunStatsDataBean as JSON\n\nUse @Autowired for TradeService and TradeDBService. All controllers should use @RestController.\nHandle exceptions with try-catch returning appropriate error responses.\nUse @RequestBody for JSON input, Map<String,Object> for flexible input parsing.\n\nWrite all 6 files now using the Write tool. Use FULL absolute paths."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"2c1184d3-d9ef-4d1d-84c5-197821df8a6b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01XKTk7qccy9V161TXzkxmg8","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/HealthController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for health check endpoint\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/health\")\npublic class HealthController {\n\n    @GetMapping\n    public Map<String, String> health() {\n        Map<String, String> response = new HashMap<>();\n        response.put(\"status\", \"UP\");\n        return response;\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"3494e072-670d-4b59-8b17-02421f3cdf28"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_016ykmiyTyJb3UgjP2Cjnbr4","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/QuoteController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for quote operations\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/quotes\")\npublic class QuoteController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private TradeService tradeService;\n\n    @GetMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getAllQuotes() {\n        try {\n            Collection<QuoteDataBean> quotes = tradeService.getAllQuotes();\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(quotes);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{symbol}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getQuote(@PathVariable String symbol) {\n        try {\n            QuoteDataBean quote = tradeService.getQuote(symbol);\n            if (quote == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Quote not found for symbol: \" + symbol);\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n            }\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(quote);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<?> createQuote(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String symbol = (String) request.get(\"symbol\");\n            String companyName = (String) request.get(\"companyName\");\n            BigDecimal price;\n\n            Object priceObj = request.get(\"price\");\n            if (priceObj instanceof Number) {\n                price = new BigDecimal(priceObj.toString());\n            } else if (priceObj instanceof String) {\n                price = new BigDecimal((String) priceObj);\n            } else {\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid price format\");\n            }\n\n            if (symbol == null || companyName == null || price == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: symbol, companyName, price\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            QuoteDataBean quote = tradeService.createQuote(symbol, companyName, price);\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(quote);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"885e0565-7095-41e3-9134-9d662f5a3688"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_0112Bv45tMgUdYqpovFqDT5i","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/AccountController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for account operations\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/account\")\npublic class AccountController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private TradeService tradeService;\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> register(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n            String fullname = (String) request.get(\"fullname\");\n            String address = (String) request.get(\"address\");\n            String email = (String) request.get(\"email\");\n            String creditcard = (String) request.get(\"creditcard\");\n\n            BigDecimal openBalance;\n            Object balanceObj = request.get(\"openBalance\");\n            if (balanceObj instanceof Number) {\n                openBalance = new BigDecimal(balanceObj.toString());\n            } else if (balanceObj instanceof String) {\n                openBalance = new BigDecimal((String) balanceObj);\n            } else {\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid openBalance format\");\n            }\n\n            if (userID == null || password == null || fullname == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password, fullname\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(account);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> login(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n\n            if (userID == null || password == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(userID, password);\n            if (account == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Invalid credentials\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED).body(error);\n            }\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/logout\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> logout(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n\n            if (userID == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required field: userID\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            tradeService.logout(userID);\n            Map<String, String> response = new HashMap<>();\n            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n            response.put(\"message\", \"User logged out successfully\");\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n        try {\n            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n            if (account == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Account not found for userID: \" + userID);\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n            }\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountProfileData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n        try {\n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n            if (profile == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Profile not found for userID: \" + userID);\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n            }\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(profile);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PutMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> updateAccountProfile(@PathVariable String userID, @RequestBody AccountProfileDataBean profileData) {\n        try {\n            // Ensure the userID matches\n            if (profileData.getUserID() == null) {\n                profileData.setUserID(userID);\n            } else if (!userID.equals(profileData.getUserID())) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"UserID mismatch between path and body\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            AccountProfileDataBean updatedProfile = tradeService.updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedProfile);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/holdings\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getHoldings(@PathVariable String userID) {\n        try {\n            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = tradeService.getHoldings(userID);\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(holdings);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/orders\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getOrders(@PathVariable String userID) {\n        try {\n            Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = tradeService.getOrders(userID);\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(orders);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"4d350a10-3f2a-4e4d-a545-cc888fb1d851"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01B432htNE4pVSJXGf4Xfp2Z","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/TradeController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for trade operations\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/trade\")\npublic class TradeController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private TradeService tradeService;\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/buy\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> buy(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n            String symbol = (String) request.get(\"symbol\");\n\n            double quantity;\n            Object quantityObj = request.get(\"quantity\");\n            if (quantityObj instanceof Number) {\n                quantity = ((Number) quantityObj).doubleValue();\n            } else if (quantityObj instanceof String) {\n                quantity = Double.parseDouble((String) quantityObj);\n            } else {\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid quantity format\");\n            }\n\n            if (userID == null || symbol == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, symbol, quantity\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.buy(userID, symbol, quantity, TradeConfig.SYNCH);\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(order);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/sell\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> sell(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n        try {\n            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n\n            Integer holdingID;\n            Object holdingObj = request.get(\"holdingID\");\n            if (holdingObj instanceof Number) {\n                holdingID = ((Number) holdingObj).intValue();\n            } else if (holdingObj instanceof String) {\n                holdingID = Integer.parseInt((String) holdingObj);\n            } else {\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid holdingID format\");\n            }\n\n            if (userID == null || holdingID == null) {\n                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, holdingID\");\n                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n            }\n\n            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.sell(userID, holdingID, TradeConfig.SYNCH);\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(order);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/orders/{userID}/closed\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getClosedOrders(@PathVariable String userID) {\n        try {\n            Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = tradeService.getClosedOrders(userID);\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(orders);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"e01bd2ea-6e11-4409-b307-b4c42ca51343"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_011K5heBeyWTjTCoa7NvkrK9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/MarketController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.MarketSummaryDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for market operations\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/market\")\npublic class MarketController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private TradeService tradeService;\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/summary\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getMarketSummary() {\n        try {\n            MarketSummaryDataBean summary = tradeService.getMarketSummary();\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(summary);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"061ee7ee-c5e6-4e29-9fe0-9679282da854"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01EHspLG21rF3opzeJ9bN7zE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LSoxoXB44ReZg9aQetvniX","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/rest/ConfigController.java","content":"package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.RunStatsDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeDBService;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n/**\n * REST controller for configuration operations\n */\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/config\")\npublic class ConfigController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private TradeDBService tradeDBService;\n\n    @GetMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<?> getConfig() {\n        try {\n            Map<String, Object> config = new HashMap<>();\n            config.put(\"maxUsers\", TradeConfig.MAX_USERS);\n            config.put(\"maxQuotes\", TradeConfig.MAX_QUOTES);\n            config.put(\"orderProcessingMode\", TradeConfig.SYNCH);\n\n            // Add runtime mode information if available\n            try {\n                String[] modeNames = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames();\n                config.put(\"runtimeModeNames\", modeNames);\n            } catch (Exception e) {\n                // If method doesn't exist or fails, continue without it\n            }\n\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(config);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/buildDB\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> buildDB() {\n        try {\n            boolean result = tradeDBService.buildDB();\n            Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n            response.put(\"result\", result ? \"Database built successfully\" : \"Database build completed with warnings\");\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, Object> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"status\", \"Error\");\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/resetTrade\")\n    public ResponseEntity<?> resetTrade() {\n        try {\n            RunStatsDataBean stats = tradeDBService.resetTrade();\n            return ResponseEntity.ok(stats);\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1621,"cache_read_input_tokens":11007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1621,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5942},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rC7hmtAaQC1DcbyogvGHe","session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"2be8a54a-cf31-4961-a46c-261dd1320e90"}
