ip with AccountDataBean\n\n### File 4: QuoteDataBean.java Entity\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java`\n\nKey changes:\n- Migrated all `javax.persistence.*` imports to `jakarta.persistence.*`\n- Migrated all `javax.validation.*` imports to `jakarta.validation.*`\n- Added `@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown=true)` annotation from Jackson to handle JSON serialization\n- Preserved all named queries (allQuotes, quoteForUpdate)\n\n### File 5: HoldingDataBean.java Entity\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java`\n\nKey changes:\n- Migrated all `javax.persistence.*` imports to `jakarta.persistence.*`\n- Migrated all `javax.validation.*` imports to `jakarta.validation.*`\n- Added `@JsonIgnoreProperties({\"orders\", \"holdings\", \"profile\"})` on the account field to avoid circular references in JSON serialization\n- Preserved @ManyToOne relationships with AccountDataBean and QuoteDataBean\n\n### File 6: OrderDataBean.java Entity\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java`\n\nKey changes:\n- Migrated all `javax.persistence.*` imports to `jakarta.persistence.*`\n- Migrated all `javax.validation.*` imports to `jakarta.validation.*`\n- Added `@JsonIgnoreProperties({\"orders\", \"holdings\", \"profile\"})` on the account field\n- Added `@JsonIgnoreProperties({\"account\", \"quote\"})` on the holding field\n- Preserved all named queries and business logic methods (isBuy(), isSell(), isOpen(), isCompleted(), isCancelled(), cancel())\n\n## Key Migration Points Completed:\n\n1. **Jakarta EE Migration**: All `javax.persistence.*` replaced with `jakarta.persistence.*`\n2. **Validation Migration**: All `javax.validation.*` replaced with `jakarta.validation.*`\n3. **EJB Exception Removal**: `javax.ejb.EJBException` replaced with standard `RuntimeException`\n4. **JSON Serialization**: Added `@JsonIgnoreProperties` annotations to prevent circular reference issues during JSON serialization\n5. **Business Logic Preserved**: All entity relationships, validation constraints, and business methods remain intact\n6. **Spring Boot Configuration**: Main application class configured with appropriate Spring annotations\n\nAll files have been written completely and are ready for use in your Spring Boot 3.2 application."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"c05dd363-13a6-48c0-a7bd-daf2b6ed1c11"}
