{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TnV31YKhJHcYschMgyV2vp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.RunStatsDataBean;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeDBService;\n     5→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n     6→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     7→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n     8→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n     9→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.HashMap;\n    12→import java.util.Map;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * REST controller for configuration operations\n    16→ */\n    17→@RestController\n    18→@RequestMapping(\"/api/config\")\n    19→public class ConfigController {\n    20→\n    21→    @Autowired\n    22→    private TradeDBService tradeDBService;\n    23→\n    24→    @GetMapping\n    25→    public ResponseEntity<?> getConfig() {\n    26→        try {\n    27→            Map<String, Object> config = new HashMap<>();\n    28→            config.put(\"maxUsers\", TradeConfig.MAX_USERS);\n    29→            config.put(\"maxQuotes\", TradeConfig.MAX_QUOTES);\n    30→            config.put(\"orderProcessingMode\", TradeConfig.SYNCH);\n    31→\n    32→            // Add runtime mode information if available\n    33→            try {\n    34→                String[] modeNames = TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames();\n    35→                config.put(\"runtimeModeNames\", modeNames);\n    36→            } catch (Exception e) {\n    37→                // If method doesn't exist or fails, continue without it\n    38→            }\n    39→\n    40→            return ResponseEntity.ok(config);\n    41→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    42→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    43→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    44→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    45→        }\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @PostMapping(\"/buildDB\")\n    49→    public ResponseEntity<?> buildDB() {\n    50→        try {\n    51→            boolean result = tradeDBService.buildDB();\n    52→            Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    53→            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n    54→            response.put(\"result\", result ? \"Database built successfully\" : \"Database build completed with warnings\");\n    55→            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n    56→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    57→            Map<String, Object> error = new HashMap<>();\n    58→            error.put(\"status\", \"Error\");\n    59→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    60→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    61→        }\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @PostMapping(\"/resetTrade\")\n    65→    public ResponseEntity<?> resetTrade() {\n    66→        try {\n    67→            RunStatsDataBean stats = tradeDBService.resetTrade();\n    68→            return ResponseEntity.ok(stats);\n    69→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    70→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    71→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    72→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"b8dee3fb-7f24-4d7f-8f85-a809d86e6fa3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011ZssHzACER9RjRMFEwwxGU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n     5→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n     6→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n     7→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\n     8→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     9→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n    10→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    11→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    12→\n    13→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    14→import java.util.Collection;\n    15→import java.util.HashMap;\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * REST controller for account operations\n    20→ */\n    21→@RestController\n    22→@RequestMapping(\"/api/account\")\n    23→public class AccountController {\n    24→\n    25→    @Autowired\n    26→    private TradeService tradeService;\n    27→\n    28→    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n    29→    public ResponseEntity<?> register(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    32→            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n    33→            String fullname = (String) request.get(\"fullname\");\n    34→            String address = (String) request.get(\"address\");\n    35→            String email = (String) request.get(\"email\");\n    36→            String creditcard = (String) request.get(\"creditcard\");\n    37→\n    38→            BigDecimal openBalance;\n    39→            Object balanceObj = request.get(\"openBalance\");\n    40→            if (balanceObj instanceof Number) {\n    41→                openBalance = new BigDecimal(balanceObj.toString());\n    42→            } else if (balanceObj instanceof String) {\n    43→                openBalance = new BigDecimal((String) balanceObj);\n    44→            } else {\n    45→                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid openBalance format\");\n    46→            }\n    47→\n    48→            if (userID == null || password == null || fullname == null) {\n    49→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    50→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password, fullname\");\n    51→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    52→            }\n    53→\n    54→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n    55→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(account);\n    56→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    57→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    58→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    59→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n    64→    public ResponseEntity<?> login(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    65→        try {\n    66→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    67→            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n    68→\n    69→            if (userID == null || password == null) {\n    70→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    71→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password\");\n    72→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    73→            }\n    74→\n    75→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(userID, password);\n    76→            if (account == null) {\n    77→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    78→                error.put(\"error\", \"Invalid credentials\");\n    79→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED).body(error);\n    80→            }\n    81→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n    82→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    83→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    84→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    85→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    86→        }\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    @PostMapping(\"/logout\")\n    90→    public ResponseEntity<?> logout(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    91→        try {\n    92→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    93→\n    94→            if (userID == null) {\n    95→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    96→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required field: userID\");\n    97→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    98→            }\n    99→\n   100→            tradeService.logout(userID);\n   101→            Map<String, String> response = new HashMap<>();\n   102→            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n   103→            response.put(\"message\", \"User logged out successfully\");\n   104→            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n   105→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   106→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   107→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   108→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   109→        }\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}\")\n   113→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   114→        try {\n   115→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n   116→            if (account == null) {\n   117→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   118→                error.put(\"error\", \"Account not found for userID: \" + userID);\n   119→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n   120→            }\n   121→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n   122→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   123→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   124→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   125→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   126→        }\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n   130→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountProfileData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   131→        try {\n   132→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   133→            if (profile == null) {\n   134→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   135→                error.put(\"error\", \"Profile not found for userID: \" + userID);\n   136→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n   137→            }\n   138→            return ResponseEntity.ok(profile);\n   139→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   140→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   141→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   142→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   143→        }\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    @PutMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n   147→    public ResponseEntity<?> updateAccountProfile(@PathVariable String userID, @RequestBody AccountProfileDataBean profileData) {\n   148→        try {\n   149→            // Ensure the userID matches\n   150→            if (profileData.getUserID() == null) {\n   151→                profileData.setUserID(userID);\n   152→            } else if (!userID.equals(profileData.getUserID())) {\n   153→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   154→                error.put(\"error\", \"UserID mismatch between path and body\");\n   155→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n   156→            }\n   157→\n   158→            AccountProfileDataBean updatedProfile = tradeService.updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n   159→            return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedProfile);\n   160→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   161→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   162→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   163→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   164→        }\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/holdings\")\n   168→    public ResponseEntity<?> getHoldings(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   169→        try {\n   170→            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = tradeService.getHoldings(userID);\n   171→            return ResponseEntity.ok(holdings);\n   172→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   173→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   174→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   175→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   176→        }\n   177→    }\n   178→\n   179→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/orders\")\n   180→    public ResponseEntity<?> getOrders(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   181→        try {\n   182→            Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = tradeService.getOrders(userID);\n   183→            return ResponseEntity.ok(orders);\n   184→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   185→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   186→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   187→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   188→        }\n   189→    }\n   190→}\n   191→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"704fb9b3-e500-4a32-9044-ee6ec6d582b7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ebr5GUn9Y82sFePH8ExXno","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service;\n     2→\n     3→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n     4→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→\n     9→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    10→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n    11→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    12→\n    13→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    14→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    15→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    16→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    17→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    18→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories.AccountProfileRepository;\n    19→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories.AccountRepository;\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories.HoldingRepository;\n    21→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories.OrderRepository;\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.repositories.QuoteRepository;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    26→\n    27→@Service\n    28→@Transactional\n    29→public class TradeService implements TradeServices {\n    30→\n    31→    @Autowired\n    32→    private QuoteRepository quoteRepository;\n    33→\n    34→    @Autowired\n    35→    private AccountRepository accountRepository;\n    36→\n    37→    @Autowired\n    38→    private AccountProfileRepository accountProfileRepository;\n    39→\n    40→    @Autowired\n    41→    private HoldingRepository holdingRepository;\n    42→\n    43→    @Autowired\n    44→    private OrderRepository orderRepository;\n    45→\n    46→    @Override\n    47→    public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception {\n    48→        MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryData = null;\n    49→\n    50→        try {\n    51→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n    52→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getMarketSummary - entered\");\n    53→            }\n    54→\n    55→            // Get all quotes ordered by change\n    56→            List<QuoteDataBean> quotes = quoteRepository.findAllOrderByChangeDesc();\n    57→\n    58→            QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[0]);\n    59→\n    60→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    61→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    62→\n    63→            BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    64→            BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    65→            double volume = 0.0;\n    66→\n    67→            if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n    68→                int arraySize = quoteArray.length;\n    69→\n    70→                for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n    71→                    topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n    72→                }\n    73→                for (int i = arraySize - 1; i >= arraySize - 5; i--) {\n    74→                    topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n    75→                }\n    76→\n    77→                for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n    78→                    BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n    79→                    BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n    80→                    double vol = quote.getVolume();\n    81→                    TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n    82→                    openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n    83→                    volume += vol;\n    84→                }\n    85→\n    86→                TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(arraySize), FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n    87→                openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(arraySize), FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n    88→            }\n    89→\n    90→            marketSummaryData = new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, volume, topGainers, topLosers);\n    91→\n    92→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    93→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getMarketSummary -- error getting market summary\", e);\n    94→            throw e;\n    95→        }\n    96→\n    97→        return marketSummaryData;\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    @Override\n   101→    @Transactional\n   102→    public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n   103→        OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   104→\n   105→        try {\n   106→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   107→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:buy - entered with userID=\" + userID + \" symbol=\" + symbol + \" quantity=\" + quantity);\n   108→            }\n   109→\n   110→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID)\n   111→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find profile for user: \" + userID));\n   112→\n   113→            AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   114→            if (account == null) {\n   115→                throw new Exception(\"Cannot find account for user: \" + userID);\n   116→            }\n   117→\n   118→            QuoteDataBean quote = quoteRepository.findById(symbol)\n   119→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find quote for symbol: \" + symbol));\n   120→\n   121→            HoldingDataBean holding = null;\n   122→            orderData = createOrder(account, quote, holding, \"buy\", quantity);\n   123→\n   124→            // Debit the account balance\n   125→            BigDecimal total = quote.getPrice().multiply(new BigDecimal(quantity)).setScale(FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   126→            account.setBalance(account.getBalance().subtract(total));\n   127→            accountRepository.save(account);\n   128→\n   129→            // Complete order immediately (simplified - no JMS)\n   130→            completeOrder(orderData.getOrderID(), false);\n   131→\n   132→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   133→            Log.error(\"TradeService:buy -- error buying stock\", e);\n   134→            throw e;\n   135→        }\n   136→\n   137→        return orderData;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    @Override\n   141→    @Transactional\n   142→    public OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n   143→        OrderDataBean orderData = null;\n   144→\n   145→        try {\n   146→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   147→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:sell - entered with userID=\" + userID + \" holdingID=\" + holdingID);\n   148→            }\n   149→\n   150→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID)\n   151→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find profile for user: \" + userID));\n   152→\n   153→            AccountDataBean account = profile.getAccount();\n   154→            if (account == null) {\n   155→                throw new Exception(\"Cannot find account for user: \" + userID);\n   156→            }\n   157→\n   158→            HoldingDataBean holding = holdingRepository.findById(holdingID)\n   159→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find holding: \" + holdingID));\n   160→\n   161→            if (!holding.getAccount().getAccountID().equals(account.getAccountID())) {\n   162→                throw new Exception(\"Holding \" + holdingID + \" does not belong to user \" + userID);\n   163→            }\n   164→\n   165→            QuoteDataBean quote = quoteRepository.findById(holding.getQuoteSymbol())\n   166→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find quote for symbol: \" + holding.getQuoteSymbol()));\n   167→\n   168→            double quantity = holding.getQuantity();\n   169→            orderData = createOrder(account, quote, holding, \"sell\", quantity);\n   170→\n   171→            // Credit the account balance\n   172→            BigDecimal total = quote.getPrice().multiply(new BigDecimal(quantity)).setScale(FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   173→            account.setBalance(account.getBalance().add(total));\n   174→            accountRepository.save(account);\n   175→\n   176→            // Complete order immediately (simplified - no JMS)\n   177→            completeOrder(orderData.getOrderID(), false);\n   178→\n   179→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   180→            Log.error(\"TradeService:sell -- error selling stock\", e);\n   181→            throw e;\n   182→        }\n   183→\n   184→        return orderData;\n   185→    }\n   186→\n   187→    @Override\n   188→    @Transactional\n   189→    public void completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   190→        try {\n   191→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   192→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:completeOrder - entered with orderID=\" + orderID);\n   193→            }\n   194→\n   195→            OrderDataBean order = orderRepository.findById(orderID)\n   196→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find order: \" + orderID));\n   197→\n   198→            order.setOrderStatus(\"closed\");\n   199→            order.setCompletionDate(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   200→\n   201→            if (\"buy\".equals(order.getOrderType())) {\n   202→                // Create a new holding\n   203→                HoldingDataBean holding = new HoldingDataBean();\n   204→                holding.setQuantity(order.getQuantity());\n   205→                holding.setPurchasePrice(order.getPrice());\n   206→                holding.setPurchaseDate(order.getCompletionDate());\n   207→                holding.setQuoteSymbol(order.getSymbol());\n   208→                holding.setAccount(order.getAccount());\n   209→                holdingRepository.save(holding);\n   210→\n   211→                if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   212→                    Log.trace(\"TradeService:completeOrder -- completed buy order, new holding: \" + holding.getHoldingID());\n   213→                }\n   214→            } else if (\"sell\".equals(order.getOrderType())) {\n   215→                // Remove the holding\n   216→                HoldingDataBean holding = order.getHolding();\n   217→                if (holding != null) {\n   218→                    holdingRepository.delete(holding);\n   219→\n   220→                    if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   221→                        Log.trace(\"TradeService:completeOrder -- completed sell order, removed holding: \" + holding.getHoldingID());\n   222→                    }\n   223→                }\n   224→            }\n   225→\n   226→            orderRepository.save(order);\n   227→\n   228→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   229→            Log.error(\"TradeService:completeOrder -- error completing order \" + orderID, e);\n   230→            throw e;\n   231→        }\n   232→    }\n   233→\n   234→    @Override\n   235→    @Transactional\n   236→    public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   237→        completeOrder(orderID, false);\n   238→        return orderRepository.findById(orderID).orElse(null);\n   239→    }\n   240→\n   241→    @Override\n   242→    @Transactional\n   243→    public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   244→        try {\n   245→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   246→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:cancelOrder - entered with orderID=\" + orderID);\n   247→            }\n   248→\n   249→            OrderDataBean order = orderRepository.findById(orderID)\n   250→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find order: \" + orderID));\n   251→\n   252→            order.setOrderStatus(\"cancelled\");\n   253→            order.setCompletionDate(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   254→            orderRepository.save(order);\n   255→\n   256→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   257→            Log.error(\"TradeService:cancelOrder -- error cancelling order \" + orderID, e);\n   258→            throw e;\n   259→        }\n   260→    }\n   261→\n   262→    @Override\n   263→    public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   264→        if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   265→            Log.trace(\"TradeService:orderCompleted - userID=\" + userID + \" orderID=\" + orderID);\n   266→        }\n   267→        // This is a callback notification - in the original EJB version this would be called\n   268→        // by MDB after processing. For Spring Boot, we complete orders synchronously, so this is a no-op.\n   269→    }\n   270→\n   271→    @Override\n   272→    @Transactional\n   273→    public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception {\n   274→        QuoteDataBean quote = null;\n   275→\n   276→        try {\n   277→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   278→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:createQuote - entered with symbol=\" + symbol);\n   279→            }\n   280→\n   281→            quote = new QuoteDataBean(symbol, companyName, 0, price, price, price, price, 0);\n   282→            quoteRepository.save(quote);\n   283→\n   284→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   285→            Log.error(\"TradeService:createQuote -- error creating quote for symbol \" + symbol, e);\n   286→            throw e;\n   287→        }\n   288→\n   289→        return quote;\n   290→    }\n   291→\n   292→    @Override\n   293→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   294→        QuoteDataBean quote = null;\n   295→\n   296→        try {\n   297→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   298→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getQuote - entered with symbol=\" + symbol);\n   299→            }\n   300→\n   301→            quote = quoteRepository.findById(symbol).orElse(null);\n   302→\n   303→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   304→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getQuote -- error getting quote for symbol \" + symbol, e);\n   305→            throw e;\n   306→        }\n   307→\n   308→        return quote;\n   309→    }\n   310→\n   311→    @Override\n   312→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getAllQuotes() throws Exception {\n   313→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> quotes = null;\n   314→\n   315→        try {\n   316→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   317→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getAllQuotes - entered\");\n   318→            }\n   319→\n   320→            quotes = quoteRepository.findAll();\n   321→\n   322→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   323→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getAllQuotes -- error getting all quotes\", e);\n   324→            throw e;\n   325→        }\n   326→\n   327→        return quotes;\n   328→    }\n   329→\n   330→    @Override\n   331→    @Transactional\n   332→    public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) throws Exception {\n   333→        QuoteDataBean quote = null;\n   334→\n   335→        try {\n   336→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   337→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:updateQuotePriceVolume - entered with symbol=\" + symbol);\n   338→            }\n   339→\n   340→            quote = quoteRepository.findBySymbolForUpdate(symbol);\n   341→            if (quote == null) {\n   342→                throw new Exception(\"Cannot find quote for symbol: \" + symbol);\n   343→            }\n   344→\n   345→            BigDecimal oldPrice = quote.getPrice();\n   346→            BigDecimal newPrice = oldPrice.multiply(changeFactor).setScale(FinancialUtils.SCALE, FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   347→            quote.setPrice(newPrice);\n   348→            quote.setChange1(newPrice.subtract(quote.getOpen()).doubleValue());\n   349→            quote.setVolume(quote.getVolume() + sharesTraded);\n   350→\n   351→            if (newPrice.compareTo(quote.getHigh()) > 0) {\n   352→                quote.setHigh(newPrice);\n   353→            }\n   354→            if (newPrice.compareTo(quote.getLow()) < 0) {\n   355→                quote.setLow(newPrice);\n   356→            }\n   357→\n   358→            quoteRepository.save(quote);\n   359→\n   360→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   361→            Log.error(\"TradeService:updateQuotePriceVolume -- error updating quote for symbol \" + symbol, e);\n   362→            throw e;\n   363→        }\n   364→\n   365→        return quote;\n   366→    }\n   367→\n   368→    @Override\n   369→    @Transactional\n   370→    public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception {\n   371→        AccountDataBean account = null;\n   372→\n   373→        try {\n   374→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   375→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:login - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   376→            }\n   377→\n   378→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID)\n   379→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find profile for user: \" + userID));\n   380→\n   381→            if (!profile.getPassword().equals(password)) {\n   382→                throw new Exception(\"Invalid password for user: \" + userID);\n   383→            }\n   384→\n   385→            account = profile.getAccount();\n   386→            if (account == null) {\n   387→                throw new Exception(\"Cannot find account for user: \" + userID);\n   388→            }\n   389→\n   390→            profile.setLoginCount(profile.getLoginCount() + 1);\n   391→            profile.setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   392→            accountProfileRepository.save(profile);\n   393→\n   394→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   395→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:login -- logged in user: \" + userID);\n   396→            }\n   397→\n   398→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   399→            Log.error(\"TradeService:login -- error logging in user \" + userID, e);\n   400→            throw e;\n   401→        }\n   402→\n   403→        return account;\n   404→    }\n   405→\n   406→    @Override\n   407→    public void logout(String userID) throws Exception {\n   408→        try {\n   409→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   410→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:logout - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   411→            }\n   412→\n   413→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID).orElse(null);\n   414→            if (profile != null) {\n   415→                profile.setLogoutCount(profile.getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   416→                accountProfileRepository.save(profile);\n   417→            }\n   418→\n   419→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   420→            Log.error(\"TradeService:logout -- error logging out user \" + userID, e);\n   421→            throw e;\n   422→        }\n   423→    }\n   424→\n   425→    @Override\n   426→    @Transactional\n   427→    public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) throws Exception {\n   428→        AccountDataBean account = null;\n   429→\n   430→        try {\n   431→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   432→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:register - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   433→            }\n   434→\n   435→            // Check if user already exists\n   436→            if (accountProfileRepository.findById(userID).isPresent()) {\n   437→                throw new Exception(\"User \" + userID + \" already exists\");\n   438→            }\n   439→\n   440→            // Create account\n   441→            account = new AccountDataBean();\n   442→            account.setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   443→            account.setBalance(openBalance);\n   444→            account.setCreationDate(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   445→            account.setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   446→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   447→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   448→            accountRepository.save(account);\n   449→\n   450→            // Create profile\n   451→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   452→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   453→            profile.setPassword(password);\n   454→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   455→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   456→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   457→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   458→            profile.setAccount(account);\n   459→            accountProfileRepository.save(profile);\n   460→\n   461→            // Link account to profile\n   462→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   463→            accountRepository.save(account);\n   464→\n   465→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   466→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:register -- registered new user: \" + userID);\n   467→            }\n   468→\n   469→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   470→            Log.error(\"TradeService:register -- error registering user \" + userID, e);\n   471→            throw e;\n   472→        }\n   473→\n   474→        return account;\n   475→    }\n   476→\n   477→    @Override\n   478→    @Transactional\n   479→    public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, String openBalanceString) throws Exception {\n   480→        BigDecimal openBalance = new BigDecimal(openBalanceString);\n   481→        return register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n   482→    }\n   483→\n   484→    @Override\n   485→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   486→        Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = null;\n   487→\n   488→        try {\n   489→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   490→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getOrders - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   491→            }\n   492→\n   493→            orders = orderRepository.findByAccountProfileUserID(userID);\n   494→\n   495→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   496→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getOrders -- error getting orders for user \" + userID, e);\n   497→            throw e;\n   498→        }\n   499→\n   500→        return orders;\n   501→    }\n   502→\n   503→    @Override\n   504→    @Transactional\n   505→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   506→        Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = null;\n   507→\n   508→        try {\n   509→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   510→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getClosedOrders - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   511→            }\n   512→\n   513→            orders = orderRepository.findClosedOrdersByUserID(userID);\n   514→\n   515→            // Mark them as completed\n   516→            orderRepository.completeClosedOrders(userID);\n   517→\n   518→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   519→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getClosedOrders -- error getting closed orders for user \" + userID, e);\n   520→            throw e;\n   521→        }\n   522→\n   523→        return orders;\n   524→    }\n   525→\n   526→    @Override\n   527→    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception {\n   528→        Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = null;\n   529→\n   530→        try {\n   531→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   532→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getHoldings - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   533→            }\n   534→\n   535→            holdings = holdingRepository.findByAccountProfileUserID(userID);\n   536→\n   537→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   538→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getHoldings -- error getting holdings for user \" + userID, e);\n   539→            throw e;\n   540→        }\n   541→\n   542→        return holdings;\n   543→    }\n   544→\n   545→    @Override\n   546→    public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception {\n   547→        HoldingDataBean holding = null;\n   548→\n   549→        try {\n   550→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   551→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getHolding - entered with holdingID=\" + holdingID);\n   552→            }\n   553→\n   554→            holding = holdingRepository.findById(holdingID).orElse(null);\n   555→\n   556→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   557→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getHolding -- error getting holding \" + holdingID, e);\n   558→            throw e;\n   559→        }\n   560→\n   561→        return holding;\n   562→    }\n   563→\n   564→    @Override\n   565→    public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   566→        AccountDataBean account = null;\n   567→\n   568→        try {\n   569→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   570→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getAccountData - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   571→            }\n   572→\n   573→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID)\n   574→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find profile for user: \" + userID));\n   575→\n   576→            account = profile.getAccount();\n   577→\n   578→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   579→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getAccountData -- error getting account data for user \" + userID, e);\n   580→            throw e;\n   581→        }\n   582→\n   583→        return account;\n   584→    }\n   585→\n   586→    @Override\n   587→    public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   588→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = null;\n   589→\n   590→        try {\n   591→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   592→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:getAccountProfileData - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   593→            }\n   594→\n   595→            profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(userID).orElse(null);\n   596→\n   597→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   598→            Log.error(\"TradeService:getAccountProfileData -- error getting profile data for user \" + userID, e);\n   599→            throw e;\n   600→        }\n   601→\n   602→        return profile;\n   603→    }\n   604→\n   605→    @Override\n   606→    @Transactional\n   607→    public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n   608→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = null;\n   609→\n   610→        try {\n   611→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   612→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:updateAccountProfile - entered with userID=\" + profileData.getUserID());\n   613→            }\n   614→\n   615→            profile = accountProfileRepository.findById(profileData.getUserID())\n   616→                .orElseThrow(() -> new Exception(\"Cannot find profile for user: \" + profileData.getUserID()));\n   617→\n   618→            profile.setAddress(profileData.getAddress());\n   619→            profile.setPassword(profileData.getPassword());\n   620→            profile.setFullName(profileData.getFullName());\n   621→            profile.setEmail(profileData.getEmail());\n   622→            profile.setCreditCard(profileData.getCreditCard());\n   623→\n   624→            accountProfileRepository.save(profile);\n   625→\n   626→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   627→            Log.error(\"TradeService:updateAccountProfile -- error updating profile for user \" + profileData.getUserID(), e);\n   628→            throw e;\n   629→        }\n   630→\n   631→        return profile;\n   632→    }\n   633→\n   634→    private OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType, double quantity) {\n   635→        try {\n   636→            OrderDataBean order = new OrderDataBean();\n   637→            order.setOrderType(orderType);\n   638→            order.setOrderStatus(\"open\");\n   639→            order.setOpenDate(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   640→            order.setQuantity(quantity);\n   641→            order.setPrice(quote.getPrice());\n   642→            order.setOrderFee(TradeConfig.getOrderFee(orderType));\n   643→            order.setAccount(account);\n   644→            order.setQuote(quote);\n   645→            order.setSymbol(quote.getSymbol());\n   646→            order.setHolding(holding);\n   647→\n   648→            orderRepository.save(order);\n   649→\n   650→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   651→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:createOrder -- created order \" + order.getOrderID() + \" for \" + orderType);\n   652→            }\n   653→\n   654→            return order;\n   655→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   656→            Log.error(\"TradeService:createOrder -- error creating order\", e);\n   657→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   658→        }\n   659→    }\n   660→\n   661→    @Override\n   662→    public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   663→        // In the original EJB version, this would queue to JMS\n   664→        // For Spring Boot, we complete orders synchronously\n   665→        completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   666→    }\n   667→\n   668→    @Override\n   669→    public OrderDataBean completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   670→        // In the original EJB version, this would be async via MDB\n   671→        // For Spring Boot, we complete orders synchronously\n   672→        return completeOrder(orderID);\n   673→    }\n   674→\n   675→    @Override\n   676→    public void pingTwoPhase() throws Exception {\n   677→        if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   678→            Log.trace(\"TradeService:pingTwoPhase - simple ping\");\n   679→        }\n   680→        // Simple no-op for two-phase commit testing\n   681→    }\n   682→\n   683→    @Override\n   684→    public double investmentReturn(String userID, double investment) throws Exception {\n   685→        double currentValue = 0.0;\n   686→\n   687→        try {\n   688→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   689→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:investmentReturn - entered with userID=\" + userID);\n   690→            }\n   691→\n   692→            AccountDataBean account = getAccountData(userID);\n   693→            if (account != null) {\n   694→                currentValue = account.getBalance().doubleValue();\n   695→            }\n   696→\n   697→            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = getHoldings(userID);\n   698→            for (HoldingDataBean holding : holdings) {\n   699→                QuoteDataBean quote = getQuote(holding.getQuoteSymbol());\n   700→                if (quote != null) {\n   701→                    currentValue += holding.getQuantity() * quote.getPrice().doubleValue();\n   702→                }\n   703→            }\n   704→\n   705→            double returnValue = currentValue - investment;\n   706→\n   707→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   708→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:investmentReturn -- investment=\" + investment + \" current=\" + currentValue + \" return=\" + returnValue);\n   709→            }\n   710→\n   711→            return returnValue;\n   712→\n   713→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   714→            Log.error(\"TradeService:investmentReturn -- error calculating return for user \" + userID, e);\n   715→            throw e;\n   716→        }\n   717→    }\n   718→\n   719→    @Override\n   720→    public void setInSession(String userID, Object value) throws Exception {\n   721→        // This was used for session management in the servlet version\n   722→        // For Spring Boot, session management is handled differently\n   723→        // This is a no-op stub\n   724→        if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   725→            Log.trace(\"TradeService:setInSession - userID=\" + userID);\n   726→        }\n   727→    }\n   728→\n   729→    @Override\n   730→    public int getImpl() {\n   731→        return 0; // Return 0 to indicate Spring/JPA implementation\n   732→    }\n   733→\n   734→    @Override\n   735→    @Transactional\n   736→    public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhaseCommit() throws Exception {\n   737→        if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   738→            Log.trace(\"TradeService:pingTwoPhaseCommit - entered\");\n   739→        }\n   740→\n   741→        // Simple two-phase commit test - create and retrieve a test quote\n   742→        String symbol = \"TEST_2PC\";\n   743→        QuoteDataBean quote = quoteRepository.findById(symbol).orElse(null);\n   744→\n   745→        if (quote == null) {\n   746→            quote = createQuote(symbol, \"Test Two Phase Commit\", new BigDecimal(\"100.00\"));\n   747→        } else {\n   748→            // Update the price slightly\n   749→            BigDecimal newPrice = quote.getPrice().add(BigDecimal.ONE);\n   750→            quote.setPrice(newPrice);\n   751→            quoteRepository.save(quote);\n   752→        }\n   753→\n   754→        return quote;\n   755→    }\n   756→\n   757→    @Override\n   758→    @Transactional\n   759→    public void resetTrade(boolean deleteAll) throws Exception {\n   760→        try {\n   761→            if (Log.doTrace()) {\n   762→                Log.trace(\"TradeService:resetTrade - entered with deleteAll=\" + deleteAll);\n   763→            }\n   764→\n   765→            if (deleteAll) {\n   766→                // Delete all data\n   767→                orderRepository.deleteAll();\n   768→                holdingRepository.deleteAll();\n   769→                accountRepository.deleteAll();\n   770→                accountProfileRepository.deleteAll();\n   771→                quoteRepository.deleteAll();\n   772→\n   773→                Log.log(\"TradeService:resetTrade -- deleted all trade data\");\n   774→            } else {\n   775→                // Just reset order statuses\n   776→                List<OrderDataBean> orders = orderRepository.findAll();\n   777→                for (OrderDataBean order : orders) {\n   778→                    if (\"closed\".equals(order.getOrderStatus())) {\n   779→                        order.setOrderStatus(\"completed\");\n   780→                    }\n   781→                }\n   782→                orderRepository.saveAll(orders);\n   783→\n   784→                Log.log(\"TradeService:resetTrade -- reset order statuses\");\n   785→            }\n   786→\n   787→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   788→            Log.error(\"TradeService:resetTrade -- error resetting trade\", e);\n   789→            throw e;\n   790→        }\n   791→    }\n   792→}\n   793→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"abb5ad51-3356-442d-9c76-121651773d40"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01G8UPze77vHW5QDQ38r6FZQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see several issues that need fixing:\n\n1. `TradeService` implements `TradeServices` - an interface that no longer exists (it was deleted with the old code)\n2. `ConfigController` references `RunStatsDataBean` from wrong package and `TradeConfig.MAX_USERS/MAX_QUOTES` as public fields but they're private\n3. `ConfigController.buildDB()` expects boolean return but our TradeDBService returns String\n4. `AccountProfileDataBean` has `loginCount`/`logoutCount`/`lastLogin` fields used in TradeService but those fields are on AccountDataBean\n\nLet me fix all these issues:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3837,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10649,"cache_read_input_tokens":106352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":10649,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":605},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"dba5a129-156c-44c3-bee4-071b11836de5"}
