{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KjrbHegRG3M8GPmbeRt6M7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     6→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n     7→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n     8→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n     9→\n    10→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    11→import java.util.Collection;\n    12→import java.util.HashMap;\n    13→import java.util.Map;\n    14→\n    15→/**\n    16→ * REST controller for quote operations\n    17→ */\n    18→@RestController\n    19→@RequestMapping(\"/api/quotes\")\n    20→public class QuoteController {\n    21→\n    22→    @Autowired\n    23→    private TradeService tradeService;\n    24→\n    25→    @GetMapping\n    26→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAllQuotes() {\n    27→        try {\n    28→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> quotes = tradeService.getAllQuotes();\n    29→            return ResponseEntity.ok(quotes);\n    30→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    31→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    32→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    33→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    34→        }\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    @GetMapping(\"/{symbol}\")\n    38→    public ResponseEntity<?> getQuote(@PathVariable String symbol) {\n    39→        try {\n    40→            QuoteDataBean quote = tradeService.getQuote(symbol);\n    41→            if (quote == null) {\n    42→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    43→                error.put(\"error\", \"Quote not found for symbol: \" + symbol);\n    44→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n    45→            }\n    46→            return ResponseEntity.ok(quote);\n    47→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    48→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    49→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    50→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    51→        }\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    @PostMapping\n    55→    public ResponseEntity<?> createQuote(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    56→        try {\n    57→            String symbol = (String) request.get(\"symbol\");\n    58→            String companyName = (String) request.get(\"companyName\");\n    59→            BigDecimal price;\n    60→\n    61→            Object priceObj = request.get(\"price\");\n    62→            if (priceObj instanceof Number) {\n    63→                price = new BigDecimal(priceObj.toString());\n    64→            } else if (priceObj instanceof String) {\n    65→                price = new BigDecimal((String) priceObj);\n    66→            } else {\n    67→                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid price format\");\n    68→            }\n    69→\n    70→            if (symbol == null || companyName == null || price == null) {\n    71→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    72→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: symbol, companyName, price\");\n    73→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    74→            }\n    75→\n    76→            QuoteDataBean quote = tradeService.createQuote(symbol, companyName, price);\n    77→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(quote);\n    78→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    79→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    80→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    81→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    82→        }\n    83→    }\n    84→}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"39693b4f-2054-4749-933c-f215f2627e36"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L8TSm3kEqLyf4GwNGGGAiJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n     5→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n     6→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n     7→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeService;\n     8→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     9→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n    10→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    11→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    12→\n    13→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    14→import java.util.Collection;\n    15→import java.util.HashMap;\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * REST controller for account operations\n    20→ */\n    21→@RestController\n    22→@RequestMapping(\"/api/account\")\n    23→public class AccountController {\n    24→\n    25→    @Autowired\n    26→    private TradeService tradeService;\n    27→\n    28→    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n    29→    public ResponseEntity<?> register(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    32→            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n    33→            String fullname = (String) request.get(\"fullname\");\n    34→            String address = (String) request.get(\"address\");\n    35→            String email = (String) request.get(\"email\");\n    36→            String creditcard = (String) request.get(\"creditcard\");\n    37→\n    38→            BigDecimal openBalance;\n    39→            Object balanceObj = request.get(\"openBalance\");\n    40→            if (balanceObj instanceof Number) {\n    41→                openBalance = new BigDecimal(balanceObj.toString());\n    42→            } else if (balanceObj instanceof String) {\n    43→                openBalance = new BigDecimal((String) balanceObj);\n    44→            } else {\n    45→                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid openBalance format\");\n    46→            }\n    47→\n    48→            if (userID == null || password == null || fullname == null) {\n    49→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    50→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password, fullname\");\n    51→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    52→            }\n    53→\n    54→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n    55→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(account);\n    56→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    57→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    58→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    59→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    60→        }\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n    64→    public ResponseEntity<?> login(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    65→        try {\n    66→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    67→            String password = (String) request.get(\"password\");\n    68→\n    69→            if (userID == null || password == null) {\n    70→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    71→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required fields: userID, password\");\n    72→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    73→            }\n    74→\n    75→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(userID, password);\n    76→            if (account == null) {\n    77→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    78→                error.put(\"error\", \"Invalid credentials\");\n    79→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED).body(error);\n    80→            }\n    81→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n    82→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    83→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    84→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    85→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    86→        }\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    @PostMapping(\"/logout\")\n    90→    public ResponseEntity<?> logout(@RequestBody Map<String, Object> request) {\n    91→        try {\n    92→            String userID = (String) request.get(\"userID\");\n    93→\n    94→            if (userID == null) {\n    95→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    96→                error.put(\"error\", \"Missing required field: userID\");\n    97→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n    98→            }\n    99→\n   100→            tradeService.logout(userID);\n   101→            Map<String, String> response = new HashMap<>();\n   102→            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n   103→            response.put(\"message\", \"User logged out successfully\");\n   104→            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n   105→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   106→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   107→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   108→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   109→        }\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}\")\n   113→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   114→        try {\n   115→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n   116→            if (account == null) {\n   117→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   118→                error.put(\"error\", \"Account not found for userID: \" + userID);\n   119→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n   120→            }\n   121→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n   122→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   123→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   124→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   125→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   126→        }\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n   130→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountProfileData(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   131→        try {\n   132→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   133→            if (profile == null) {\n   134→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   135→                error.put(\"error\", \"Profile not found for userID: \" + userID);\n   136→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND).body(error);\n   137→            }\n   138→            return ResponseEntity.ok(profile);\n   139→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   140→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   141→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   142→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   143→        }\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    @PutMapping(\"/{userID}/profile\")\n   147→    public ResponseEntity<?> updateAccountProfile(@PathVariable String userID, @RequestBody AccountProfileDataBean profileData) {\n   148→        try {\n   149→            // Ensure the userID matches\n   150→            if (profileData.getUserID() == null) {\n   151→                profileData.setUserID(userID);\n   152→            } else if (!userID.equals(profileData.getUserID())) {\n   153→                Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   154→                error.put(\"error\", \"UserID mismatch between path and body\");\n   155→                return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST).body(error);\n   156→            }\n   157→\n   158→            AccountProfileDataBean updatedProfile = tradeService.updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n   159→            return ResponseEntity.ok(updatedProfile);\n   160→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   161→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   162→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   163→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   164→        }\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/holdings\")\n   168→    public ResponseEntity<?> getHoldings(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   169→        try {\n   170→            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = tradeService.getHoldings(userID);\n   171→            return ResponseEntity.ok(holdings);\n   172→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   173→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   174→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   175→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   176→        }\n   177→    }\n   178→\n   179→    @GetMapping(\"/{userID}/orders\")\n   180→    public ResponseEntity<?> getOrders(@PathVariable String userID) {\n   181→        try {\n   182→            Collection<OrderDataBean> orders = tradeService.getOrders(userID);\n   183→            return ResponseEntity.ok(orders);\n   184→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   185→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n   186→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n   187→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n   188→        }\n   189→    }\n   190→}\n   191→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"532ca283-0896-405a-954b-60e9c5089da3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KPENbL87vXdVo9zdy73MZP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n     4→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.service.TradeDBService;\n     5→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n     6→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     7→import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;\n     8→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n     9→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    10→\n    11→import java.util.HashMap;\n    12→import java.util.Map;\n    13→\n    14→@RestController\n    15→@RequestMapping(\"/api/config\")\n    16→public class ConfigController {\n    17→\n    18→    @Autowired\n    19→    private TradeDBService tradeDBService;\n    20→\n    21→    @GetMapping\n    22→    public ResponseEntity<?> getConfig() {\n    23→        try {\n    24→            Map<String, Object> config = new HashMap<>();\n    25→            config.put(\"runtimeMode\", \"Spring Boot\");\n    26→            config.put(\"maxUsers\", TradeConfig.getMAX_USERS());\n    27→            config.put(\"maxQuotes\", TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES());\n    28→            config.put(\"orderProcessingMode\", TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n    29→            config.put(\"runtimeModeNames\", TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames());\n    30→            config.put(\"orderProcessingModeNames\", TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingModeNames());\n    31→            return ResponseEntity.ok(config);\n    32→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    33→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    34→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    35→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    36→        }\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @PostMapping(\"/buildDB\")\n    40→    public ResponseEntity<?> buildDB() {\n    41→        try {\n    42→            String result = tradeDBService.buildDB();\n    43→            Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    44→            response.put(\"status\", \"Success\");\n    45→            response.put(\"result\", result);\n    46→            return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n    47→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    48→            Map<String, Object> error = new HashMap<>();\n    49→            error.put(\"status\", \"Error\");\n    50→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    51→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    @PostMapping(\"/resetTrade\")\n    56→    public ResponseEntity<?> resetTrade() {\n    57→        try {\n    58→            RunStatsDataBean stats = tradeDBService.resetTrade(true);\n    59→            return ResponseEntity.ok(stats);\n    60→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    61→            Map<String, String> error = new HashMap<>();\n    62→            error.put(\"error\", e.getMessage());\n    63→            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).body(error);\n    64→        }\n    65→    }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"4bf85de6-4cee-4b5b-be2c-85c2baee33f7"}
