{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KKyax4Eg5MkFYUeC9XUQQY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    29→\n    30→public class MarketSummaryDataBean implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 650652242288745600L;\n    33→    private BigDecimal TSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average */\n    34→    private BigDecimal openTSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average at the open */\n    35→    private double volume; /* volume of shares traded */\n    36→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers;\n    37→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers;\n    38→    private Date summaryDate; /* Date this summary was taken */\n    39→\n    40→    // cache the gainPercent once computed for this bean\n    41→    private BigDecimal gainPercent = null;\n    42→\n    43→    public MarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public MarketSummaryDataBean(BigDecimal TSIA, BigDecimal openTSIA, double volume,\n    47→            Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n    48→        setTSIA(TSIA);\n    49→        setOpenTSIA(openTSIA);\n    50→        setVolume(volume);\n    51→        setTopGainers(topGainers);\n    52→        setTopLosers(topLosers);\n    53→        setSummaryDate(new java.sql.Date(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n    54→        gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    public static MarketSummaryDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    58→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> gain = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    59→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> lose = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    60→\n    61→        for (int ii = 0; ii < 5; ii++) {\n    62→            QuoteDataBean quote1 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    63→            QuoteDataBean quote2 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    64→            gain.add(quote1);\n    65→            lose.add(quote2);\n    66→        }\n    67→\n    68→        return new MarketSummaryDataBean(TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f),\n    69→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), gain, lose);\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    @Override\n    73→    public String toString() {\n    74→        String ret = \"\\n\\tMarket Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t        TSIA:\" + getTSIA()\n    75→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA() + \"\\n\\t\\t        gain:\" + getGainPercent()\n    76→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume:\" + getVolume();\n    77→\n    78→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n    79→            return ret;\n    80→        }\n    81→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Gainers:\";\n    82→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n    83→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n    84→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n    85→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n    86→        }\n    87→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Losers:\";\n    88→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n    89→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n    90→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n    91→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n    92→        }\n    93→        return ret;\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    public String toHTML() {\n    97→        String ret = \"<BR>Market Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"<LI>        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"</LI>\"\n    98→                + \"<LI>    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      volume:\" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\";\n    99→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n   100→            return ret;\n   101→        }\n   102→        ret += \"<BR> Current Top Gainers:\";\n   103→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n   104→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   105→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   106→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   107→        }\n   108→        ret += \"<BR>   Current Top Losers:\";\n   109→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n   110→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   111→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   112→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   113→        }\n   114→        return ret;\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public void print() {\n   118→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   119→    }\n   120→\n   121→    public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   122→        if (gainPercent == null) {\n   123→            gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n   124→        }\n   125→        return gainPercent;\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    public BigDecimal getTSIA() {\n   129→        return TSIA;\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    public void setTSIA(BigDecimal tSIA) {\n   133→        TSIA = tSIA;\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    public BigDecimal getOpenTSIA() {\n   137→        return openTSIA;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public void setOpenTSIA(BigDecimal openTSIA) {\n   141→        this.openTSIA = openTSIA;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public double getVolume() {\n   145→        return volume;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   149→        this.volume = volume;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopGainers() {\n   153→        return topGainers;\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public void setTopGainers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers) {\n   157→        this.topGainers = topGainers;\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopLosers() {\n   161→        return topLosers;\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    public void setTopLosers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n   165→        this.topLosers = topLosers;\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    public Date getSummaryDate() {\n   169→        return summaryDate;\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public void setSummaryDate(Date summaryDate) {\n   173→        this.summaryDate = summaryDate;\n   174→    }\n   175→}\n   176→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"883bb534-9436-4e8b-82e0-53fc9bd80504"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FhDW4T9gi53vCYFzTSQaJ2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# DayTrader Spring Boot Configuration\n     2→server.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# H2 Database Configuration\n     5→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n     6→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     7→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     8→spring.datasource.password=\n     9→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    10→spring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n    11→\n    12→# JPA/Hibernate Configuration\n    13→spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n    14→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update\n    15→spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n    16→spring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n    17→\n    18→# Jackson JSON Configuration\n    19→spring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n    20→spring.jackson.serialization.write-dates-as-timestamps=true\n    21→\n    22→# Logging\n    23→logging.level.root=INFO\n    24→logging.level.com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader=INFO\n    25→logging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=WARN\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac4f36ad-05ed-4d27-a34f-96d57675074f","uuid":"55da6ea2-cd90-4c4c-a349-1b06465b413c"}
