{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DUMsbEXaceATsQkyHcDYNo","type":"tool_result","content":"   322→    @Transactional\n   323→    public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname,\n   324→            String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) throws Exception {\n   325→        // Check if user already exists\n   326→        if (accountProfileRepository.findById(userID).isPresent()) {\n   327→            Log.error(\"Failed to register new Account - AccountProfile with userID(\" + userID + \") already exists\");\n   328→            return null;\n   329→        }\n   330→\n   331→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard);\n   332→        // Save profile first (it has no FK to account)\n   333→        accountProfileRepository.save(profile);\n   334→\n   335→        AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean(0, 0, null,\n   336→            new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()), openBalance, openBalance, userID);\n   337→\n   338→        // Set the owning side FK reference (account -> profile)\n   339→        account.setProfile(profile);\n   340→\n   341→        // Save account (owns the FK PROFILE_USERID)\n   342→        accountRepository.save(account);\n   343→\n   344→        // Now set the inverse reference for in-memory consistency\n   345→        profile.setAccount(account);\n   346→\n   347→        return account;\n   348→    }\n   349→\n   350→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   351→        return orderRepository.findByAccountProfileUserID(userID);\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or a